83/* FIX: we don't handle multiple link local scopes */
84/* "scopeless" replacement IN6_ARE_ADDR_EQUAL */
85#ifdef INET6
86int
87SCTP6_ARE_ADDR_EQUAL(struct sockaddr_in6 *a, struct sockaddr_in6 *b)
88{
89#ifdef SCTP_EMBEDDED_V6_SCOPE
90#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
91 struct in6_addr tmp_a, tmp_b;
92
93 tmp_a = a->sin6_addr;
94#if defined(APPLE_LEOPARD) || defined(APPLE_SNOWLEOPARD)
95 if (in6_embedscope(&tmp_a, a, NULL, NULL) != 0) {
96#else
97 if (in6_embedscope(&tmp_a, a, NULL, NULL, NULL) != 0) {
98#endif
99 return (0);
100 }
101 tmp_b = b->sin6_addr;
102#if defined(APPLE_LEOPARD) || defined(APPLE_SNOWLEOPARD)
103 if (in6_embedscope(&tmp_b, b, NULL, NULL) != 0) {
104#else
105 if (in6_embedscope(&tmp_b, b, NULL, NULL, NULL) != 0) {
106#endif
107 return (0);
108 }
109 return (IN6_ARE_ADDR_EQUAL(&tmp_a, &tmp_b));
110#elif defined(SCTP_KAME)
111 struct sockaddr_in6 tmp_a, tmp_b;
112
113 memcpy(&tmp_a, a, sizeof(struct sockaddr_in6));
114 if (sa6_embedscope(&tmp_a, MODULE_GLOBAL(ip6_use_defzone)) != 0) {
115 return (0);
116 }
117 memcpy(&tmp_b, b, sizeof(struct sockaddr_in6));
118 if (sa6_embedscope(&tmp_b, MODULE_GLOBAL(ip6_use_defzone)) != 0) {
119 return (0);
120 }
121 return (IN6_ARE_ADDR_EQUAL(&tmp_a.sin6_addr, &tmp_b.sin6_addr));
122#else
123 struct in6_addr tmp_a, tmp_b;
124
125 tmp_a = a->sin6_addr;
126 if (in6_embedscope(&tmp_a, a) != 0) {
127 return (0);
128 }
129 tmp_b = b->sin6_addr;
130 if (in6_embedscope(&tmp_b, b) != 0) {
131 return (0);
132 }
133 return (IN6_ARE_ADDR_EQUAL(&tmp_a, &tmp_b));
134#endif
135#else
136 return (IN6_ARE_ADDR_EQUAL(&(a->sin6_addr), &(b->sin6_addr)));
137#endif /* SCTP_EMBEDDED_V6_SCOPE */
138}
139#endif
140
141void
142sctp_fill_pcbinfo(struct sctp_pcbinfo *spcb)
143{
144 /*
145 * We really don't need to lock this, but I will just because it
146 * does not hurt.
147 */
148 SCTP_INP_INFO_RLOCK();
149 spcb->ep_count = SCTP_BASE_INFO(ipi_count_ep);
150 spcb->asoc_count = SCTP_BASE_INFO(ipi_count_asoc);
151 spcb->laddr_count = SCTP_BASE_INFO(ipi_count_laddr);
152 spcb->raddr_count = SCTP_BASE_INFO(ipi_count_raddr);
153 spcb->chk_count = SCTP_BASE_INFO(ipi_count_chunk);
154 spcb->readq_count = SCTP_BASE_INFO(ipi_count_readq);
155 spcb->stream_oque = SCTP_BASE_INFO(ipi_count_strmoq);
156 spcb->free_chunks = SCTP_BASE_INFO(ipi_free_chunks);
157 SCTP_INP_INFO_RUNLOCK();
158}
159
160/*-
161 * Addresses are added to VRF's (Virtual Router's). For BSD we
162 * have only the default VRF 0. We maintain a hash list of
163 * VRF's. Each VRF has its own list of sctp_ifn's. Each of
164 * these has a list of addresses. When we add a new address
165 * to a VRF we lookup the ifn/ifn_index, if the ifn does
166 * not exist we create it and add it to the list of IFN's
167 * within the VRF. Once we have the sctp_ifn, we add the
168 * address to the list. So we look something like:
169 *
170 * hash-vrf-table
171 * vrf-> ifn-> ifn -> ifn
172 * vrf |
173 * ... +--ifa-> ifa -> ifa
174 * vrf
175 *
176 * We keep these separate lists since the SCTP subsystem will
177 * point to these from its source address selection nets structure.
178 * When an address is deleted it does not happen right away on
179 * the SCTP side, it gets scheduled. What we do when a
180 * delete happens is immediately remove the address from
181 * the master list and decrement the refcount. As our
182 * addip iterator works through and frees the src address
183 * selection pointing to the sctp_ifa, eventually the refcount
184 * will reach 0 and we will delete it. Note that it is assumed
185 * that any locking on system level ifn/ifa is done at the
186 * caller of these functions and these routines will only
187 * lock the SCTP structures as they add or delete things.
188 *
189 * Other notes on VRF concepts.
190 * - An endpoint can be in multiple VRF's
191 * - An association lives within a VRF and only one VRF.
192 * - Any incoming packet we can deduce the VRF for by
193 * looking at the mbuf/pak inbound (for BSD its VRF=0 :D)
194 * - Any downward send call or connect call must supply the
195 * VRF via ancillary data or via some sort of set default
196 * VRF socket option call (again for BSD no brainer since
197 * the VRF is always 0).
198 * - An endpoint may add multiple VRF's to it.
199 * - Listening sockets can accept associations in any
200 * of the VRF's they are in but the assoc will end up
201 * in only one VRF (gotten from the packet or connect/send).
202 *
203 */
204
205struct sctp_vrf *
206sctp_allocate_vrf(int vrf_id)
207{
208 struct sctp_vrf *vrf = NULL;
209 struct sctp_vrflist *bucket;
210
211 /* First allocate the VRF structure */
212 vrf = sctp_find_vrf(vrf_id);
213 if (vrf) {
214 /* Already allocated */
215 return (vrf);
216 }
217 SCTP_MALLOC(vrf, struct sctp_vrf *, sizeof(struct sctp_vrf),
218 SCTP_M_VRF);
219 if (vrf == NULL) {
220 /* No memory */
221#ifdef INVARIANTS
222 panic("No memory for VRF:%d", vrf_id);
223#endif
224 return (NULL);
225 }
226 /* setup the VRF */
227 memset(vrf, 0, sizeof(struct sctp_vrf));
228 vrf->vrf_id = vrf_id;
229 LIST_INIT(&vrf->ifnlist);
230 vrf->total_ifa_count = 0;
231 vrf->refcount = 0;
232 /* now also setup table ids */
233 SCTP_INIT_VRF_TABLEID(vrf);
234 /* Init the HASH of addresses */
235 vrf->vrf_addr_hash = SCTP_HASH_INIT(SCTP_VRF_ADDR_HASH_SIZE,
236 &vrf->vrf_addr_hashmark);
237 if (vrf->vrf_addr_hash == NULL) {
238 /* No memory */
239#ifdef INVARIANTS
240 panic("No memory for VRF:%d", vrf_id);
241#endif
242 SCTP_FREE(vrf, SCTP_M_VRF);
243 return (NULL);
244 }
245
246 /* Add it to the hash table */
247 bucket = &SCTP_BASE_INFO(sctp_vrfhash)[(vrf_id & SCTP_BASE_INFO(hashvrfmark))];
248 LIST_INSERT_HEAD(bucket, vrf, next_vrf);
249 atomic_add_int(&SCTP_BASE_INFO(ipi_count_vrfs), 1);
250 return (vrf);
251}
252
253struct sctp_ifn *
254sctp_find_ifn(void *ifn, uint32_t ifn_index)
255{
256 struct sctp_ifn *sctp_ifnp;
257 struct sctp_ifnlist *hash_ifn_head;
258
259 /* We assume the lock is held for the addresses
260 * if that's wrong problems could occur :-)
261 */
262 SCTP_IPI_ADDR_LOCK_ASSERT();
263 hash_ifn_head = &SCTP_BASE_INFO(vrf_ifn_hash)[(ifn_index & SCTP_BASE_INFO(vrf_ifn_hashmark))];
264 LIST_FOREACH(sctp_ifnp, hash_ifn_head, next_bucket) {
265 if (sctp_ifnp->ifn_index == ifn_index) {
266 return (sctp_ifnp);
267 }
268 if (sctp_ifnp->ifn_p && ifn && (sctp_ifnp->ifn_p == ifn)) {
269 return (sctp_ifnp);
270 }
271 }
272 return (NULL);
273}
274
275struct sctp_vrf *
276sctp_find_vrf(uint32_t vrf_id)
277{
278 struct sctp_vrflist *bucket;
279 struct sctp_vrf *liste;
280
281 bucket = &SCTP_BASE_INFO(sctp_vrfhash)[(vrf_id & SCTP_BASE_INFO(hashvrfmark))];
282 LIST_FOREACH(liste, bucket, next_vrf) {
283 if (vrf_id == liste->vrf_id) {
284 return (liste);
285 }
286 }
287 return (NULL);
288}
289
290void
291sctp_free_vrf(struct sctp_vrf *vrf)
292{
293 if (SCTP_DECREMENT_AND_CHECK_REFCOUNT(&vrf->refcount)) {
294 if (vrf->vrf_addr_hash) {
295 SCTP_HASH_FREE(vrf->vrf_addr_hash, vrf->vrf_addr_hashmark);
296 vrf->vrf_addr_hash = NULL;
297 }
298 /* We zero'd the count */
299 LIST_REMOVE(vrf, next_vrf);
300 SCTP_FREE(vrf, SCTP_M_VRF);
301 atomic_subtract_int(&SCTP_BASE_INFO(ipi_count_vrfs), 1);
302 }
303}
304
305void
306sctp_free_ifn(struct sctp_ifn *sctp_ifnp)
307{
308 if (SCTP_DECREMENT_AND_CHECK_REFCOUNT(&sctp_ifnp->refcount)) {
309 /* We zero'd the count */
310 if (sctp_ifnp->vrf) {
311 sctp_free_vrf(sctp_ifnp->vrf);
312 }
313 SCTP_FREE(sctp_ifnp, SCTP_M_IFN);
314 atomic_subtract_int(&SCTP_BASE_INFO(ipi_count_ifns), 1);
315 }
316}
317
318void
319sctp_update_ifn_mtu(uint32_t ifn_index, uint32_t mtu)
320{
321 struct sctp_ifn *sctp_ifnp;
322
323 sctp_ifnp = sctp_find_ifn((void *)NULL, ifn_index);
324 if (sctp_ifnp != NULL) {
325 sctp_ifnp->ifn_mtu = mtu;
326 }
327}
328
329void
330sctp_free_ifa(struct sctp_ifa *sctp_ifap)
331{
332 if (SCTP_DECREMENT_AND_CHECK_REFCOUNT(&sctp_ifap->refcount)) {
333 /* We zero'd the count */
334 if (sctp_ifap->ifn_p) {
335 sctp_free_ifn(sctp_ifap->ifn_p);
336 }
337 SCTP_FREE(sctp_ifap, SCTP_M_IFA);
338 atomic_subtract_int(&SCTP_BASE_INFO(ipi_count_ifas), 1);
339 }
340}
341
342static void
343sctp_delete_ifn(struct sctp_ifn *sctp_ifnp, int hold_addr_lock)
344{
345 struct sctp_ifn *found;
346
347 found = sctp_find_ifn(sctp_ifnp->ifn_p, sctp_ifnp->ifn_index);
348 if (found == NULL) {
349 /* Not in the list.. sorry */
350 return;
351 }
352 if (hold_addr_lock == 0) {
353 SCTP_IPI_ADDR_WLOCK();
354 } else {
355 SCTP_IPI_ADDR_WLOCK_ASSERT();
356 }
357 LIST_REMOVE(sctp_ifnp, next_bucket);
358 LIST_REMOVE(sctp_ifnp, next_ifn);
359 if (hold_addr_lock == 0) {
360 SCTP_IPI_ADDR_WUNLOCK();
361 }
362 /* Take away the reference, and possibly free it */
363 sctp_free_ifn(sctp_ifnp);
364}
365
366void
367sctp_mark_ifa_addr_down(uint32_t vrf_id, struct sockaddr *addr,
368 const char *if_name, uint32_t ifn_index)
369{
370 struct sctp_vrf *vrf;
371 struct sctp_ifa *sctp_ifap;
372
373 SCTP_IPI_ADDR_RLOCK();
374 vrf = sctp_find_vrf(vrf_id);
375 if (vrf == NULL) {
376 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_PCB4, "Can't find vrf_id 0x%x\n", vrf_id);
377 goto out;
378 }
379 sctp_ifap = sctp_find_ifa_by_addr(addr, vrf->vrf_id, SCTP_ADDR_LOCKED);
380 if (sctp_ifap == NULL) {
381 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_PCB4, "Can't find sctp_ifap for address\n");
382 goto out;
383 }
384 if (sctp_ifap->ifn_p == NULL) {
385 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_PCB4, "IFA has no IFN - can't mark unusable\n");
386 goto out;
387 }
388 if (if_name) {
389 if (strncmp(if_name, sctp_ifap->ifn_p->ifn_name, SCTP_IFNAMSIZ) != 0) {
390 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_PCB4, "IFN %s of IFA not the same as %s\n",
391 sctp_ifap->ifn_p->ifn_name, if_name);
392 goto out;
393 }
394 } else {
395 if (sctp_ifap->ifn_p->ifn_index != ifn_index) {
396 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_PCB4, "IFA owned by ifn_index:%d down command for ifn_index:%d - ignored\n",
397 sctp_ifap->ifn_p->ifn_index, ifn_index);
398 goto out;
399 }
400 }
401
402 sctp_ifap->localifa_flags &= (~SCTP_ADDR_VALID);
403 sctp_ifap->localifa_flags |= SCTP_ADDR_IFA_UNUSEABLE;
404 out:
405 SCTP_IPI_ADDR_RUNLOCK();
406}
407
408void
409sctp_mark_ifa_addr_up(uint32_t vrf_id, struct sockaddr *addr,
410 const char *if_name, uint32_t ifn_index)
411{
412 struct sctp_vrf *vrf;
413 struct sctp_ifa *sctp_ifap;
414
415 SCTP_IPI_ADDR_RLOCK();
416 vrf = sctp_find_vrf(vrf_id);
417 if (vrf == NULL) {
418 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_PCB4, "Can't find vrf_id 0x%x\n", vrf_id);
419 goto out;
420 }
421 sctp_ifap = sctp_find_ifa_by_addr(addr, vrf->vrf_id, SCTP_ADDR_LOCKED);
422 if (sctp_ifap == NULL) {
423 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_PCB4, "Can't find sctp_ifap for address\n");
424 goto out;
425 }
426 if (sctp_ifap->ifn_p == NULL) {
427 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_PCB4, "IFA has no IFN - can't mark unusable\n");
428 goto out;
429 }
430 if (if_name) {
431 if (strncmp(if_name, sctp_ifap->ifn_p->ifn_name, SCTP_IFNAMSIZ) != 0) {
432 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_PCB4, "IFN %s of IFA not the same as %s\n",
433 sctp_ifap->ifn_p->ifn_name, if_name);
434 goto out;
435 }
436 } else {
437 if (sctp_ifap->ifn_p->ifn_index != ifn_index) {
438 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_PCB4, "IFA owned by ifn_index:%d down command for ifn_index:%d - ignored\n",
439 sctp_ifap->ifn_p->ifn_index, ifn_index);
440 goto out;
441 }
442 }
443
444 sctp_ifap->localifa_flags &= (~SCTP_ADDR_IFA_UNUSEABLE);
445 sctp_ifap->localifa_flags |= SCTP_ADDR_VALID;
446 out:
447 SCTP_IPI_ADDR_RUNLOCK();
448}
449
450/*-
451 * Add an ifa to an ifn.
452 * Register the interface as necessary.
453 * NOTE: ADDR write lock MUST be held.
454 */
455static void
456sctp_add_ifa_to_ifn(struct sctp_ifn *sctp_ifnp, struct sctp_ifa *sctp_ifap)
457{
458 int ifa_af;
459
460 LIST_INSERT_HEAD(&sctp_ifnp->ifalist, sctp_ifap, next_ifa);
461 sctp_ifap->ifn_p = sctp_ifnp;
462 atomic_add_int(&sctp_ifap->ifn_p->refcount, 1);
463 /* update address counts */
464 sctp_ifnp->ifa_count++;
465 ifa_af = sctp_ifap->address.sa.sa_family;
466 switch (ifa_af) {
467#ifdef INET
468 case AF_INET:
469 sctp_ifnp->num_v4++;
470 break;
471#endif
472#ifdef INET6
473 case AF_INET6:
474 sctp_ifnp->num_v6++;
475 break;
476#endif
477 default:
478 break;
479 }
480 if (sctp_ifnp->ifa_count == 1) {
481 /* register the new interface */
482 sctp_ifnp->registered_af = ifa_af;
483 }
484}
485
486/*-
487 * Remove an ifa from its ifn.
488 * If no more addresses exist, remove the ifn too. Otherwise, re-register
489 * the interface based on the remaining address families left.
490 * NOTE: ADDR write lock MUST be held.
491 */
492static void
493sctp_remove_ifa_from_ifn(struct sctp_ifa *sctp_ifap)
494{
495 LIST_REMOVE(sctp_ifap, next_ifa);
496 if (sctp_ifap->ifn_p) {
497 /* update address counts */
498 sctp_ifap->ifn_p->ifa_count--;
499 switch (sctp_ifap->address.sa.sa_family) {
500#ifdef INET
501 case AF_INET:
502 sctp_ifap->ifn_p->num_v4--;
503 break;
504#endif
505#ifdef INET6
506 case AF_INET6:
507 sctp_ifap->ifn_p->num_v6--;
508 break;
509#endif
510 default:
511 break;
512 }
513
514 if (LIST_EMPTY(&sctp_ifap->ifn_p->ifalist)) {
515 /* remove the ifn, possibly freeing it */
516 sctp_delete_ifn(sctp_ifap->ifn_p, SCTP_ADDR_LOCKED);
517 } else {
518 /* re-register address family type, if needed */
519 if ((sctp_ifap->ifn_p->num_v6 == 0) &&
520 (sctp_ifap->ifn_p->registered_af == AF_INET6)) {
521 sctp_ifap->ifn_p->registered_af = AF_INET;
522 } else if ((sctp_ifap->ifn_p->num_v4 == 0) &&
523 (sctp_ifap->ifn_p->registered_af == AF_INET)) {
524 sctp_ifap->ifn_p->registered_af = AF_INET6;
525 }
526 /* free the ifn refcount */
527 sctp_free_ifn(sctp_ifap->ifn_p);
528 }
529 sctp_ifap->ifn_p = NULL;
530 }
531}
532
533struct sctp_ifa *
534sctp_add_addr_to_vrf(uint32_t vrf_id, void *ifn, uint32_t ifn_index,
535 uint32_t ifn_type, const char *if_name, void *ifa,
536 struct sockaddr *addr, uint32_t ifa_flags,
537 int dynamic_add)
538{
539 struct sctp_vrf *vrf;
540 struct sctp_ifn *sctp_ifnp, *new_sctp_ifnp;
541 struct sctp_ifa *sctp_ifap, *new_sctp_ifap;
542 struct sctp_ifalist *hash_addr_head;
543 struct sctp_ifnlist *hash_ifn_head;
544 uint32_t hash_of_addr;
545 int new_ifn_af = 0;
546
547#ifdef SCTP_DEBUG
548 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_PCB4, "vrf_id 0x%x: adding address: ", vrf_id);
549 SCTPDBG_ADDR(SCTP_DEBUG_PCB4, addr);
550#endif
551 SCTP_MALLOC(new_sctp_ifnp, struct sctp_ifn *,
552 sizeof(struct sctp_ifn), SCTP_M_IFN);
553 if (new_sctp_ifnp == NULL) {
554#ifdef INVARIANTS
555 panic("No memory for IFN");
556#endif
557 return (NULL);
558 }
559 SCTP_MALLOC(new_sctp_ifap, struct sctp_ifa *, sizeof(struct sctp_ifa), SCTP_M_IFA);
560 if (new_sctp_ifap == NULL) {
561#ifdef INVARIANTS
562 panic("No memory for IFA");
563#endif
564 SCTP_FREE(new_sctp_ifnp, SCTP_M_IFN);
565 return (NULL);
566 }
567
568 SCTP_IPI_ADDR_WLOCK();
569 sctp_ifnp = sctp_find_ifn(ifn, ifn_index);
570 if (sctp_ifnp) {
571 vrf = sctp_ifnp->vrf;
572 } else {
573 vrf = sctp_find_vrf(vrf_id);
574 if (vrf == NULL) {
575 vrf = sctp_allocate_vrf(vrf_id);
576 if (vrf == NULL) {
577 SCTP_IPI_ADDR_WUNLOCK();
578 SCTP_FREE(new_sctp_ifnp, SCTP_M_IFN);
579 SCTP_FREE(new_sctp_ifap, SCTP_M_IFA);
580 return (NULL);
581 }
582 }
583 }
584 if (sctp_ifnp == NULL) {
585 /* build one and add it, can't hold lock
586 * until after malloc done though.
587 */
588 sctp_ifnp = new_sctp_ifnp;
589 new_sctp_ifnp = NULL;
590 memset(sctp_ifnp, 0, sizeof(struct sctp_ifn));
591 sctp_ifnp->ifn_index = ifn_index;
592 sctp_ifnp->ifn_p = ifn;
593 sctp_ifnp->ifn_type = ifn_type;
594 sctp_ifnp->refcount = 0;
595 sctp_ifnp->vrf = vrf;
596 atomic_add_int(&vrf->refcount, 1);
597 sctp_ifnp->ifn_mtu = SCTP_GATHER_MTU_FROM_IFN_INFO(ifn, ifn_index, addr->sa_family);
598 if (if_name != NULL) {
599 SCTP_SNPRINTF(sctp_ifnp->ifn_name, SCTP_IFNAMSIZ, "%s", if_name);
600 } else {
601 SCTP_SNPRINTF(sctp_ifnp->ifn_name, SCTP_IFNAMSIZ, "%s", "unknown");
602 }
603 hash_ifn_head = &SCTP_BASE_INFO(vrf_ifn_hash)[(ifn_index & SCTP_BASE_INFO(vrf_ifn_hashmark))];
604 LIST_INIT(&sctp_ifnp->ifalist);
605 LIST_INSERT_HEAD(hash_ifn_head, sctp_ifnp, next_bucket);
606 LIST_INSERT_HEAD(&vrf->ifnlist, sctp_ifnp, next_ifn);
607 atomic_add_int(&SCTP_BASE_INFO(ipi_count_ifns), 1);
608 new_ifn_af = 1;
609 }
610 sctp_ifap = sctp_find_ifa_by_addr(addr, vrf->vrf_id, SCTP_ADDR_LOCKED);
611 if (sctp_ifap) {
612 /* Hmm, it already exists? */
613 if ((sctp_ifap->ifn_p) &&
614 (sctp_ifap->ifn_p->ifn_index == ifn_index)) {
615 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_PCB4, "Using existing ifn %s (0x%x) for ifa %p\n",
616 sctp_ifap->ifn_p->ifn_name, ifn_index,
617 (void *)sctp_ifap);
618 if (new_ifn_af) {
619 /* Remove the created one that we don't want */
620 sctp_delete_ifn(sctp_ifnp, SCTP_ADDR_LOCKED);
621 }
622 if (sctp_ifap->localifa_flags & SCTP_BEING_DELETED) {
623 /* easy to solve, just switch back to active */
624 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_PCB4, "Clearing deleted ifa flag\n");
625 sctp_ifap->localifa_flags = SCTP_ADDR_VALID;
626 sctp_ifap->ifn_p = sctp_ifnp;
627 atomic_add_int(&sctp_ifap->ifn_p->refcount, 1);
628 }
629 exit_stage_left:
630 SCTP_IPI_ADDR_WUNLOCK();
631 if (new_sctp_ifnp != NULL) {
632 SCTP_FREE(new_sctp_ifnp, SCTP_M_IFN);
633 }
634 SCTP_FREE(new_sctp_ifap, SCTP_M_IFA);
635 return (sctp_ifap);
636 } else {
637 if (sctp_ifap->ifn_p) {
638 /*
639 * The last IFN gets the address, remove the
640 * old one
641 */
642 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_PCB4, "Moving ifa %p from %s (0x%x) to %s (0x%x)\n",
643 (void *)sctp_ifap, sctp_ifap->ifn_p->ifn_name,
644 sctp_ifap->ifn_p->ifn_index, if_name,
645 ifn_index);
646 /* remove the address from the old ifn */
647 sctp_remove_ifa_from_ifn(sctp_ifap);
648 /* move the address over to the new ifn */
649 sctp_add_ifa_to_ifn(sctp_ifnp, sctp_ifap);
650 goto exit_stage_left;
651 } else {
652 /* repair ifnp which was NULL ? */
653 sctp_ifap->localifa_flags = SCTP_ADDR_VALID;
654 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_PCB4, "Repairing ifn %p for ifa %p\n",
655 (void *)sctp_ifnp, (void *)sctp_ifap);
656 sctp_add_ifa_to_ifn(sctp_ifnp, sctp_ifap);
657 }
658 goto exit_stage_left;
659 }
660 }
661 sctp_ifap = new_sctp_ifap;
662 memset(sctp_ifap, 0, sizeof(struct sctp_ifa));
663 sctp_ifap->ifn_p = sctp_ifnp;
664 atomic_add_int(&sctp_ifnp->refcount, 1);
665 sctp_ifap->vrf_id = vrf_id;
666 sctp_ifap->ifa = ifa;
667#ifdef HAVE_SA_LEN
668 memcpy(&sctp_ifap->address, addr, addr->sa_len);
669#else
670 switch (addr->sa_family) {
671#ifdef INET
672 case AF_INET:
673 memcpy(&sctp_ifap->address, addr, sizeof(struct sockaddr_in));
674 break;
675#endif
676#ifdef INET6
677 case AF_INET6:
678 memcpy(&sctp_ifap->address, addr, sizeof(struct sockaddr_in6));
679 break;
680#endif
681#if defined(__Userspace__)
682 case AF_CONN:
683 memcpy(&sctp_ifap->address, addr, sizeof(struct sockaddr_conn));
684 break;
685#endif
686 default:
687 /* TSNH */
688 break;
689 }
690#endif
691 sctp_ifap->localifa_flags = SCTP_ADDR_VALID | SCTP_ADDR_DEFER_USE;
692 sctp_ifap->flags = ifa_flags;
693 /* Set scope */
694 switch (sctp_ifap->address.sa.sa_family) {
695#ifdef INET
696 case AF_INET:
697 {
698 struct sockaddr_in *sin;
699
700 sin = &sctp_ifap->address.sin;
701 if (SCTP_IFN_IS_IFT_LOOP(sctp_ifap->ifn_p) ||
702 (IN4_ISLOOPBACK_ADDRESS(&sin->sin_addr))) {
703 sctp_ifap->src_is_loop = 1;
704 }
705 if ((IN4_ISPRIVATE_ADDRESS(&sin->sin_addr))) {
706 sctp_ifap->src_is_priv = 1;
707 }
708 sctp_ifnp->num_v4++;
709 if (new_ifn_af)
710 new_ifn_af = AF_INET;
711 break;
712 }
713#endif
714#ifdef INET6
715 case AF_INET6:
716 {
717 /* ok to use deprecated addresses? */
718 struct sockaddr_in6 *sin6;
719
720 sin6 = &sctp_ifap->address.sin6;
721 if (SCTP_IFN_IS_IFT_LOOP(sctp_ifap->ifn_p) ||
722 (IN6_IS_ADDR_LOOPBACK(&sin6->sin6_addr))) {
723 sctp_ifap->src_is_loop = 1;
724 }
725 if (IN6_IS_ADDR_LINKLOCAL(&sin6->sin6_addr)) {
726 sctp_ifap->src_is_priv = 1;
727 }
728 sctp_ifnp->num_v6++;
729 if (new_ifn_af)
730 new_ifn_af = AF_INET6;
731 break;
732 }
733#endif
734#if defined(__Userspace__)
735 case AF_CONN:
736 if (new_ifn_af)
737 new_ifn_af = AF_CONN;
738 break;
739#endif
740 default:
741 new_ifn_af = 0;
742 break;
743 }
744 hash_of_addr = sctp_get_ifa_hash_val(&sctp_ifap->address.sa);
745
746 if ((sctp_ifap->src_is_priv == 0) &&
747 (sctp_ifap->src_is_loop == 0)) {
748 sctp_ifap->src_is_glob = 1;
749 }
750 hash_addr_head = &vrf->vrf_addr_hash[(hash_of_addr & vrf->vrf_addr_hashmark)];
751 LIST_INSERT_HEAD(hash_addr_head, sctp_ifap, next_bucket);
752 sctp_ifap->refcount = 1;
753 LIST_INSERT_HEAD(&sctp_ifnp->ifalist, sctp_ifap, next_ifa);
754 sctp_ifnp->ifa_count++;
755 vrf->total_ifa_count++;
756 atomic_add_int(&SCTP_BASE_INFO(ipi_count_ifas), 1);
757 if (new_ifn_af) {
758 sctp_ifnp->registered_af = new_ifn_af;
759 }
760 SCTP_IPI_ADDR_WUNLOCK();
761 if (new_sctp_ifnp != NULL) {
762 SCTP_FREE(new_sctp_ifnp, SCTP_M_IFN);
763 }
764
765 if (dynamic_add) {
766 /* Bump up the refcount so that when the timer
767 * completes it will drop back down.
768 */
769 struct sctp_laddr *wi;
770
771 atomic_add_int(&sctp_ifap->refcount, 1);
772 wi = SCTP_ZONE_GET(SCTP_BASE_INFO(ipi_zone_laddr), struct sctp_laddr);
773 if (wi == NULL) {
774 /*
775 * Gak, what can we do? We have lost an address
776 * change can you say HOSED?
777 */
778 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_PCB4, "Lost an address change?\n");
779 /* Opps, must decrement the count */
780 sctp_del_addr_from_vrf(vrf_id, addr, ifn_index,
781 if_name);
782 return (NULL);
783 }
784 SCTP_INCR_LADDR_COUNT();
785 memset(wi, 0, sizeof(*wi));
786 (void)SCTP_GETTIME_TIMEVAL(&wi->start_time);
787 wi->ifa = sctp_ifap;
788 wi->action = SCTP_ADD_IP_ADDRESS;
789
790 SCTP_WQ_ADDR_LOCK();
791 LIST_INSERT_HEAD(&SCTP_BASE_INFO(addr_wq), wi, sctp_nxt_addr);
792 sctp_timer_start(SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_ADDR_WQ,
793 (struct sctp_inpcb *)NULL,
794 (struct sctp_tcb *)NULL,
795 (struct sctp_nets *)NULL);
796 SCTP_WQ_ADDR_UNLOCK();
797 } else {
798 /* it's ready for use */
799 sctp_ifap->localifa_flags &= ~SCTP_ADDR_DEFER_USE;
800 }
801 return (sctp_ifap);
802}
803
804void
805sctp_del_addr_from_vrf(uint32_t vrf_id, struct sockaddr *addr,
806 uint32_t ifn_index, const char *if_name)
807{
808 struct sctp_vrf *vrf;
809 struct sctp_ifa *sctp_ifap = NULL;
810
811 SCTP_IPI_ADDR_WLOCK();
812 vrf = sctp_find_vrf(vrf_id);
813 if (vrf == NULL) {
814 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_PCB4, "Can't find vrf_id 0x%x\n", vrf_id);
815 goto out_now;
816 }
817
818#ifdef SCTP_DEBUG
819 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_PCB4, "vrf_id 0x%x: deleting address:", vrf_id);
820 SCTPDBG_ADDR(SCTP_DEBUG_PCB4, addr);
821#endif
822 sctp_ifap = sctp_find_ifa_by_addr(addr, vrf->vrf_id, SCTP_ADDR_LOCKED);
823 if (sctp_ifap) {
824 /* Validate the delete */
825 if (sctp_ifap->ifn_p) {
826 int valid = 0;
827 /*-
828 * The name has priority over the ifn_index
829 * if its given.
830 */
831 if (if_name) {
832 if (strncmp(if_name, sctp_ifap->ifn_p->ifn_name, SCTP_IFNAMSIZ) == 0) {
833 /* They match its a correct delete */
834 valid = 1;
835 }
836 }
837 if (!valid) {
838 /* last ditch check ifn_index */
839 if (ifn_index == sctp_ifap->ifn_p->ifn_index) {
840 valid = 1;
841 }
842 }
843 if (!valid) {
844 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_PCB4, "ifn:%d ifname:%s does not match addresses\n",
845 ifn_index, ((if_name == NULL) ? "NULL" : if_name));
846 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_PCB4, "ifn:%d ifname:%s - ignoring delete\n",
847 sctp_ifap->ifn_p->ifn_index, sctp_ifap->ifn_p->ifn_name);
848 SCTP_IPI_ADDR_WUNLOCK();
849 return;
850 }
851 }
852 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_PCB4, "Deleting ifa %p\n", (void *)sctp_ifap);
853 sctp_ifap->localifa_flags &= SCTP_ADDR_VALID;
854 /*
855 * We don't set the flag. This means that the structure will
856 * hang around in EP's that have bound specific to it until
857 * they close. This gives us TCP like behavior if someone
858 * removes an address (or for that matter adds it right back).
859 */
860 /* sctp_ifap->localifa_flags |= SCTP_BEING_DELETED; */
861 vrf->total_ifa_count--;
862 LIST_REMOVE(sctp_ifap, next_bucket);
863 sctp_remove_ifa_from_ifn(sctp_ifap);
864 }
865#ifdef SCTP_DEBUG
866 else {
867 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_PCB4, "Del Addr-ifn:%d Could not find address:",
868 ifn_index);
869 SCTPDBG_ADDR(SCTP_DEBUG_PCB1, addr);
870 }
871#endif
872
873 out_now:
874 SCTP_IPI_ADDR_WUNLOCK();
875 if (sctp_ifap) {
876 struct sctp_laddr *wi;
877
878 wi = SCTP_ZONE_GET(SCTP_BASE_INFO(ipi_zone_laddr), struct sctp_laddr);
879 if (wi == NULL) {
880 /*
881 * Gak, what can we do? We have lost an address
882 * change can you say HOSED?
883 */
884 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_PCB4, "Lost an address change?\n");
885
886 /* Oops, must decrement the count */
887 sctp_free_ifa(sctp_ifap);
888 return;
889 }
890 SCTP_INCR_LADDR_COUNT();
891 memset(wi, 0, sizeof(*wi));
892 (void)SCTP_GETTIME_TIMEVAL(&wi->start_time);
893 wi->ifa = sctp_ifap;
894 wi->action = SCTP_DEL_IP_ADDRESS;
895 SCTP_WQ_ADDR_LOCK();
896 /*
897 * Should this really be a tailq? As it is we will process the
898 * newest first :-0
899 */
900 LIST_INSERT_HEAD(&SCTP_BASE_INFO(addr_wq), wi, sctp_nxt_addr);
901 sctp_timer_start(SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_ADDR_WQ,
902 (struct sctp_inpcb *)NULL,
903 (struct sctp_tcb *)NULL,
904 (struct sctp_nets *)NULL);
905 SCTP_WQ_ADDR_UNLOCK();
906 }
907 return;
908}
909
910static int
911sctp_does_stcb_own_this_addr(struct sctp_tcb *stcb, struct sockaddr *to)
912{
913 int loopback_scope;
914#if defined(INET)
915 int ipv4_local_scope, ipv4_addr_legal;
916#endif
917#if defined(INET6)
918 int local_scope, site_scope, ipv6_addr_legal;
919#endif
920#if defined(__Userspace__)
921 int conn_addr_legal;
922#endif
923 struct sctp_vrf *vrf;
924 struct sctp_ifn *sctp_ifn;
925 struct sctp_ifa *sctp_ifa;
926
927 loopback_scope = stcb->asoc.scope.loopback_scope;
928#if defined(INET)
929 ipv4_local_scope = stcb->asoc.scope.ipv4_local_scope;
930 ipv4_addr_legal = stcb->asoc.scope.ipv4_addr_legal;
931#endif
932#if defined(INET6)
933 local_scope = stcb->asoc.scope.local_scope;
934 site_scope = stcb->asoc.scope.site_scope;
935 ipv6_addr_legal = stcb->asoc.scope.ipv6_addr_legal;
936#endif
937#if defined(__Userspace__)
938 conn_addr_legal = stcb->asoc.scope.conn_addr_legal;
939#endif
940
941 SCTP_IPI_ADDR_RLOCK();
942 vrf = sctp_find_vrf(stcb->asoc.vrf_id);
943 if (vrf == NULL) {
944 /* no vrf, no addresses */
945 SCTP_IPI_ADDR_RUNLOCK();
946 return (0);
947 }
948
949 if (stcb->sctp_ep->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_BOUNDALL) {
950 LIST_FOREACH(sctp_ifn, &vrf->ifnlist, next_ifn) {
951 if ((loopback_scope == 0) &&
952 SCTP_IFN_IS_IFT_LOOP(sctp_ifn)) {
953 continue;
954 }
955 LIST_FOREACH(sctp_ifa, &sctp_ifn->ifalist, next_ifa) {
956 if (sctp_is_addr_restricted(stcb, sctp_ifa) &&
957 (!sctp_is_addr_pending(stcb, sctp_ifa))) {
958 /* We allow pending addresses, where we
959 * have sent an asconf-add to be considered
960 * valid.
961 */
962 continue;
963 }
964 if (sctp_ifa->address.sa.sa_family != to->sa_family) {
965 continue;
966 }
967 switch (sctp_ifa->address.sa.sa_family) {
968#ifdef INET
969 case AF_INET:
970 if (ipv4_addr_legal) {
971 struct sockaddr_in *sin, *rsin;
972
973 sin = &sctp_ifa->address.sin;
974 rsin = (struct sockaddr_in *)to;
975 if ((ipv4_local_scope == 0) &&
976 IN4_ISPRIVATE_ADDRESS(&sin->sin_addr)) {
977 continue;
978 }
979#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
980 if (prison_check_ip4(stcb->sctp_ep->ip_inp.inp.inp_cred,
981 &sin->sin_addr) != 0) {
982 continue;
983 }
984#endif
985 if (sin->sin_addr.s_addr == rsin->sin_addr.s_addr) {
986 SCTP_IPI_ADDR_RUNLOCK();
987 return (1);
988 }
989 }
990 break;
991#endif
992#ifdef INET6
993 case AF_INET6:
994 if (ipv6_addr_legal) {
995 struct sockaddr_in6 *sin6, *rsin6;
996#if defined(SCTP_EMBEDDED_V6_SCOPE) && !defined(SCTP_KAME)
997 struct sockaddr_in6 lsa6;
998#endif
999 sin6 = &sctp_ifa->address.sin6;
1000 rsin6 = (struct sockaddr_in6 *)to;
1001#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
1002 if (prison_check_ip6(stcb->sctp_ep->ip_inp.inp.inp_cred,
1003 &sin6->sin6_addr) != 0) {
1004 continue;
1005 }
1006#endif
1007 if (IN6_IS_ADDR_LINKLOCAL(&sin6->sin6_addr)) {
1008 if (local_scope == 0)
1009 continue;
1010#if defined(SCTP_EMBEDDED_V6_SCOPE)
1011 if (sin6->sin6_scope_id == 0) {
1012#ifdef SCTP_KAME
1013 if (sa6_recoverscope(sin6) != 0)
1014 continue;
1015#else
1016 lsa6 = *sin6;
1017 if (in6_recoverscope(&lsa6,
1018 &lsa6.sin6_addr,
1019 NULL))
1020 continue;
1021 sin6 = &lsa6;
1022#endif /* SCTP_KAME */
1023 }
1024#endif /* SCTP_EMBEDDED_V6_SCOPE */
1025 }
1026 if ((site_scope == 0) &&
1027 (IN6_IS_ADDR_SITELOCAL(&sin6->sin6_addr))) {
1028 continue;
1029 }
1030 if (SCTP6_ARE_ADDR_EQUAL(sin6, rsin6)) {
1031 SCTP_IPI_ADDR_RUNLOCK();
1032 return (1);
1033 }
1034 }
1035 break;
1036#endif
1037#if defined(__Userspace__)
1038 case AF_CONN:
1039 if (conn_addr_legal) {
1040 struct sockaddr_conn *sconn, *rsconn;
1041
1042 sconn = &sctp_ifa->address.sconn;
1043 rsconn = (struct sockaddr_conn *)to;
1044 if (sconn->sconn_addr == rsconn->sconn_addr) {
1045 SCTP_IPI_ADDR_RUNLOCK();
1046 return (1);
1047 }
1048 }
1049 break;
1050#endif
1051 default:
1052 /* TSNH */
1053 break;
1054 }
1055 }
1056 }
1057 } else {
1058 struct sctp_laddr *laddr;
1059
1060 LIST_FOREACH(laddr, &stcb->sctp_ep->sctp_addr_list, sctp_nxt_addr) {
1061 if (laddr->ifa->localifa_flags & SCTP_BEING_DELETED) {
1062 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_PCB1, "ifa being deleted\n");
1063 continue;
1064 }
1065 if (sctp_is_addr_restricted(stcb, laddr->ifa) &&
1066 (!sctp_is_addr_pending(stcb, laddr->ifa))) {
1067 /* We allow pending addresses, where we
1068 * have sent an asconf-add to be considered
1069 * valid.
1070 */
1071 continue;
1072 }
1073 if (laddr->ifa->address.sa.sa_family != to->sa_family) {
1074 continue;
1075 }
1076 switch (to->sa_family) {
1077#ifdef INET
1078 case AF_INET:
1079 {
1080 struct sockaddr_in *sin, *rsin;
1081
1082 sin = &laddr->ifa->address.sin;
1083 rsin = (struct sockaddr_in *)to;
1084 if (sin->sin_addr.s_addr == rsin->sin_addr.s_addr) {
1085 SCTP_IPI_ADDR_RUNLOCK();
1086 return (1);
1087 }
1088 break;
1089 }
1090#endif
1091#ifdef INET6
1092 case AF_INET6:
1093 {
1094 struct sockaddr_in6 *sin6, *rsin6;
1095
1096 sin6 = &laddr->ifa->address.sin6;
1097 rsin6 = (struct sockaddr_in6 *)to;
1098 if (SCTP6_ARE_ADDR_EQUAL(sin6, rsin6)) {
1099 SCTP_IPI_ADDR_RUNLOCK();
1100 return (1);
1101 }
1102 break;
1103 }
1104
1105#endif
1106#if defined(__Userspace__)
1107 case AF_CONN:
1108 {
1109 struct sockaddr_conn *sconn, *rsconn;
1110
1111 sconn = &laddr->ifa->address.sconn;
1112 rsconn = (struct sockaddr_conn *)to;
1113 if (sconn->sconn_addr == rsconn->sconn_addr) {
1114 SCTP_IPI_ADDR_RUNLOCK();
1115 return (1);
1116 }
1117 break;
1118 }
1119#endif
1120 default:
1121 /* TSNH */
1122 break;
1123 }
1124 }
1125 }
1126 SCTP_IPI_ADDR_RUNLOCK();
1127 return (0);
1128}
1129
1130static struct sctp_tcb *
1131sctp_tcb_special_locate(struct sctp_inpcb **inp_p, struct sockaddr *from,
1132 struct sockaddr *to, struct sctp_nets **netp, uint32_t vrf_id)
1133{
1134 /**** ASSUMES THE CALLER holds the INP_INFO_RLOCK */
1135 /*
1136 * If we support the TCP model, then we must now dig through to see
1137 * if we can find our endpoint in the list of tcp ep's.
1138 */
1139 uint16_t lport, rport;
1140 struct sctppcbhead *ephead;
1141 struct sctp_inpcb *inp;
1142 struct sctp_laddr *laddr;
1143 struct sctp_tcb *stcb;
1144 struct sctp_nets *net;
1145#ifdef SCTP_MVRF
1146 int fnd, i;
1147#endif
1148
1149 if ((to == NULL) || (from == NULL)) {
1150 return (NULL);
1151 }
1152
1153 switch (to->sa_family) {
1154#ifdef INET
1155 case AF_INET:
1156 if (from->sa_family == AF_INET) {
1157 lport = ((struct sockaddr_in *)to)->sin_port;
1158 rport = ((struct sockaddr_in *)from)->sin_port;
1159 } else {
1160 return (NULL);
1161 }
1162 break;
1163#endif
1164#ifdef INET6
1165 case AF_INET6:
1166 if (from->sa_family == AF_INET6) {
1167 lport = ((struct sockaddr_in6 *)to)->sin6_port;
1168 rport = ((struct sockaddr_in6 *)from)->sin6_port;
1169 } else {
1170 return (NULL);
1171 }
1172 break;
1173#endif
1174#if defined(__Userspace__)
1175 case AF_CONN:
1176 if (from->sa_family == AF_CONN) {
1177 lport = ((struct sockaddr_conn *)to)->sconn_port;
1178 rport = ((struct sockaddr_conn *)from)->sconn_port;
1179 } else {
1180 return (NULL);
1181 }
1182 break;
1183#endif
1184 default:
1185 return (NULL);
1186 }
1187 ephead = &SCTP_BASE_INFO(sctp_tcpephash)[SCTP_PCBHASH_ALLADDR((lport | rport), SCTP_BASE_INFO(hashtcpmark))];
1188 /*
1189 * Ok now for each of the guys in this bucket we must look and see:
1190 * - Does the remote port match. - Does there single association's
1191 * addresses match this address (to). If so we update p_ep to point
1192 * to this ep and return the tcb from it.
1193 */
1194 LIST_FOREACH(inp, ephead, sctp_hash) {
1195 SCTP_INP_RLOCK(inp);
1196 if (inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_SOCKET_ALLGONE) {
1197 SCTP_INP_RUNLOCK(inp);
1198 continue;
1199 }
1200 if (lport != inp->sctp_lport) {
1201 SCTP_INP_RUNLOCK(inp);
1202 continue;
1203 }
1204#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
1205 switch (to->sa_family) {
1206#ifdef INET
1207 case AF_INET:
1208 {
1209 struct sockaddr_in *sin;
1210
1211 sin = (struct sockaddr_in *)to;
1212 if (prison_check_ip4(inp->ip_inp.inp.inp_cred,
1213 &sin->sin_addr) != 0) {
1214 SCTP_INP_RUNLOCK(inp);
1215 continue;
1216 }
1217 break;
1218 }
1219#endif
1220#ifdef INET6
1221 case AF_INET6:
1222 {
1223 struct sockaddr_in6 *sin6;
1224
1225 sin6 = (struct sockaddr_in6 *)to;
1226 if (prison_check_ip6(inp->ip_inp.inp.inp_cred,
1227 &sin6->sin6_addr) != 0) {
1228 SCTP_INP_RUNLOCK(inp);
1229 continue;
1230 }
1231 break;
1232 }
1233#endif
1234 default:
1235 SCTP_INP_RUNLOCK(inp);
1236 continue;
1237 }
1238#endif
1239#ifdef SCTP_MVRF
1240 fnd = 0;
1241 for (i = 0; i < inp->num_vrfs; i++) {
1242 if (inp->m_vrf_ids[i] == vrf_id) {
1243 fnd = 1;
1244 break;
1245 }
1246 }
1247 if (fnd == 0) {
1248 SCTP_INP_RUNLOCK(inp);
1249 continue;
1250 }
1251#else
1252 if (inp->def_vrf_id != vrf_id) {
1253 SCTP_INP_RUNLOCK(inp);
1254 continue;
1255 }
1256#endif
1257 /* check to see if the ep has one of the addresses */
1258 if ((inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_BOUNDALL) == 0) {
1259 /* We are NOT bound all, so look further */
1260 int match = 0;
1261
1262 LIST_FOREACH(laddr, &inp->sctp_addr_list, sctp_nxt_addr) {
1263 if (laddr->ifa == NULL) {
1264 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_PCB1, "%s: NULL ifa\n", __func__);
1265 continue;
1266 }
1267 if (laddr->ifa->localifa_flags & SCTP_BEING_DELETED) {
1268 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_PCB1, "ifa being deleted\n");
1269 continue;
1270 }
1271 if (laddr->ifa->address.sa.sa_family ==
1272 to->sa_family) {
1273 /* see if it matches */
1274#ifdef INET
1275 if (from->sa_family == AF_INET) {
1276 struct sockaddr_in *intf_addr, *sin;
1277
1278 intf_addr = &laddr->ifa->address.sin;
1279 sin = (struct sockaddr_in *)to;
1280 if (sin->sin_addr.s_addr ==
1281 intf_addr->sin_addr.s_addr) {
1282 match = 1;
1283 break;
1284 }
1285 }
1286#endif
1287#ifdef INET6
1288 if (from->sa_family == AF_INET6) {
1289 struct sockaddr_in6 *intf_addr6;
1290 struct sockaddr_in6 *sin6;
1291
1292 sin6 = (struct sockaddr_in6 *)
1293 to;
1294 intf_addr6 = &laddr->ifa->address.sin6;
1295
1296 if (SCTP6_ARE_ADDR_EQUAL(sin6,
1297 intf_addr6)) {
1298 match = 1;
1299 break;
1300 }
1301 }
1302#endif
1303#if defined(__Userspace__)
1304 if (from->sa_family == AF_CONN) {
1305 struct sockaddr_conn *intf_addr, *sconn;
1306
1307 intf_addr = &laddr->ifa->address.sconn;
1308 sconn = (struct sockaddr_conn *)to;
1309 if (sconn->sconn_addr ==
1310 intf_addr->sconn_addr) {
1311 match = 1;
1312 break;
1313 }
1314 }
1315#endif
1316 }
1317 }
1318 if (match == 0) {
1319 /* This endpoint does not have this address */
1320 SCTP_INP_RUNLOCK(inp);
1321 continue;
1322 }
1323 }
1324 /*
1325 * Ok if we hit here the ep has the address, does it hold
1326 * the tcb?
1327 */
1328 /* XXX: Why don't we TAILQ_FOREACH through sctp_asoc_list? */
1329 stcb = LIST_FIRST(&inp->sctp_asoc_list);
1330 if (stcb == NULL) {
1331 SCTP_INP_RUNLOCK(inp);
1332 continue;
1333 }
1334 SCTP_TCB_LOCK(stcb);
1335 if (!sctp_does_stcb_own_this_addr(stcb, to)) {
1336 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
1337 SCTP_INP_RUNLOCK(inp);
1338 continue;
1339 }
1340 if (stcb->rport != rport) {
1341 /* remote port does not match. */
1342 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
1343 SCTP_INP_RUNLOCK(inp);
1344 continue;
1345 }
1346 if (stcb->asoc.state & SCTP_STATE_ABOUT_TO_BE_FREED) {
1347 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
1348 SCTP_INP_RUNLOCK(inp);
1349 continue;
1350 }
1351 if (!sctp_does_stcb_own_this_addr(stcb, to)) {
1352 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
1353 SCTP_INP_RUNLOCK(inp);
1354 continue;
1355 }
1356 /* Does this TCB have a matching address? */
1357 TAILQ_FOREACH(net, &stcb->asoc.nets, sctp_next) {
1358 if (net->ro._l_addr.sa.sa_family != from->sa_family) {
1359 /* not the same family, can't be a match */
1360 continue;
1361 }
1362 switch (from->sa_family) {
1363#ifdef INET
1364 case AF_INET:
1365 {
1366 struct sockaddr_in *sin, *rsin;
1367
1368 sin = (struct sockaddr_in *)&net->ro._l_addr;
1369 rsin = (struct sockaddr_in *)from;
1370 if (sin->sin_addr.s_addr ==
1371 rsin->sin_addr.s_addr) {
1372 /* found it */
1373 if (netp != NULL) {
1374 *netp = net;
1375 }
1376 /* Update the endpoint pointer */
1377 *inp_p = inp;
1378 SCTP_INP_RUNLOCK(inp);
1379 return (stcb);
1380 }
1381 break;
1382 }
1383#endif
1384#ifdef INET6
1385 case AF_INET6:
1386 {
1387 struct sockaddr_in6 *sin6, *rsin6;
1388
1389 sin6 = (struct sockaddr_in6 *)&net->ro._l_addr;
1390 rsin6 = (struct sockaddr_in6 *)from;
1391 if (SCTP6_ARE_ADDR_EQUAL(sin6,
1392 rsin6)) {
1393 /* found it */
1394 if (netp != NULL) {
1395 *netp = net;
1396 }
1397 /* Update the endpoint pointer */
1398 *inp_p = inp;
1399 SCTP_INP_RUNLOCK(inp);
1400 return (stcb);
1401 }
1402 break;
1403 }
1404#endif
1405#if defined(__Userspace__)
1406 case AF_CONN:
1407 {
1408 struct sockaddr_conn *sconn, *rsconn;
1409
1410 sconn = (struct sockaddr_conn *)&net->ro._l_addr;
1411 rsconn = (struct sockaddr_conn *)from;
1412 if (sconn->sconn_addr == rsconn->sconn_addr) {
1413 /* found it */
1414 if (netp != NULL) {
1415 *netp = net;
1416 }
1417 /* Update the endpoint pointer */
1418 *inp_p = inp;
1419 SCTP_INP_RUNLOCK(inp);
1420 return (stcb);
1421 }
1422 break;
1423 }
1424#endif
1425 default:
1426 /* TSNH */
1427 break;
1428 }
1429 }
1430 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
1431 SCTP_INP_RUNLOCK(inp);
1432 }
1433 return (NULL);
1434}
1435
1436/*
1437 * rules for use
1438 *
1439 * 1) If I return a NULL you must decrement any INP ref cnt. 2) If I find an
1440 * stcb, both will be locked (locked_tcb and stcb) but decrement will be done
1441 * (if locked == NULL). 3) Decrement happens on return ONLY if locked ==
1442 * NULL.
1443 */
1444
1445struct sctp_tcb *
1446sctp_findassociation_ep_addr(struct sctp_inpcb **inp_p, struct sockaddr *remote,
1447 struct sctp_nets **netp, struct sockaddr *local, struct sctp_tcb *locked_tcb)
1448{
1449 struct sctpasochead *head;
1450 struct sctp_inpcb *inp;
1451 struct sctp_tcb *stcb = NULL;
1452 struct sctp_nets *net;
1453 uint16_t rport;
1454
1455 inp = *inp_p;
1456 switch (remote->sa_family) {
1457#ifdef INET
1458 case AF_INET:
1459 rport = (((struct sockaddr_in *)remote)->sin_port);
1460 break;
1461#endif
1462#ifdef INET6
1463 case AF_INET6:
1464 rport = (((struct sockaddr_in6 *)remote)->sin6_port);
1465 break;
1466#endif
1467#if defined(__Userspace__)
1468 case AF_CONN:
1469 rport = (((struct sockaddr_conn *)remote)->sconn_port);
1470 break;
1471#endif
1472 default:
1473 return (NULL);
1474 }
1475 if (locked_tcb) {
1476 /*
1477 * UN-lock so we can do proper locking here this occurs when
1478 * called from load_addresses_from_init.
1479 */
1480 atomic_add_int(&locked_tcb->asoc.refcnt, 1);
1481 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(locked_tcb);
1482 }
1483 SCTP_INP_INFO_RLOCK();
1484 if ((inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_TCPTYPE) ||
1485 (inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_IN_TCPPOOL)) {
1486 /*-
1487 * Now either this guy is our listener or it's the
1488 * connector. If it is the one that issued the connect, then
1489 * it's only chance is to be the first TCB in the list. If
1490 * it is the acceptor, then do the special_lookup to hash
1491 * and find the real inp.
1492 */
1493 if ((inp->sctp_socket) && SCTP_IS_LISTENING(inp)) {
1494 /* to is peer addr, from is my addr */
1495#ifndef SCTP_MVRF
1496 stcb = sctp_tcb_special_locate(inp_p, remote, local,
1497 netp, inp->def_vrf_id);
1498 if ((stcb != NULL) && (locked_tcb == NULL)) {
1499 /* we have a locked tcb, lower refcount */
1500 SCTP_INP_DECR_REF(inp);
1501 }
1502 if ((locked_tcb != NULL) && (locked_tcb != stcb)) {
1503 SCTP_INP_RLOCK(locked_tcb->sctp_ep);
1504 SCTP_TCB_LOCK(locked_tcb);
1505 atomic_subtract_int(&locked_tcb->asoc.refcnt, 1);
1506 SCTP_INP_RUNLOCK(locked_tcb->sctp_ep);
1507 }
1508#else
1509 /*-
1510 * MVRF is tricky, we must look in every VRF
1511 * the endpoint has.
1512 */
1513 int i;
1514
1515 for (i = 0; i < inp->num_vrfs; i++) {
1516 stcb = sctp_tcb_special_locate(inp_p, remote, local,
1517 netp, inp->m_vrf_ids[i]);
1518 if ((stcb != NULL) && (locked_tcb == NULL)) {
1519 /* we have a locked tcb, lower refcount */
1520 SCTP_INP_DECR_REF(inp);
1521 break;
1522 }
1523 if ((locked_tcb != NULL) && (locked_tcb != stcb)) {
1524 SCTP_INP_RLOCK(locked_tcb->sctp_ep);
1525 SCTP_TCB_LOCK(locked_tcb);
1526 atomic_subtract_int(&locked_tcb->asoc.refcnt, 1);
1527 SCTP_INP_RUNLOCK(locked_tcb->sctp_ep);
1528 break;
1529 }
1530 }
1531#endif
1532 SCTP_INP_INFO_RUNLOCK();
1533 return (stcb);
1534 } else {
1535 SCTP_INP_WLOCK(inp);
1536 if (inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_SOCKET_ALLGONE) {
1537 goto null_return;
1538 }
1539 stcb = LIST_FIRST(&inp->sctp_asoc_list);
1540 if (stcb == NULL) {
1541 goto null_return;
1542 }
1543 SCTP_TCB_LOCK(stcb);
1544
1545 if (stcb->rport != rport) {
1546 /* remote port does not match. */
1547 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
1548 goto null_return;
1549 }
1550 if (stcb->asoc.state & SCTP_STATE_ABOUT_TO_BE_FREED) {
1551 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
1552 goto null_return;
1553 }
1554 if (local && !sctp_does_stcb_own_this_addr(stcb, local)) {
1555 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
1556 goto null_return;
1557 }
1558 /* now look at the list of remote addresses */
1559 TAILQ_FOREACH(net, &stcb->asoc.nets, sctp_next) {
1560#ifdef INVARIANTS
1561 if (net == (TAILQ_NEXT(net, sctp_next))) {
1562 panic("Corrupt net list");
1563 }
1564#endif
1565 if (net->ro._l_addr.sa.sa_family !=
1566 remote->sa_family) {
1567 /* not the same family */
1568 continue;
1569 }
1570 switch (remote->sa_family) {
1571#ifdef INET
1572 case AF_INET:
1573 {
1574 struct sockaddr_in *sin, *rsin;
1575
1576 sin = (struct sockaddr_in *)
1577 &net->ro._l_addr;
1578 rsin = (struct sockaddr_in *)remote;
1579 if (sin->sin_addr.s_addr ==
1580 rsin->sin_addr.s_addr) {
1581 /* found it */
1582 if (netp != NULL) {
1583 *netp = net;
1584 }
1585 if (locked_tcb == NULL) {
1586 SCTP_INP_DECR_REF(inp);
1587 } else if (locked_tcb != stcb) {
1588 SCTP_TCB_LOCK(locked_tcb);
1589 }
1590 if (locked_tcb) {
1591 atomic_subtract_int(&locked_tcb->asoc.refcnt, 1);
1592 }
1593
1594 SCTP_INP_WUNLOCK(inp);
1595 SCTP_INP_INFO_RUNLOCK();
1596 return (stcb);
1597 }
1598 break;
1599 }
1600#endif
1601#ifdef INET6
1602 case AF_INET6:
1603 {
1604 struct sockaddr_in6 *sin6, *rsin6;
1605
1606 sin6 = (struct sockaddr_in6 *)&net->ro._l_addr;
1607 rsin6 = (struct sockaddr_in6 *)remote;
1608 if (SCTP6_ARE_ADDR_EQUAL(sin6,
1609 rsin6)) {
1610 /* found it */
1611 if (netp != NULL) {
1612 *netp = net;
1613 }
1614 if (locked_tcb == NULL) {
1615 SCTP_INP_DECR_REF(inp);
1616 } else if (locked_tcb != stcb) {
1617 SCTP_TCB_LOCK(locked_tcb);
1618 }
1619 if (locked_tcb) {
1620 atomic_subtract_int(&locked_tcb->asoc.refcnt, 1);
1621 }
1622 SCTP_INP_WUNLOCK(inp);
1623 SCTP_INP_INFO_RUNLOCK();
1624 return (stcb);
1625 }
1626 break;
1627 }
1628#endif
1629#if defined(__Userspace__)
1630 case AF_CONN:
1631 {
1632 struct sockaddr_conn *sconn, *rsconn;
1633
1634 sconn = (struct sockaddr_conn *)&net->ro._l_addr;
1635 rsconn = (struct sockaddr_conn *)remote;
1636 if (sconn->sconn_addr == rsconn->sconn_addr) {
1637 /* found it */
1638 if (netp != NULL) {
1639 *netp = net;
1640 }
1641 if (locked_tcb == NULL) {
1642 SCTP_INP_DECR_REF(inp);
1643 } else if (locked_tcb != stcb) {
1644 SCTP_TCB_LOCK(locked_tcb);
1645 }
1646 if (locked_tcb) {
1647 atomic_subtract_int(&locked_tcb->asoc.refcnt, 1);
1648 }
1649 SCTP_INP_WUNLOCK(inp);
1650 SCTP_INP_INFO_RUNLOCK();
1651 return (stcb);
1652 }
1653 break;
1654 }
1655#endif
1656 default:
1657 /* TSNH */
1658 break;
1659 }
1660 }
1661 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
1662 }
1663 } else {
1664 SCTP_INP_WLOCK(inp);
1665 if (inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_SOCKET_ALLGONE) {
1666 goto null_return;
1667 }
1668 head = &inp->sctp_tcbhash[SCTP_PCBHASH_ALLADDR(rport,
1669 inp->sctp_hashmark)];
1670 LIST_FOREACH(stcb, head, sctp_tcbhash) {
1671 if (stcb->rport != rport) {
1672 /* remote port does not match */
1673 continue;
1674 }
1675 SCTP_TCB_LOCK(stcb);
1676 if (stcb->asoc.state & SCTP_STATE_ABOUT_TO_BE_FREED) {
1677 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
1678 continue;
1679 }
1680 if (local && !sctp_does_stcb_own_this_addr(stcb, local)) {
1681 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
1682 continue;
1683 }
1684 /* now look at the list of remote addresses */
1685 TAILQ_FOREACH(net, &stcb->asoc.nets, sctp_next) {
1686#ifdef INVARIANTS
1687 if (net == (TAILQ_NEXT(net, sctp_next))) {
1688 panic("Corrupt net list");
1689 }
1690#endif
1691 if (net->ro._l_addr.sa.sa_family !=
1692 remote->sa_family) {
1693 /* not the same family */
1694 continue;
1695 }
1696 switch (remote->sa_family) {
1697#ifdef INET
1698 case AF_INET:
1699 {
1700 struct sockaddr_in *sin, *rsin;
1701
1702 sin = (struct sockaddr_in *)
1703 &net->ro._l_addr;
1704 rsin = (struct sockaddr_in *)remote;
1705 if (sin->sin_addr.s_addr ==
1706 rsin->sin_addr.s_addr) {
1707 /* found it */
1708 if (netp != NULL) {
1709 *netp = net;
1710 }
1711 if (locked_tcb == NULL) {
1712 SCTP_INP_DECR_REF(inp);
1713 } else if (locked_tcb != stcb) {
1714 SCTP_TCB_LOCK(locked_tcb);
1715 }
1716 if (locked_tcb) {
1717 atomic_subtract_int(&locked_tcb->asoc.refcnt, 1);
1718 }
1719 SCTP_INP_WUNLOCK(inp);
1720 SCTP_INP_INFO_RUNLOCK();
1721 return (stcb);
1722 }
1723 break;
1724 }
1725#endif
1726#ifdef INET6
1727 case AF_INET6:
1728 {
1729 struct sockaddr_in6 *sin6, *rsin6;
1730
1731 sin6 = (struct sockaddr_in6 *)
1732 &net->ro._l_addr;
1733 rsin6 = (struct sockaddr_in6 *)remote;
1734 if (SCTP6_ARE_ADDR_EQUAL(sin6,
1735 rsin6)) {
1736 /* found it */
1737 if (netp != NULL) {
1738 *netp = net;
1739 }
1740 if (locked_tcb == NULL) {
1741 SCTP_INP_DECR_REF(inp);
1742 } else if (locked_tcb != stcb) {
1743 SCTP_TCB_LOCK(locked_tcb);
1744 }
1745 if (locked_tcb) {
1746 atomic_subtract_int(&locked_tcb->asoc.refcnt, 1);
1747 }
1748 SCTP_INP_WUNLOCK(inp);
1749 SCTP_INP_INFO_RUNLOCK();
1750 return (stcb);
1751 }
1752 break;
1753 }
1754#endif
1755#if defined(__Userspace__)
1756 case AF_CONN:
1757 {
1758 struct sockaddr_conn *sconn, *rsconn;
1759
1760 sconn = (struct sockaddr_conn *)&net->ro._l_addr;
1761 rsconn = (struct sockaddr_conn *)remote;
1762 if (sconn->sconn_addr == rsconn->sconn_addr) {
1763 /* found it */
1764 if (netp != NULL) {
1765 *netp = net;
1766 }
1767 if (locked_tcb == NULL) {
1768 SCTP_INP_DECR_REF(inp);
1769 } else if (locked_tcb != stcb) {
1770 SCTP_TCB_LOCK(locked_tcb);
1771 }
1772 if (locked_tcb) {
1773 atomic_subtract_int(&locked_tcb->asoc.refcnt, 1);
1774 }
1775 SCTP_INP_WUNLOCK(inp);
1776 SCTP_INP_INFO_RUNLOCK();
1777 return (stcb);
1778 }
1779 break;
1780 }
1781#endif
1782 default:
1783 /* TSNH */
1784 break;
1785 }
1786 }
1787 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
1788 }
1789 }
1790null_return:
1791 /* clean up for returning null */
1792 if (locked_tcb) {
1793 SCTP_TCB_LOCK(locked_tcb);
1794 atomic_subtract_int(&locked_tcb->asoc.refcnt, 1);
1795 }
1796 SCTP_INP_WUNLOCK(inp);
1797 SCTP_INP_INFO_RUNLOCK();
1798 /* not found */
1799 return (NULL);
1800}
1801
1802/*
1803 * Find an association for a specific endpoint using the association id given
1804 * out in the COMM_UP notification
1805 */
1806struct sctp_tcb *
1807sctp_findasoc_ep_asocid_locked(struct sctp_inpcb *inp, sctp_assoc_t asoc_id, int want_lock)
1808{
1809 /*
1810 * Use my the assoc_id to find a endpoint
1811 */
1812 struct sctpasochead *head;
1813 struct sctp_tcb *stcb;
1814 uint32_t id;
1815
1816 if (inp == NULL) {
1817 SCTP_PRINTF("TSNH ep_associd\n");
1818 return (NULL);
1819 }
1820 if (inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_SOCKET_ALLGONE) {
1821 SCTP_PRINTF("TSNH ep_associd0\n");
1822 return (NULL);
1823 }
1824 id = (uint32_t)asoc_id;
1825 head = &inp->sctp_asocidhash[SCTP_PCBHASH_ASOC(id, inp->hashasocidmark)];
1826 if (head == NULL) {
1827 /* invalid id TSNH */
1828 SCTP_PRINTF("TSNH ep_associd1\n");
1829 return (NULL);
1830 }
1831 LIST_FOREACH(stcb, head, sctp_tcbasocidhash) {
1832 if (stcb->asoc.assoc_id == id) {
1833 if (inp != stcb->sctp_ep) {
1834 /*
1835 * some other guy has the same id active (id
1836 * collision ??).
1837 */
1838 SCTP_PRINTF("TSNH ep_associd2\n");
1839 continue;
1840 }
1841 if (stcb->asoc.state & SCTP_STATE_ABOUT_TO_BE_FREED) {
1842 continue;
1843 }
1844 if (want_lock) {
1845 SCTP_TCB_LOCK(stcb);
1846 }
1847 return (stcb);
1848 }
1849 }
1850 return (NULL);
1851}
1852
1853struct sctp_tcb *
1854sctp_findassociation_ep_asocid(struct sctp_inpcb *inp, sctp_assoc_t asoc_id, int want_lock)
1855{
1856 struct sctp_tcb *stcb;
1857
1858 SCTP_INP_RLOCK(inp);
1859 stcb = sctp_findasoc_ep_asocid_locked(inp, asoc_id, want_lock);
1860 SCTP_INP_RUNLOCK(inp);
1861 return (stcb);
1862}
1863
1864/*
1865 * Endpoint probe expects that the INP_INFO is locked.
1866 */
1867static struct sctp_inpcb *
1868sctp_endpoint_probe(struct sockaddr *nam, struct sctppcbhead *head,
1869 uint16_t lport, uint32_t vrf_id)
1870{
1871 struct sctp_inpcb *inp;
1872 struct sctp_laddr *laddr;
1873#ifdef INET
1874 struct sockaddr_in *sin;
1875#endif
1876#ifdef INET6
1877 struct sockaddr_in6 *sin6;
1878 struct sockaddr_in6 *intf_addr6;
1879#endif
1880#if defined(__Userspace__)
1881 struct sockaddr_conn *sconn;
1882#endif
1883#ifdef SCTP_MVRF
1884 int i;
1885#endif
1886 int fnd;
1887
1888#ifdef INET
1889 sin = NULL;
1890#endif
1891#ifdef INET6
1892 sin6 = NULL;
1893#endif
1894#if defined(__Userspace__)
1895 sconn = NULL;
1896#endif
1897 switch (nam->sa_family) {
1898#ifdef INET
1899 case AF_INET:
1900 sin = (struct sockaddr_in *)nam;
1901 break;
1902#endif
1903#ifdef INET6
1904 case AF_INET6:
1905 sin6 = (struct sockaddr_in6 *)nam;
1906 break;
1907#endif
1908#if defined(__Userspace__)
1909 case AF_CONN:
1910 sconn = (struct sockaddr_conn *)nam;
1911 break;
1912#endif
1913 default:
1914 /* unsupported family */
1915 return (NULL);
1916 }
1917
1918 if (head == NULL)
1919 return (NULL);
1920
1921 LIST_FOREACH(inp, head, sctp_hash) {
1922 SCTP_INP_RLOCK(inp);
1923 if (inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_SOCKET_ALLGONE) {
1924 SCTP_INP_RUNLOCK(inp);
1925 continue;
1926 }
1927 if ((inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_BOUNDALL) &&
1928 (inp->sctp_lport == lport)) {
1929 /* got it */
1930 switch (nam->sa_family) {
1931#ifdef INET
1932 case AF_INET:
1933 if ((inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_BOUND_V6) &&
1934 SCTP_IPV6_V6ONLY(inp)) {
1935 /* IPv4 on a IPv6 socket with ONLY IPv6 set */
1936 SCTP_INP_RUNLOCK(inp);
1937 continue;
1938 }
1939#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
1940 if (prison_check_ip4(inp->ip_inp.inp.inp_cred,
1941 &sin->sin_addr) != 0) {
1942 SCTP_INP_RUNLOCK(inp);
1943 continue;
1944 }
1945#endif
1946 break;
1947#endif
1948#ifdef INET6
1949 case AF_INET6:
1950 /* A V6 address and the endpoint is NOT bound V6 */
1951 if ((inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_BOUND_V6) == 0) {
1952 SCTP_INP_RUNLOCK(inp);
1953 continue;
1954 }
1955#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
1956 if (prison_check_ip6(inp->ip_inp.inp.inp_cred,
1957 &sin6->sin6_addr) != 0) {
1958 SCTP_INP_RUNLOCK(inp);
1959 continue;
1960 }
1961#endif
1962 break;
1963#endif
1964 default:
1965 break;
1966 }
1967 /* does a VRF id match? */
1968 fnd = 0;
1969#ifdef SCTP_MVRF
1970 for (i = 0; i < inp->num_vrfs; i++) {
1971 if (inp->m_vrf_ids[i] == vrf_id) {
1972 fnd = 1;
1973 break;
1974 }
1975 }
1976#else
1977 if (inp->def_vrf_id == vrf_id)
1978 fnd = 1;
1979#endif
1980
1981 SCTP_INP_RUNLOCK(inp);
1982 if (!fnd)
1983 continue;
1984 return (inp);
1985 }
1986 SCTP_INP_RUNLOCK(inp);
1987 }
1988 switch (nam->sa_family) {
1989#ifdef INET
1990 case AF_INET:
1991 if (sin->sin_addr.s_addr == INADDR_ANY) {
1992 /* Can't hunt for one that has no address specified */
1993 return (NULL);
1994 }
1995 break;
1996#endif
1997#ifdef INET6
1998 case AF_INET6:
1999 if (IN6_IS_ADDR_UNSPECIFIED(&sin6->sin6_addr)) {
2000 /* Can't hunt for one that has no address specified */
2001 return (NULL);
2002 }
2003 break;
2004#endif
2005#if defined(__Userspace__)
2006 case AF_CONN:
2007 if (sconn->sconn_addr == NULL) {
2008 return (NULL);
2009 }
2010 break;
2011#endif
2012 default:
2013 break;
2014 }
2015 /*
2016 * ok, not bound to all so see if we can find a EP bound to this
2017 * address.
2018 */
2019 LIST_FOREACH(inp, head, sctp_hash) {
2020 SCTP_INP_RLOCK(inp);
2021 if (inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_SOCKET_ALLGONE) {
2022 SCTP_INP_RUNLOCK(inp);
2023 continue;
2024 }
2025 if ((inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_BOUNDALL)) {
2026 SCTP_INP_RUNLOCK(inp);
2027 continue;
2028 }
2029 /*
2030 * Ok this could be a likely candidate, look at all of its
2031 * addresses
2032 */
2033 if (inp->sctp_lport != lport) {
2034 SCTP_INP_RUNLOCK(inp);
2035 continue;
2036 }
2037 /* does a VRF id match? */
2038 fnd = 0;
2039#ifdef SCTP_MVRF
2040 for (i = 0; i < inp->num_vrfs; i++) {
2041 if (inp->m_vrf_ids[i] == vrf_id) {
2042 fnd = 1;
2043 break;
2044 }
2045 }
2046#else
2047 if (inp->def_vrf_id == vrf_id)
2048 fnd = 1;
2049
2050#endif
2051 if (!fnd) {
2052 SCTP_INP_RUNLOCK(inp);
2053 continue;
2054 }
2055 LIST_FOREACH(laddr, &inp->sctp_addr_list, sctp_nxt_addr) {
2056 if (laddr->ifa == NULL) {
2057 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_PCB1, "%s: NULL ifa\n",
2058 __func__);
2059 continue;
2060 }
2061 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_PCB1, "Ok laddr->ifa:%p is possible, ",
2062 (void *)laddr->ifa);
2063 if (laddr->ifa->localifa_flags & SCTP_BEING_DELETED) {
2064 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_PCB1, "Huh IFA being deleted\n");
2065 continue;
2066 }
2067 if (laddr->ifa->address.sa.sa_family == nam->sa_family) {
2068 /* possible, see if it matches */
2069 switch (nam->sa_family) {
2070#ifdef INET
2071 case AF_INET:
2072#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
2073 if (sin == NULL) {
2074 /* TSNH */
2075 break;
2076 }
2077#endif
2078 if (sin->sin_addr.s_addr ==
2079 laddr->ifa->address.sin.sin_addr.s_addr) {
2080 SCTP_INP_RUNLOCK(inp);
2081 return (inp);
2082 }
2083 break;
2084#endif
2085#ifdef INET6
2086 case AF_INET6:
2087 intf_addr6 = &laddr->ifa->address.sin6;
2088 if (SCTP6_ARE_ADDR_EQUAL(sin6,
2089 intf_addr6)) {
2090 SCTP_INP_RUNLOCK(inp);
2091 return (inp);
2092 }
2093 break;
2094#endif
2095#if defined(__Userspace__)
2096 case AF_CONN:
2097 if (sconn->sconn_addr == laddr->ifa->address.sconn.sconn_addr) {
2098 SCTP_INP_RUNLOCK(inp);
2099 return (inp);
2100 }
2101 break;
2102#endif
2103 }
2104 }
2105 }
2106 SCTP_INP_RUNLOCK(inp);
2107 }
2108 return (NULL);
2109}
2110
2111static struct sctp_inpcb *
2112sctp_isport_inuse(struct sctp_inpcb *inp, uint16_t lport, uint32_t vrf_id)
2113{
2114 struct sctppcbhead *head;
2115 struct sctp_inpcb *t_inp;
2116#ifdef SCTP_MVRF
2117 int i;
2118#endif
2119 int fnd;
2120
2121 head = &SCTP_BASE_INFO(sctp_ephash)[SCTP_PCBHASH_ALLADDR(lport,
2122 SCTP_BASE_INFO(hashmark))];
2123 LIST_FOREACH(t_inp, head, sctp_hash) {
2124 if (t_inp->sctp_lport != lport) {
2125 continue;
2126 }
2127 /* is it in the VRF in question */
2128 fnd = 0;
2129#ifdef SCTP_MVRF
2130 for (i = 0; i < inp->num_vrfs; i++) {
2131 if (t_inp->m_vrf_ids[i] == vrf_id) {
2132 fnd = 1;
2133 break;
2134 }
2135 }
2136#else
2137 if (t_inp->def_vrf_id == vrf_id)
2138 fnd = 1;
2139#endif
2140 if (!fnd)
2141 continue;
2142
2143 /* This one is in use. */
2144 /* check the v6/v4 binding issue */
2145 if ((t_inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_BOUND_V6) &&
2146 SCTP_IPV6_V6ONLY(t_inp)) {
2147 if (inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_BOUND_V6) {
2148 /* collision in V6 space */
2149 return (t_inp);
2150 } else {
2151 /* inp is BOUND_V4 no conflict */
2152 continue;
2153 }
2154 } else if (t_inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_BOUND_V6) {
2155 /* t_inp is bound v4 and v6, conflict always */
2156 return (t_inp);
2157 } else {
2158 /* t_inp is bound only V4 */
2159 if ((inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_BOUND_V6) &&
2160 SCTP_IPV6_V6ONLY(inp)) {
2161 /* no conflict */
2162 continue;
2163 }
2164 /* else fall through to conflict */
2165 }
2166 return (t_inp);
2167 }
2168 return (NULL);
2169}
2170
2171int
2172sctp_swap_inpcb_for_listen(struct sctp_inpcb *inp)
2173{
2174 /* For 1-2-1 with port reuse */
2175 struct sctppcbhead *head;
2176 struct sctp_inpcb *tinp, *ninp;
2177
2178 if (sctp_is_feature_off(inp, SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_PORTREUSE)) {
2179 /* only works with port reuse on */
2180 return (-1);
2181 }
2182 if ((inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_IN_TCPPOOL) == 0) {
2183 return (0);
2184 }
2185 SCTP_INP_RUNLOCK(inp);
2186 SCTP_INP_INFO_WLOCK();
2187 head = &SCTP_BASE_INFO(sctp_ephash)[SCTP_PCBHASH_ALLADDR(inp->sctp_lport,
2188 SCTP_BASE_INFO(hashmark))];
2189 /* Kick out all non-listeners to the TCP hash */
2190 LIST_FOREACH_SAFE(tinp, head, sctp_hash, ninp) {
2191 if (tinp->sctp_lport != inp->sctp_lport) {
2192 continue;
2193 }
2194 if (tinp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_SOCKET_ALLGONE) {
2195 continue;
2196 }
2197 if (tinp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_SOCKET_GONE) {
2198 continue;
2199 }
2200 if (SCTP_IS_LISTENING(tinp)) {
2201 continue;
2202 }
2203 SCTP_INP_WLOCK(tinp);
2204 LIST_REMOVE(tinp, sctp_hash);
2205 head = &SCTP_BASE_INFO(sctp_tcpephash)[SCTP_PCBHASH_ALLADDR(tinp->sctp_lport, SCTP_BASE_INFO(hashtcpmark))];
2206 tinp->sctp_flags |= SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_IN_TCPPOOL;
2207 LIST_INSERT_HEAD(head, tinp, sctp_hash);
2208 SCTP_INP_WUNLOCK(tinp);
2209 }
2210 SCTP_INP_WLOCK(inp);
2211 /* Pull from where he was */
2212 LIST_REMOVE(inp, sctp_hash);
2213 inp->sctp_flags &= ~SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_IN_TCPPOOL;
2214 head = &SCTP_BASE_INFO(sctp_ephash)[SCTP_PCBHASH_ALLADDR(inp->sctp_lport, SCTP_BASE_INFO(hashmark))];
2215 LIST_INSERT_HEAD(head, inp, sctp_hash);
2216 SCTP_INP_WUNLOCK(inp);
2217 SCTP_INP_RLOCK(inp);
2218 SCTP_INP_INFO_WUNLOCK();
2219 return (0);
2220}
2221
2222struct sctp_inpcb *
2223sctp_pcb_findep(struct sockaddr *nam, int find_tcp_pool, int have_lock,
2224 uint32_t vrf_id)
2225{
2226 /*
2227 * First we check the hash table to see if someone has this port
2228 * bound with just the port.
2229 */
2230 struct sctp_inpcb *inp;
2231 struct sctppcbhead *head;
2232 int lport;
2233 unsigned int i;
2234#ifdef INET
2235 struct sockaddr_in *sin;
2236#endif
2237#ifdef INET6
2238 struct sockaddr_in6 *sin6;
2239#endif
2240#if defined(__Userspace__)
2241 struct sockaddr_conn *sconn;
2242#endif
2243
2244 switch (nam->sa_family) {
2245#ifdef INET
2246 case AF_INET:
2247 sin = (struct sockaddr_in *)nam;
2248 lport = sin->sin_port;
2249 break;
2250#endif
2251#ifdef INET6
2252 case AF_INET6:
2253 sin6 = (struct sockaddr_in6 *)nam;
2254 lport = sin6->sin6_port;
2255 break;
2256#endif
2257#if defined(__Userspace__)
2258 case AF_CONN:
2259 sconn = (struct sockaddr_conn *)nam;
2260 lport = sconn->sconn_port;
2261 break;
2262#endif
2263 default:
2264 return (NULL);
2265 }
2266 /*
2267 * I could cheat here and just cast to one of the types but we will
2268 * do it right. It also provides the check against an Unsupported
2269 * type too.
2270 */
2271 /* Find the head of the ALLADDR chain */
2272 if (have_lock == 0) {
2273 SCTP_INP_INFO_RLOCK();
2274 }
2275 head = &SCTP_BASE_INFO(sctp_ephash)[SCTP_PCBHASH_ALLADDR(lport,
2276 SCTP_BASE_INFO(hashmark))];
2277 inp = sctp_endpoint_probe(nam, head, lport, vrf_id);
2278
2279 /*
2280 * If the TCP model exists it could be that the main listening
2281 * endpoint is gone but there still exists a connected socket for this
2282 * guy. If so we can return the first one that we find. This may NOT
2283 * be the correct one so the caller should be wary on the returned INP.
2284 * Currently the only caller that sets find_tcp_pool is in bindx where
2285 * we are verifying that a user CAN bind the address. He either
2286 * has bound it already, or someone else has, or its open to bind,
2287 * so this is good enough.
2288 */
2289 if (inp == NULL && find_tcp_pool) {
2290 for (i = 0; i < SCTP_BASE_INFO(hashtcpmark) + 1; i++) {
2291 head = &SCTP_BASE_INFO(sctp_tcpephash)[i];
2292 inp = sctp_endpoint_probe(nam, head, lport, vrf_id);
2293 if (inp) {
2294 break;
2295 }
2296 }
2297 }
2298 if (inp) {
2299 SCTP_INP_INCR_REF(inp);
2300 }
2301 if (have_lock == 0) {
2302 SCTP_INP_INFO_RUNLOCK();
2303 }
2304 return (inp);
2305}
2306
2307/*
2308 * Find an association for an endpoint with the pointer to whom you want to
2309 * send to and the endpoint pointer. The address can be IPv4 or IPv6. We may
2310 * need to change the *to to some other struct like a mbuf...
2311 */
2312struct sctp_tcb *
2313sctp_findassociation_addr_sa(struct sockaddr *from, struct sockaddr *to,
2314 struct sctp_inpcb **inp_p, struct sctp_nets **netp, int find_tcp_pool,
2315 uint32_t vrf_id)
2316{
2317 struct sctp_inpcb *inp = NULL;
2318 struct sctp_tcb *stcb;
2319
2320 SCTP_INP_INFO_RLOCK();
2321 if (find_tcp_pool) {
2322 if (inp_p != NULL) {
2323 stcb = sctp_tcb_special_locate(inp_p, from, to, netp,
2324 vrf_id);
2325 } else {
2326 stcb = sctp_tcb_special_locate(&inp, from, to, netp,
2327 vrf_id);
2328 }
2329 if (stcb != NULL) {
2330 SCTP_INP_INFO_RUNLOCK();
2331 return (stcb);
2332 }
2333 }
2334 inp = sctp_pcb_findep(to, 0, 1, vrf_id);
2335 if (inp_p != NULL) {
2336 *inp_p = inp;
2337 }
2338 SCTP_INP_INFO_RUNLOCK();
2339 if (inp == NULL) {
2340 return (NULL);
2341 }
2342 /*
2343 * ok, we have an endpoint, now lets find the assoc for it (if any)
2344 * we now place the source address or from in the to of the find
2345 * endpoint call. Since in reality this chain is used from the
2346 * inbound packet side.
2347 */
2348 if (inp_p != NULL) {
2349 stcb = sctp_findassociation_ep_addr(inp_p, from, netp, to,
2350 NULL);
2351 } else {
2352 stcb = sctp_findassociation_ep_addr(&inp, from, netp, to,
2353 NULL);
2354 }
2355 return (stcb);
2356}
2357
2358/*
2359 * This routine will grub through the mbuf that is a INIT or INIT-ACK and
2360 * find all addresses that the sender has specified in any address list. Each
2361 * address will be used to lookup the TCB and see if one exits.
2362 */
2363static struct sctp_tcb *
2364sctp_findassociation_special_addr(struct mbuf *m, int offset,
2365 struct sctphdr *sh, struct sctp_inpcb **inp_p, struct sctp_nets **netp,
2366 struct sockaddr *dst)
2367{
2368 struct sctp_paramhdr *phdr, param_buf;
2369#if defined(INET) || defined(INET6)
2370 struct sctp_tcb *stcb;
2371 uint16_t ptype;
2372#endif
2373 uint16_t plen;
2374#ifdef INET
2375 struct sockaddr_in sin4;
2376#endif
2377#ifdef INET6
2378 struct sockaddr_in6 sin6;
2379#endif
2380
2381#ifdef INET
2382 memset(&sin4, 0, sizeof(sin4));
2383#ifdef HAVE_SIN_LEN
2384 sin4.sin_len = sizeof(sin4);
2385#endif
2386 sin4.sin_family = AF_INET;
2387 sin4.sin_port = sh->src_port;
2388#endif
2389#ifdef INET6
2390 memset(&sin6, 0, sizeof(sin6));
2391#ifdef HAVE_SIN6_LEN
2392 sin6.sin6_len = sizeof(sin6);
2393#endif
2394 sin6.sin6_family = AF_INET6;
2395 sin6.sin6_port = sh->src_port;
2396#endif
2397
2398 offset += sizeof(struct sctp_init_chunk);
2399
2400 phdr = sctp_get_next_param(m, offset, &param_buf, sizeof(param_buf));
2401 while (phdr != NULL) {
2402 /* now we must see if we want the parameter */
2403#if defined(INET) || defined(INET6)
2404 ptype = ntohs(phdr->param_type);
2405#endif
2406 plen = ntohs(phdr->param_length);
2407 if (plen == 0) {
2408 break;
2409 }
2410#ifdef INET
2411 if (ptype == SCTP_IPV4_ADDRESS &&
2412 plen == sizeof(struct sctp_ipv4addr_param)) {
2413 /* Get the rest of the address */
2414 struct sctp_ipv4addr_param ip4_param, *p4;
2415
2416 phdr = sctp_get_next_param(m, offset,
2417 (struct sctp_paramhdr *)&ip4_param, sizeof(ip4_param));
2418 if (phdr == NULL) {
2419 return (NULL);
2420 }
2421 p4 = (struct sctp_ipv4addr_param *)phdr;
2422 memcpy(&sin4.sin_addr, &p4->addr, sizeof(p4->addr));
2423 /* look it up */
2424 stcb = sctp_findassociation_ep_addr(inp_p,
2425 (struct sockaddr *)&sin4, netp, dst, NULL);
2426 if (stcb != NULL) {
2427 return (stcb);
2428 }
2429 }
2430#endif
2431#ifdef INET6
2432 if (ptype == SCTP_IPV6_ADDRESS &&
2433 plen == sizeof(struct sctp_ipv6addr_param)) {
2434 /* Get the rest of the address */
2435 struct sctp_ipv6addr_param ip6_param, *p6;
2436
2437 phdr = sctp_get_next_param(m, offset,
2438 (struct sctp_paramhdr *)&ip6_param, sizeof(ip6_param));
2439 if (phdr == NULL) {
2440 return (NULL);
2441 }
2442 p6 = (struct sctp_ipv6addr_param *)phdr;
2443 memcpy(&sin6.sin6_addr, &p6->addr, sizeof(p6->addr));
2444 /* look it up */
2445 stcb = sctp_findassociation_ep_addr(inp_p,
2446 (struct sockaddr *)&sin6, netp, dst, NULL);
2447 if (stcb != NULL) {
2448 return (stcb);
2449 }
2450 }
2451#endif
2452 offset += SCTP_SIZE32(plen);
2453 phdr = sctp_get_next_param(m, offset, &param_buf,
2454 sizeof(param_buf));
2455 }
2456 return (NULL);
2457}
2458
2459static struct sctp_tcb *
2460sctp_findassoc_by_vtag(struct sockaddr *from, struct sockaddr *to, uint32_t vtag,
2461 struct sctp_inpcb **inp_p, struct sctp_nets **netp, uint16_t rport,
2462 uint16_t lport, int skip_src_check, uint32_t vrf_id, uint32_t remote_tag)
2463{
2464 /*
2465 * Use my vtag to hash. If we find it we then verify the source addr
2466 * is in the assoc. If all goes well we save a bit on rec of a
2467 * packet.
2468 */
2469 struct sctpasochead *head;
2470 struct sctp_nets *net;
2471 struct sctp_tcb *stcb;
2472#ifdef SCTP_MVRF
2473 unsigned int i;
2474#endif
2475
2476 SCTP_INP_INFO_RLOCK();
2477 head = &SCTP_BASE_INFO(sctp_asochash)[SCTP_PCBHASH_ASOC(vtag,
2478 SCTP_BASE_INFO(hashasocmark))];
2479 LIST_FOREACH(stcb, head, sctp_asocs) {
2480 SCTP_INP_RLOCK(stcb->sctp_ep);
2481 if (stcb->sctp_ep->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_SOCKET_ALLGONE) {
2482 SCTP_INP_RUNLOCK(stcb->sctp_ep);
2483 continue;
2484 }
2485#ifdef SCTP_MVRF
2486 for (i = 0; i < stcb->sctp_ep->num_vrfs; i++) {
2487 if (stcb->sctp_ep->m_vrf_ids[i] == vrf_id) {
2488 break;
2489 }
2490 }
2491 if (i == stcb->sctp_ep->num_vrfs) {
2492 SCTP_INP_RUNLOCK(inp);
2493 continue;
2494 }
2495#else
2496 if (stcb->sctp_ep->def_vrf_id != vrf_id) {
2497 SCTP_INP_RUNLOCK(stcb->sctp_ep);
2498 continue;
2499 }
2500#endif
2501 SCTP_TCB_LOCK(stcb);
2502 SCTP_INP_RUNLOCK(stcb->sctp_ep);
2503 if (stcb->asoc.my_vtag == vtag) {
2504 /* candidate */
2505 if (stcb->rport != rport) {
2506 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
2507 continue;
2508 }
2509 if (stcb->sctp_ep->sctp_lport != lport) {
2510 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
2511 continue;
2512 }
2513 if (stcb->asoc.state & SCTP_STATE_ABOUT_TO_BE_FREED) {
2514 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
2515 continue;
2516 }
2517 /* RRS:Need toaddr check here */
2518 if (sctp_does_stcb_own_this_addr(stcb, to) == 0) {
2519 /* Endpoint does not own this address */
2520 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
2521 continue;
2522 }
2523 if (remote_tag) {
2524 /* If we have both vtags that's all we match on */
2525 if (stcb->asoc.peer_vtag == remote_tag) {
2526 /* If both tags match we consider it conclusive
2527 * and check NO source/destination addresses
2528 */
2529 goto conclusive;
2530 }
2531 }
2532 if (skip_src_check) {
2533 conclusive:
2534 if (from) {
2535 *netp = sctp_findnet(stcb, from);
2536 } else {
2537 *netp = NULL; /* unknown */
2538 }
2539 if (inp_p)
2540 *inp_p = stcb->sctp_ep;
2541 SCTP_INP_INFO_RUNLOCK();
2542 return (stcb);
2543 }
2544 net = sctp_findnet(stcb, from);
2545 if (net) {
2546 /* yep its him. */
2547 *netp = net;
2548 SCTP_STAT_INCR(sctps_vtagexpress);
2549 *inp_p = stcb->sctp_ep;
2550 SCTP_INP_INFO_RUNLOCK();
2551 return (stcb);
2552 } else {
2553 /*
2554 * not him, this should only happen in rare
2555 * cases so I peg it.
2556 */
2557 SCTP_STAT_INCR(sctps_vtagbogus);
2558 }
2559 }
2560 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
2561 }
2562 SCTP_INP_INFO_RUNLOCK();
2563 return (NULL);
2564}
2565
2566/*
2567 * Find an association with the pointer to the inbound IP packet. This can be
2568 * a IPv4 or IPv6 packet.
2569 */
2570struct sctp_tcb *
2571sctp_findassociation_addr(struct mbuf *m, int offset,
2572 struct sockaddr *src, struct sockaddr *dst,
2573 struct sctphdr *sh, struct sctp_chunkhdr *ch,
2574 struct sctp_inpcb **inp_p, struct sctp_nets **netp, uint32_t vrf_id)
2575{
2576 struct sctp_tcb *stcb;
2577 struct sctp_inpcb *inp;
2578
2579 if (sh->v_tag) {
2580 /* we only go down this path if vtag is non-zero */
2581 stcb = sctp_findassoc_by_vtag(src, dst, ntohl(sh->v_tag),
2582 inp_p, netp, sh->src_port, sh->dest_port, 0, vrf_id, 0);
2583 if (stcb) {
2584 return (stcb);
2585 }
2586 }
2587
2588 if (inp_p) {
2589 stcb = sctp_findassociation_addr_sa(src, dst, inp_p, netp,
2590 1, vrf_id);
2591 inp = *inp_p;
2592 } else {
2593 stcb = sctp_findassociation_addr_sa(src, dst, &inp, netp,
2594 1, vrf_id);
2595 }
2596 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_PCB1, "stcb:%p inp:%p\n", (void *)stcb, (void *)inp);
2597 if (stcb == NULL && inp) {
2598 /* Found a EP but not this address */
2599 if ((ch->chunk_type == SCTP_INITIATION) ||
2600 (ch->chunk_type == SCTP_INITIATION_ACK)) {
2601 /*-
2602 * special hook, we do NOT return linp or an
2603 * association that is linked to an existing
2604 * association that is under the TCP pool (i.e. no
2605 * listener exists). The endpoint finding routine
2606 * will always find a listener before examining the
2607 * TCP pool.
2608 */
2609 if (inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_IN_TCPPOOL) {
2610 if (inp_p) {
2611 *inp_p = NULL;
2612 }
2613 return (NULL);
2614 }
2615 stcb = sctp_findassociation_special_addr(m,
2616 offset, sh, &inp, netp, dst);
2617 if (inp_p != NULL) {
2618 *inp_p = inp;
2619 }
2620 }
2621 }
2622 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_PCB1, "stcb is %p\n", (void *)stcb);
2623 return (stcb);
2624}
2625
2626/*
2627 * lookup an association by an ASCONF lookup address.
2628 * if the lookup address is 0.0.0.0 or ::0, use the vtag to do the lookup
2629 */
2630struct sctp_tcb *
2631sctp_findassociation_ep_asconf(struct mbuf *m, int offset,
2632 struct sockaddr *dst, struct sctphdr *sh,
2633 struct sctp_inpcb **inp_p, struct sctp_nets **netp, uint32_t vrf_id)
2634{
2635 struct sctp_tcb *stcb;
2636 union sctp_sockstore remote_store;
2637 struct sctp_paramhdr param_buf, *phdr;
2638 int ptype;
2639 int zero_address = 0;
2640#ifdef INET
2641 struct sockaddr_in *sin;
2642#endif
2643#ifdef INET6
2644 struct sockaddr_in6 *sin6;
2645#endif
2646
2647 memset(&remote_store, 0, sizeof(remote_store));
2648 phdr = sctp_get_next_param(m, offset + sizeof(struct sctp_asconf_chunk),
2649 &param_buf, sizeof(struct sctp_paramhdr));
2650 if (phdr == NULL) {
2651 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_INPUT3, "%s: failed to get asconf lookup addr\n",
2652 __func__);
2653 return NULL;
2654 }
2655 ptype = (int)((uint32_t) ntohs(phdr->param_type));
2656 /* get the correlation address */
2657 switch (ptype) {
2658#ifdef INET6
2659 case SCTP_IPV6_ADDRESS:
2660 {
2661 /* ipv6 address param */
2662 struct sctp_ipv6addr_param *p6, p6_buf;
2663
2664 if (ntohs(phdr->param_length) != sizeof(struct sctp_ipv6addr_param)) {
2665 return NULL;
2666 }
2667 p6 = (struct sctp_ipv6addr_param *)sctp_get_next_param(m,
2668 offset + sizeof(struct sctp_asconf_chunk),
2669 &p6_buf.ph, sizeof(p6_buf));
2670 if (p6 == NULL) {
2671 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_INPUT3, "%s: failed to get asconf v6 lookup addr\n",
2672 __func__);
2673 return (NULL);
2674 }
2675 sin6 = &remote_store.sin6;
2676 sin6->sin6_family = AF_INET6;
2677#ifdef HAVE_SIN6_LEN
2678 sin6->sin6_len = sizeof(*sin6);
2679#endif
2680 sin6->sin6_port = sh->src_port;
2681 memcpy(&sin6->sin6_addr, &p6->addr, sizeof(struct in6_addr));
2682 if (IN6_IS_ADDR_UNSPECIFIED(&sin6->sin6_addr))
2683 zero_address = 1;
2684 break;
2685 }
2686#endif
2687#ifdef INET
2688 case SCTP_IPV4_ADDRESS:
2689 {
2690 /* ipv4 address param */
2691 struct sctp_ipv4addr_param *p4, p4_buf;
2692
2693 if (ntohs(phdr->param_length) != sizeof(struct sctp_ipv4addr_param)) {
2694 return NULL;
2695 }
2696 p4 = (struct sctp_ipv4addr_param *)sctp_get_next_param(m,
2697 offset + sizeof(struct sctp_asconf_chunk),
2698 &p4_buf.ph, sizeof(p4_buf));
2699 if (p4 == NULL) {
2700 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_INPUT3, "%s: failed to get asconf v4 lookup addr\n",
2701 __func__);
2702 return (NULL);
2703 }
2704 sin = &remote_store.sin;
2705 sin->sin_family = AF_INET;
2706#ifdef HAVE_SIN_LEN
2707 sin->sin_len = sizeof(*sin);
2708#endif
2709 sin->sin_port = sh->src_port;
2710 memcpy(&sin->sin_addr, &p4->addr, sizeof(struct in_addr));
2711 if (sin->sin_addr.s_addr == INADDR_ANY)
2712 zero_address = 1;
2713 break;
2714 }
2715#endif
2716 default:
2717 /* invalid address param type */
2718 return NULL;
2719 }
2720
2721 if (zero_address) {
2722 stcb = sctp_findassoc_by_vtag(NULL, dst, ntohl(sh->v_tag), inp_p,
2723 netp, sh->src_port, sh->dest_port, 1, vrf_id, 0);
2724 if (stcb != NULL) {
2725 SCTP_INP_DECR_REF(*inp_p);
2726 }
2727 } else {
2728 stcb = sctp_findassociation_ep_addr(inp_p,
2729 &remote_store.sa, netp,
2730 dst, NULL);
2731 }
2732 return (stcb);
2733}
2734
2735/*
2736 * allocate a sctp_inpcb and setup a temporary binding to a port/all
2737 * addresses. This way if we don't get a bind we by default pick a ephemeral
2738 * port with all addresses bound.
2739 */
2740int
2741sctp_inpcb_alloc(struct socket *so, uint32_t vrf_id)
2742{
2743 /*
2744 * we get called when a new endpoint starts up. We need to allocate
2745 * the sctp_inpcb structure from the zone and init it. Mark it as
2746 * unbound and find a port that we can use as an ephemeral with
2747 * INADDR_ANY. If the user binds later no problem we can then add in
2748 * the specific addresses. And setup the default parameters for the
2749 * EP.
2750 */
2751 int i, error;
2752 struct sctp_inpcb *inp;
2753 struct sctp_pcb *m;
2754 struct timeval time;
2755 sctp_sharedkey_t *null_key;
2756
2757 error = 0;
2758
2759 SCTP_INP_INFO_WLOCK();
2760 inp = SCTP_ZONE_GET(SCTP_BASE_INFO(ipi_zone_ep), struct sctp_inpcb);
2761 if (inp == NULL) {
2762 SCTP_PRINTF("Out of SCTP-INPCB structures - no resources\n");
2763 SCTP_INP_INFO_WUNLOCK();
2764 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_PCB, ENOBUFS);
2765 return (ENOBUFS);
2766 }
2767 /* zap it */
2768 memset(inp, 0, sizeof(*inp));
2769
2770 /* bump generations */
2771#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
2772 inp->ip_inp.inp.inp_state = INPCB_STATE_INUSE;
2773#endif
2774 /* setup socket pointers */
2775 inp->sctp_socket = so;
2776 inp->ip_inp.inp.inp_socket = so;
2777#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
2778 inp->ip_inp.inp.inp_cred = crhold(so->so_cred);
2779#endif
2780#ifdef INET6
2781#if !defined(__Userspace__) && !defined(_WIN32)
2782 if (INP_SOCKAF(so) == AF_INET6) {
2783 if (MODULE_GLOBAL(ip6_auto_flowlabel)) {
2784 inp->ip_inp.inp.inp_flags |= IN6P_AUTOFLOWLABEL;
2785 }
2786 if (MODULE_GLOBAL(ip6_v6only)) {
2787 inp->ip_inp.inp.inp_flags |= IN6P_IPV6_V6ONLY;
2788 }
2789 }
2790#endif
2791#endif
2792 inp->sctp_associd_counter = 1;
2793 inp->partial_delivery_point = SCTP_SB_LIMIT_RCV(so) >> SCTP_PARTIAL_DELIVERY_SHIFT;
2794 inp->sctp_frag_point = SCTP_DEFAULT_MAXSEGMENT;
2795 inp->max_cwnd = 0;
2796 inp->sctp_cmt_on_off = SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_cmt_on_off);
2797 inp->ecn_supported = (uint8_t)SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_ecn_enable);
2798 inp->prsctp_supported = (uint8_t)SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_pr_enable);
2799 inp->auth_supported = (uint8_t)SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_auth_enable);
2800 inp->asconf_supported = (uint8_t)SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_asconf_enable);
2801 inp->reconfig_supported = (uint8_t)SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_reconfig_enable);
2802 inp->nrsack_supported = (uint8_t)SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_nrsack_enable);
2803 inp->pktdrop_supported = (uint8_t)SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_pktdrop_enable);
2804 inp->idata_supported = 0;
2805
2806#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
2807 inp->fibnum = so->so_fibnum;
2808#else
2809 inp->fibnum = 0;
2810#endif
2811#if defined(__Userspace__)
2812 inp->ulp_info = NULL;
2813 inp->recv_callback = NULL;
2814 inp->send_callback = NULL;
2815 inp->send_sb_threshold = 0;
2816#endif
2817 /* init the small hash table we use to track asocid <-> tcb */
2818 inp->sctp_asocidhash = SCTP_HASH_INIT(SCTP_STACK_VTAG_HASH_SIZE, &inp->hashasocidmark);
2819 if (inp->sctp_asocidhash == NULL) {
2820#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
2821 crfree(inp->ip_inp.inp.inp_cred);
2822#endif
2823 SCTP_ZONE_FREE(SCTP_BASE_INFO(ipi_zone_ep), inp);
2824 SCTP_INP_INFO_WUNLOCK();
2825 return (ENOBUFS);
2826 }
2827 SCTP_INCR_EP_COUNT();
2828 inp->ip_inp.inp.inp_ip_ttl = MODULE_GLOBAL(ip_defttl);
2829 SCTP_INP_INFO_WUNLOCK();
2830
2831 so->so_pcb = (caddr_t)inp;
2832
2833 if (SCTP_SO_TYPE(so) == SOCK_SEQPACKET) {
2834 /* UDP style socket */
2835 inp->sctp_flags = (SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_UDPTYPE |
2836 SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_UNBOUND);
2837 /* Be sure it is NON-BLOCKING IO for UDP */
2838 /* SCTP_SET_SO_NBIO(so); */
2839 } else if (SCTP_SO_TYPE(so) == SOCK_STREAM) {
2840 /* TCP style socket */
2841 inp->sctp_flags = (SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_TCPTYPE |
2842 SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_UNBOUND);
2843 /* Be sure we have blocking IO by default */
2844 SOCK_LOCK(so);
2845 SCTP_CLEAR_SO_NBIO(so);
2846 SOCK_UNLOCK(so);
2847 } else {
2848 /*
2849 * unsupported socket type (RAW, etc)- in case we missed it
2850 * in protosw
2851 */
2852 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_PCB, EOPNOTSUPP);
2853 so->so_pcb = NULL;
2854#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
2855 crfree(inp->ip_inp.inp.inp_cred);
2856#endif
2857 SCTP_ZONE_FREE(SCTP_BASE_INFO(ipi_zone_ep), inp);
2858 return (EOPNOTSUPP);
2859 }
2860 if (SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_default_frag_interleave) == SCTP_FRAG_LEVEL_1) {
2861 sctp_feature_on(inp, SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_FRAG_INTERLEAVE);
2862 sctp_feature_off(inp, SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_INTERLEAVE_STRMS);
2863 } else if (SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_default_frag_interleave) == SCTP_FRAG_LEVEL_2) {
2864 sctp_feature_on(inp, SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_FRAG_INTERLEAVE);
2865 sctp_feature_on(inp, SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_INTERLEAVE_STRMS);
2866 } else if (SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_default_frag_interleave) == SCTP_FRAG_LEVEL_0) {
2867 sctp_feature_off(inp, SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_FRAG_INTERLEAVE);
2868 sctp_feature_off(inp, SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_INTERLEAVE_STRMS);
2869 }
2870 inp->sctp_tcbhash = SCTP_HASH_INIT(SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_pcbtblsize),
2871 &inp->sctp_hashmark);
2872 if (inp->sctp_tcbhash == NULL) {
2873 SCTP_PRINTF("Out of SCTP-INPCB->hashinit - no resources\n");
2874 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_PCB, ENOBUFS);
2875 so->so_pcb = NULL;
2876#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
2877 crfree(inp->ip_inp.inp.inp_cred);
2878#endif
2879 SCTP_ZONE_FREE(SCTP_BASE_INFO(ipi_zone_ep), inp);
2880 return (ENOBUFS);
2881 }
2882#ifdef SCTP_MVRF
2883 inp->vrf_size = SCTP_DEFAULT_VRF_SIZE;
2884 SCTP_MALLOC(inp->m_vrf_ids, uint32_t *,
2885 (sizeof(uint32_t) * inp->vrf_size), SCTP_M_MVRF);
2886 if (inp->m_vrf_ids == NULL) {
2887 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_PCB, ENOBUFS);
2888 so->so_pcb = NULL;
2889 SCTP_HASH_FREE(inp->sctp_tcbhash, inp->sctp_hashmark);
2890#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
2891 crfree(inp->ip_inp.inp.inp_cred);
2892#endif
2893 SCTP_ZONE_FREE(SCTP_BASE_INFO(ipi_zone_ep), inp);
2894 return (ENOBUFS);
2895 }
2896 inp->m_vrf_ids[0] = vrf_id;
2897 inp->num_vrfs = 1;
2898#endif
2899 inp->def_vrf_id = vrf_id;
2900
2901#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
2902#if defined(APPLE_LEOPARD) || defined(APPLE_SNOWLEOPARD)
2903 inp->ip_inp.inp.inpcb_mtx = lck_mtx_alloc_init(SCTP_BASE_INFO(sctbinfo).mtx_grp, SCTP_BASE_INFO(sctbinfo).mtx_attr);
2904 if (inp->ip_inp.inp.inpcb_mtx == NULL) {
2905 SCTP_PRINTF("in_pcballoc: can't alloc mutex! so=%p\n", (void *)so);
2906#ifdef SCTP_MVRF
2907 SCTP_FREE(inp->m_vrf_ids, SCTP_M_MVRF);
2908#endif
2909 SCTP_HASH_FREE(inp->sctp_tcbhash, inp->sctp_hashmark);
2910 so->so_pcb = NULL;
2911 SCTP_ZONE_FREE(SCTP_BASE_INFO(ipi_zone_ep), inp);
2912 SCTP_UNLOCK_EXC(SCTP_BASE_INFO(sctbinfo).ipi_lock);
2913 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_PCB, ENOMEM);
2914 return (ENOMEM);
2915 }
2916#elif defined(APPLE_LION) || defined(APPLE_MOUNTAINLION)
2917 lck_mtx_init(&inp->ip_inp.inp.inpcb_mtx, SCTP_BASE_INFO(sctbinfo).mtx_grp, SCTP_BASE_INFO(sctbinfo).mtx_attr);
