2918#else
2919 lck_mtx_init(&inp->ip_inp.inp.inpcb_mtx, SCTP_BASE_INFO(sctbinfo).ipi_lock_grp, SCTP_BASE_INFO(sctbinfo).ipi_lock_attr);
2920#endif
2921#endif
2922 SCTP_INP_INFO_WLOCK();
2923 SCTP_INP_LOCK_INIT(inp);
2924#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
2925 INP_LOCK_INIT(&inp->ip_inp.inp, "inp", "sctpinp");
2926#endif
2927 SCTP_INP_READ_INIT(inp);
2928 SCTP_ASOC_CREATE_LOCK_INIT(inp);
2929 /* lock the new ep */
2930 SCTP_INP_WLOCK(inp);
2931
2932 /* add it to the info area */
2933 LIST_INSERT_HEAD(&SCTP_BASE_INFO(listhead), inp, sctp_list);
2934#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
2935 inp->ip_inp.inp.inp_pcbinfo = &SCTP_BASE_INFO(sctbinfo);
2936#if defined(APPLE_LEOPARD) || defined(APPLE_SNOWLEOPARD) || defined(APPLE_LION) || defined(APPLE_MOUNTAINLION)
2937 LIST_INSERT_HEAD(SCTP_BASE_INFO(sctbinfo).listhead, &inp->ip_inp.inp, inp_list);
2938#else
2939 LIST_INSERT_HEAD(SCTP_BASE_INFO(sctbinfo).ipi_listhead, &inp->ip_inp.inp, inp_list);
2940#endif
2941#endif
2942 SCTP_INP_INFO_WUNLOCK();
2943
2944 TAILQ_INIT(&inp->read_queue);
2945 LIST_INIT(&inp->sctp_addr_list);
2946
2947 LIST_INIT(&inp->sctp_asoc_list);
2948
2949#ifdef SCTP_TRACK_FREED_ASOCS
2950 /* TEMP CODE */
2951 LIST_INIT(&inp->sctp_asoc_free_list);
2952#endif
2953 /* Init the timer structure for signature change */
2954 SCTP_OS_TIMER_INIT(&inp->sctp_ep.signature_change.timer);
2955 inp->sctp_ep.signature_change.type = SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_NEWCOOKIE;
2956
2957 /* now init the actual endpoint default data */
2958 m = &inp->sctp_ep;
2959
2960 /* setup the base timeout information */
2961 m->sctp_timeoutticks[SCTP_TIMER_SEND] = sctp_secs_to_ticks(SCTP_SEND_SEC); /* needed ? */
2962 m->sctp_timeoutticks[SCTP_TIMER_INIT] = sctp_secs_to_ticks(SCTP_INIT_SEC); /* needed ? */
2963 m->sctp_timeoutticks[SCTP_TIMER_RECV] = sctp_msecs_to_ticks(SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_delayed_sack_time_default));
2964 m->sctp_timeoutticks[SCTP_TIMER_HEARTBEAT] = sctp_msecs_to_ticks(SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_heartbeat_interval_default));
2965 m->sctp_timeoutticks[SCTP_TIMER_PMTU] = sctp_secs_to_ticks(SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_pmtu_raise_time_default));
2966 m->sctp_timeoutticks[SCTP_TIMER_MAXSHUTDOWN] = sctp_secs_to_ticks(SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_shutdown_guard_time_default));
2967 m->sctp_timeoutticks[SCTP_TIMER_SIGNATURE] = sctp_secs_to_ticks(SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_secret_lifetime_default));
2968 /* all max/min max are in ms */
2969 m->sctp_maxrto = SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_rto_max_default);
2970 m->sctp_minrto = SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_rto_min_default);
2971 m->initial_rto = SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_rto_initial_default);
2972 m->initial_init_rto_max = SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_init_rto_max_default);
2973 m->sctp_sack_freq = SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_sack_freq_default);
2974 m->max_init_times = SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_init_rtx_max_default);
2975 m->max_send_times = SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_assoc_rtx_max_default);
2976 m->def_net_failure = SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_path_rtx_max_default);
2977 m->def_net_pf_threshold = SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_path_pf_threshold);
2978 m->sctp_sws_sender = SCTP_SWS_SENDER_DEF;
2979 m->sctp_sws_receiver = SCTP_SWS_RECEIVER_DEF;
2980 m->max_burst = SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_max_burst_default);
2981 m->fr_max_burst = SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_fr_max_burst_default);
2982
2983 m->sctp_default_cc_module = SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_default_cc_module);
2984 m->sctp_default_ss_module = SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_default_ss_module);
2985 m->max_open_streams_intome = SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_nr_incoming_streams_default);
2986 /* number of streams to pre-open on a association */
2987 m->pre_open_stream_count = SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_nr_outgoing_streams_default);
2988
2989 m->default_mtu = 0;
2990 /* Add adaptation cookie */
2991 m->adaptation_layer_indicator = 0;
2992 m->adaptation_layer_indicator_provided = 0;
2993
2994 /* seed random number generator */
2995 m->random_counter = 1;
2996 m->store_at = SCTP_SIGNATURE_SIZE;
2997 SCTP_READ_RANDOM(m->random_numbers, sizeof(m->random_numbers));
2998 sctp_fill_random_store(m);
2999
3000 /* Minimum cookie size */
3001 m->size_of_a_cookie = (sizeof(struct sctp_init_msg) * 2) +
3002 sizeof(struct sctp_state_cookie);
3003 m->size_of_a_cookie += SCTP_SIGNATURE_SIZE;
3004
3005 /* Setup the initial secret */
3006 (void)SCTP_GETTIME_TIMEVAL(&time);
3007 m->time_of_secret_change = time.tv_sec;
3008
3009 for (i = 0; i < SCTP_NUMBER_OF_SECRETS; i++) {
3010 m->secret_key[0][i] = sctp_select_initial_TSN(m);
3011 }
3012 sctp_timer_start(SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_NEWCOOKIE, inp, NULL, NULL);
3013
3014 /* How long is a cookie good for ? */
3015 m->def_cookie_life = sctp_msecs_to_ticks(SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_valid_cookie_life_default));
3016 /*
3017 * Initialize authentication parameters
3018 */
3019 m->local_hmacs = sctp_default_supported_hmaclist();
3020 m->local_auth_chunks = sctp_alloc_chunklist();
3021 if (inp->asconf_supported) {
3022 sctp_auth_add_chunk(SCTP_ASCONF, m->local_auth_chunks);
3023 sctp_auth_add_chunk(SCTP_ASCONF_ACK, m->local_auth_chunks);
3024 }
3025 m->default_dscp = 0;
3026#ifdef INET6
3027 m->default_flowlabel = 0;
3028#endif
3029 m->port = 0; /* encapsulation disabled by default */
3030 LIST_INIT(&m->shared_keys);
3031 /* add default NULL key as key id 0 */
3032 null_key = sctp_alloc_sharedkey();
3033 sctp_insert_sharedkey(&m->shared_keys, null_key);
3034 SCTP_INP_WUNLOCK(inp);
3035#ifdef SCTP_LOG_CLOSING
3036 sctp_log_closing(inp, NULL, 12);
3037#endif
3038 return (error);
3039}
3040
3041void
3042sctp_move_pcb_and_assoc(struct sctp_inpcb *old_inp, struct sctp_inpcb *new_inp,
3043 struct sctp_tcb *stcb)
3044{
3045 struct sctp_nets *net;
3046 uint16_t lport, rport;
3047 struct sctppcbhead *head;
3048 struct sctp_laddr *laddr, *oladdr;
3049
3050 atomic_add_int(&stcb->asoc.refcnt, 1);
3051 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
3052 SCTP_INP_INFO_WLOCK();
3053 SCTP_INP_WLOCK(old_inp);
3054 SCTP_INP_WLOCK(new_inp);
3055 SCTP_TCB_LOCK(stcb);
3056 atomic_subtract_int(&stcb->asoc.refcnt, 1);
3057
3058 new_inp->sctp_ep.time_of_secret_change =
3059 old_inp->sctp_ep.time_of_secret_change;
3060 memcpy(new_inp->sctp_ep.secret_key, old_inp->sctp_ep.secret_key,
3061 sizeof(old_inp->sctp_ep.secret_key));
3062 new_inp->sctp_ep.current_secret_number =
3063 old_inp->sctp_ep.current_secret_number;
3064 new_inp->sctp_ep.last_secret_number =
3065 old_inp->sctp_ep.last_secret_number;
3066 new_inp->sctp_ep.size_of_a_cookie = old_inp->sctp_ep.size_of_a_cookie;
3067
3068 /* make it so new data pours into the new socket */
3069 stcb->sctp_socket = new_inp->sctp_socket;
3070 stcb->sctp_ep = new_inp;
3071
3072 /* Copy the port across */
3073 lport = new_inp->sctp_lport = old_inp->sctp_lport;
3074 rport = stcb->rport;
3075 /* Pull the tcb from the old association */
3076 LIST_REMOVE(stcb, sctp_tcbhash);
3077 LIST_REMOVE(stcb, sctp_tcblist);
3078 if (stcb->asoc.in_asocid_hash) {
3079 LIST_REMOVE(stcb, sctp_tcbasocidhash);
3080 }
3081 /* Now insert the new_inp into the TCP connected hash */
3082 head = &SCTP_BASE_INFO(sctp_tcpephash)[SCTP_PCBHASH_ALLADDR((lport | rport), SCTP_BASE_INFO(hashtcpmark))];
3083
3084 LIST_INSERT_HEAD(head, new_inp, sctp_hash);
3085 /* Its safe to access */
3086 new_inp->sctp_flags &= ~SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_UNBOUND;
3087
3088 /* Now move the tcb into the endpoint list */
3089 LIST_INSERT_HEAD(&new_inp->sctp_asoc_list, stcb, sctp_tcblist);
3090 /*
3091 * Question, do we even need to worry about the ep-hash since we
3092 * only have one connection? Probably not :> so lets get rid of it
3093 * and not suck up any kernel memory in that.
3094 */
3095 if (stcb->asoc.in_asocid_hash) {
3096 struct sctpasochead *lhd;
3097 lhd = &new_inp->sctp_asocidhash[SCTP_PCBHASH_ASOC(stcb->asoc.assoc_id,
3098 new_inp->hashasocidmark)];
3099 LIST_INSERT_HEAD(lhd, stcb, sctp_tcbasocidhash);
3100 }
3101 /* Ok. Let's restart timer. */
3102 TAILQ_FOREACH(net, &stcb->asoc.nets, sctp_next) {
3103 sctp_timer_start(SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_PATHMTURAISE, new_inp,
3104 stcb, net);
3105 }
3106
3107 SCTP_INP_INFO_WUNLOCK();
3108 if (new_inp->sctp_tcbhash != NULL) {
3109 SCTP_HASH_FREE(new_inp->sctp_tcbhash, new_inp->sctp_hashmark);
3110 new_inp->sctp_tcbhash = NULL;
3111 }
3112 if ((new_inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_BOUNDALL) == 0) {
3113 /* Subset bound, so copy in the laddr list from the old_inp */
3114 LIST_FOREACH(oladdr, &old_inp->sctp_addr_list, sctp_nxt_addr) {
3115 laddr = SCTP_ZONE_GET(SCTP_BASE_INFO(ipi_zone_laddr), struct sctp_laddr);
3116 if (laddr == NULL) {
3117 /*
3118 * Gak, what can we do? This assoc is really
3119 * HOSED. We probably should send an abort
3120 * here.
3121 */
3122 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_PCB1, "Association hosed in TCP model, out of laddr memory\n");
3123 continue;
3124 }
3125 SCTP_INCR_LADDR_COUNT();
3126 memset(laddr, 0, sizeof(*laddr));
3127 (void)SCTP_GETTIME_TIMEVAL(&laddr->start_time);
3128 laddr->ifa = oladdr->ifa;
3129 atomic_add_int(&laddr->ifa->refcount, 1);
3130 LIST_INSERT_HEAD(&new_inp->sctp_addr_list, laddr,
3131 sctp_nxt_addr);
3132 new_inp->laddr_count++;
3133 if (oladdr == stcb->asoc.last_used_address) {
3134 stcb->asoc.last_used_address = laddr;
3135 }
3136 }
3137 }
3138 /* Now any running timers need to be adjusted. */
3139 if (stcb->asoc.dack_timer.ep == old_inp) {
3140 SCTP_INP_DECR_REF(old_inp);
3141 stcb->asoc.dack_timer.ep = new_inp;
3142 SCTP_INP_INCR_REF(new_inp);
3143 }
3144 if (stcb->asoc.asconf_timer.ep == old_inp) {
3145 SCTP_INP_DECR_REF(old_inp);
3146 stcb->asoc.asconf_timer.ep = new_inp;
3147 SCTP_INP_INCR_REF(new_inp);
3148 }
3149 if (stcb->asoc.strreset_timer.ep == old_inp) {
3150 SCTP_INP_DECR_REF(old_inp);
3151 stcb->asoc.strreset_timer.ep = new_inp;
3152 SCTP_INP_INCR_REF(new_inp);
3153 }
3154 if (stcb->asoc.shut_guard_timer.ep == old_inp) {
3155 SCTP_INP_DECR_REF(old_inp);
3156 stcb->asoc.shut_guard_timer.ep = new_inp;
3157 SCTP_INP_INCR_REF(new_inp);
3158 }
3159 if (stcb->asoc.autoclose_timer.ep == old_inp) {
3160 SCTP_INP_DECR_REF(old_inp);
3161 stcb->asoc.autoclose_timer.ep = new_inp;
3162 SCTP_INP_INCR_REF(new_inp);
3163 }
3164 if (stcb->asoc.delete_prim_timer.ep == old_inp) {
3165 SCTP_INP_DECR_REF(old_inp);
3166 stcb->asoc.delete_prim_timer.ep = new_inp;
3167 SCTP_INP_INCR_REF(new_inp);
3168 }
3169 /* now what about the nets? */
3170 TAILQ_FOREACH(net, &stcb->asoc.nets, sctp_next) {
3171 if (net->pmtu_timer.ep == old_inp) {
3172 SCTP_INP_DECR_REF(old_inp);
3173 net->pmtu_timer.ep = new_inp;
3174 SCTP_INP_INCR_REF(new_inp);
3175 }
3176 if (net->hb_timer.ep == old_inp) {
3177 SCTP_INP_DECR_REF(old_inp);
3178 net->hb_timer.ep = new_inp;
3179 SCTP_INP_INCR_REF(new_inp);
3180 }
3181 if (net->rxt_timer.ep == old_inp) {
3182 SCTP_INP_DECR_REF(old_inp);
3183 net->rxt_timer.ep = new_inp;
3184 SCTP_INP_INCR_REF(new_inp);
3185 }
3186 }
3187 SCTP_INP_WUNLOCK(new_inp);
3188 SCTP_INP_WUNLOCK(old_inp);
3189}
3190
3191/*
3192 * insert an laddr entry with the given ifa for the desired list
3193 */
3194static int
3195sctp_insert_laddr(struct sctpladdr *list, struct sctp_ifa *ifa, uint32_t act)
3196{
3197 struct sctp_laddr *laddr;
3198
3199 laddr = SCTP_ZONE_GET(SCTP_BASE_INFO(ipi_zone_laddr), struct sctp_laddr);
3200 if (laddr == NULL) {
3201 /* out of memory? */
3202 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(NULL, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_PCB, EINVAL);
3203 return (EINVAL);
3204 }
3205 SCTP_INCR_LADDR_COUNT();
3206 memset(laddr, 0, sizeof(*laddr));
3207 (void)SCTP_GETTIME_TIMEVAL(&laddr->start_time);
3208 laddr->ifa = ifa;
3209 laddr->action = act;
3210 atomic_add_int(&ifa->refcount, 1);
3211 /* insert it */
3212 LIST_INSERT_HEAD(list, laddr, sctp_nxt_addr);
3213
3214 return (0);
3215}
3216
3217/*
3218 * Remove an laddr entry from the local address list (on an assoc)
3219 */
3220static void
3221sctp_remove_laddr(struct sctp_laddr *laddr)
3222{
3223
3224 /* remove from the list */
3225 LIST_REMOVE(laddr, sctp_nxt_addr);
3226 sctp_free_ifa(laddr->ifa);
3227 SCTP_ZONE_FREE(SCTP_BASE_INFO(ipi_zone_laddr), laddr);
3228 SCTP_DECR_LADDR_COUNT();
3229}
3230#if !(defined(__FreeBSD__) || defined(__APPLE__) || defined(__Userspace__))
3231
3232/*
3233 * Don't know why, but without this there is an unknown reference when
3234 * compiling NetBSD... hmm
3235 */
3236extern void in6_sin6_2_sin(struct sockaddr_in *, struct sockaddr_in6 *sin6);
3237#endif
3238
3239/* sctp_ifap is used to bypass normal local address validation checks */
3240int
3241#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
3242sctp_inpcb_bind(struct socket *so, struct sockaddr *addr,
3243 struct sctp_ifa *sctp_ifap, struct thread *p)
3244#elif defined(_WIN32) && !defined(__Userspace__)
3245sctp_inpcb_bind(struct socket *so, struct sockaddr *addr,
3246 struct sctp_ifa *sctp_ifap, PKTHREAD p)
3247#else
3248sctp_inpcb_bind(struct socket *so, struct sockaddr *addr,
3249 struct sctp_ifa *sctp_ifap, struct proc *p)
3250#endif
3251{
3252 /* bind a ep to a socket address */
3253 struct sctppcbhead *head;
3254 struct sctp_inpcb *inp, *inp_tmp;
3255#if (defined(__FreeBSD__) || defined(__APPLE__)) && !defined(__Userspace__)
3256 struct inpcb *ip_inp;
3257#endif
3258 int port_reuse_active = 0;
3259 int bindall;
3260#ifdef SCTP_MVRF
3261 int i;
3262#endif
3263 uint16_t lport;
3264 int error;
3265 uint32_t vrf_id;
3266
3267 lport = 0;
3268 bindall = 1;
3269 inp = (struct sctp_inpcb *)so->so_pcb;
3270#if (defined(__FreeBSD__) || defined(__APPLE__)) && !defined(__Userspace__)
3271 ip_inp = (struct inpcb *)so->so_pcb;
3272#endif
3273#ifdef SCTP_DEBUG
3274 if (addr) {
3275 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_PCB1, "Bind called port: %d\n",
3276 ntohs(((struct sockaddr_in *)addr)->sin_port));
3277 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_PCB1, "Addr: ");
3278 SCTPDBG_ADDR(SCTP_DEBUG_PCB1, addr);
3279 }
3280#endif
3281 if ((inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_UNBOUND) == 0) {
3282 /* already did a bind, subsequent binds NOT allowed ! */
3283 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_PCB, EINVAL);
3284 return (EINVAL);
3285 }
3286#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
3287#ifdef INVARIANTS
3288 if (p == NULL)
3289 panic("null proc/thread");
3290#endif
3291#endif
3292 if (addr != NULL) {
3293 switch (addr->sa_family) {
3294#ifdef INET
3295 case AF_INET:
3296 {
3297 struct sockaddr_in *sin;
3298
3299 /* IPV6_V6ONLY socket? */
3300 if (SCTP_IPV6_V6ONLY(inp)) {
3301 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_PCB, EINVAL);
3302 return (EINVAL);
3303 }
3304#ifdef HAVE_SA_LEN
3305 if (addr->sa_len != sizeof(*sin)) {
3306 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_PCB, EINVAL);
3307 return (EINVAL);
3308 }
3309#endif
3310
3311 sin = (struct sockaddr_in *)addr;
3312 lport = sin->sin_port;
3313#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
3314 /*
3315 * For LOOPBACK the prison_local_ip4() call will transmute the ip address
3316 * to the proper value.
3317 */
3318 if (p && (error = prison_local_ip4(p->td_ucred, &sin->sin_addr)) != 0) {
3319 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_PCB, error);
3320 return (error);
3321 }
3322#endif
3323 if (sin->sin_addr.s_addr != INADDR_ANY) {
3324 bindall = 0;
3325 }
3326 break;
3327 }
3328#endif
3329#ifdef INET6
3330 case AF_INET6:
3331 {
3332 /* Only for pure IPv6 Address. (No IPv4 Mapped!) */
3333 struct sockaddr_in6 *sin6;
3334
3335 sin6 = (struct sockaddr_in6 *)addr;
3336
3337#ifdef HAVE_SA_LEN
3338 if (addr->sa_len != sizeof(*sin6)) {
3339 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_PCB, EINVAL);
3340 return (EINVAL);
3341 }
3342#endif
3343 lport = sin6->sin6_port;
3344#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
3345 /*
3346 * For LOOPBACK the prison_local_ip6() call will transmute the ipv6 address
3347 * to the proper value.
3348 */
3349 if (p && (error = prison_local_ip6(p->td_ucred, &sin6->sin6_addr,
3350 (SCTP_IPV6_V6ONLY(inp) != 0))) != 0) {
3351 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_PCB, error);
3352 return (error);
3353 }
3354#endif
3355 if (!IN6_IS_ADDR_UNSPECIFIED(&sin6->sin6_addr)) {
3356 bindall = 0;
3357#ifdef SCTP_EMBEDDED_V6_SCOPE
3358 /* KAME hack: embed scopeid */
3359#if defined(SCTP_KAME)
3360 if (sa6_embedscope(sin6, MODULE_GLOBAL(ip6_use_defzone)) != 0) {
3361 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_PCB, EINVAL);
3362 return (EINVAL);
3363 }
3364#elif defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
3365#if defined(APPLE_LEOPARD) || defined(APPLE_SNOWLEOPARD)
3366 if (in6_embedscope(&sin6->sin6_addr, sin6, ip_inp, NULL) != 0) {
3367#else
3368 if (in6_embedscope(&sin6->sin6_addr, sin6, ip_inp, NULL, NULL) != 0) {
3369#endif
3370 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_PCB, EINVAL);
3371 return (EINVAL);
3372 }
3373#elif defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
3374 error = scope6_check_id(sin6, MODULE_GLOBAL(ip6_use_defzone));
3375 if (error != 0) {
3376 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_PCB, error);
3377 return (error);
3378 }
3379#else
3380 if (in6_embedscope(&sin6->sin6_addr, sin6) != 0) {
3381 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_PCB, EINVAL);
3382 return (EINVAL);
3383 }
3384#endif
3385#endif /* SCTP_EMBEDDED_V6_SCOPE */
3386 }
3387#ifndef SCOPEDROUTING
3388 /* this must be cleared for ifa_ifwithaddr() */
3389 sin6->sin6_scope_id = 0;
3390#endif /* SCOPEDROUTING */
3391 break;
3392 }
3393#endif
3394#if defined(__Userspace__)
3395 case AF_CONN:
3396 {
3397 struct sockaddr_conn *sconn;
3398
3399#ifdef HAVE_SA_LEN
3400 if (addr->sa_len != sizeof(struct sockaddr_conn)) {
3401 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_PCB, EINVAL);
3402 return (EINVAL);
3403 }
3404#endif
3405 sconn = (struct sockaddr_conn *)addr;
3406 lport = sconn->sconn_port;
3407 if (sconn->sconn_addr != NULL) {
3408 bindall = 0;
3409 }
3410 break;
3411 }
3412#endif
3413 default:
3414 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_PCB, EAFNOSUPPORT);
3415 return (EAFNOSUPPORT);
3416 }
3417 }
3418 SCTP_INP_INFO_WLOCK();
3419 SCTP_INP_WLOCK(inp);
3420 /* Setup a vrf_id to be the default for the non-bind-all case. */
3421 vrf_id = inp->def_vrf_id;
3422
3423 /* increase our count due to the unlock we do */
3424 SCTP_INP_INCR_REF(inp);
3425 if (lport) {
3426 /*
3427 * Did the caller specify a port? if so we must see if an ep
3428 * already has this one bound.
3429 */
3430 /* got to be root to get at low ports */
3431#if !(defined(_WIN32) && !defined(__Userspace__))
3432 if (ntohs(lport) < IPPORT_RESERVED) {
3433 if ((p != NULL) && ((error =
3434#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
3435 priv_check(p, PRIV_NETINET_RESERVEDPORT)
3436#elif defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
3437 suser(p->p_ucred, &p->p_acflag)
3438#elif defined(__Userspace__) /* must be true to use raw socket */
3439 1
3440#else
3441 suser(p, 0)
3442#endif
3443 ) != 0)) {
3444 SCTP_INP_DECR_REF(inp);
3445 SCTP_INP_WUNLOCK(inp);
3446 SCTP_INP_INFO_WUNLOCK();
3447 return (error);
3448 }
3449 }
3450#endif
3451 SCTP_INP_WUNLOCK(inp);
3452 if (bindall) {
3453#ifdef SCTP_MVRF
3454 for (i = 0; i < inp->num_vrfs; i++) {
3455 vrf_id = inp->m_vrf_ids[i];
3456#else
3457 vrf_id = inp->def_vrf_id;
3458#endif
3459 inp_tmp = sctp_pcb_findep(addr, 0, 1, vrf_id);
3460 if (inp_tmp != NULL) {
3461 /*
3462 * lock guy returned and lower count
3463 * note that we are not bound so
3464 * inp_tmp should NEVER be inp. And
3465 * it is this inp (inp_tmp) that gets
3466 * the reference bump, so we must
3467 * lower it.
3468 */
3469 SCTP_INP_DECR_REF(inp_tmp);
3470 /* unlock info */
3471 if ((sctp_is_feature_on(inp, SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_PORTREUSE)) &&
3472 (sctp_is_feature_on(inp_tmp, SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_PORTREUSE))) {
3473 /* Ok, must be one-2-one and allowing port re-use */
3474 port_reuse_active = 1;
3475 goto continue_anyway;
3476 }
3477 SCTP_INP_DECR_REF(inp);
3478 SCTP_INP_INFO_WUNLOCK();
3479 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_PCB, EADDRINUSE);
3480 return (EADDRINUSE);
3481 }
3482#ifdef SCTP_MVRF
3483 }
3484#endif
3485 } else {
3486 inp_tmp = sctp_pcb_findep(addr, 0, 1, vrf_id);
3487 if (inp_tmp != NULL) {
3488 /*
3489 * lock guy returned and lower count note
3490 * that we are not bound so inp_tmp should
3491 * NEVER be inp. And it is this inp (inp_tmp)
3492 * that gets the reference bump, so we must
3493 * lower it.
3494 */
3495 SCTP_INP_DECR_REF(inp_tmp);
3496 /* unlock info */
3497 if ((sctp_is_feature_on(inp, SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_PORTREUSE)) &&
3498 (sctp_is_feature_on(inp_tmp, SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_PORTREUSE))) {
3499 /* Ok, must be one-2-one and allowing port re-use */
3500 port_reuse_active = 1;
3501 goto continue_anyway;
3502 }
3503 SCTP_INP_DECR_REF(inp);
3504 SCTP_INP_INFO_WUNLOCK();
3505 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_PCB, EADDRINUSE);
3506 return (EADDRINUSE);
3507 }
3508 }
3509 continue_anyway:
3510 SCTP_INP_WLOCK(inp);
3511 if (bindall) {
3512 /* verify that no lport is not used by a singleton */
3513 if ((port_reuse_active == 0) &&
3514 (inp_tmp = sctp_isport_inuse(inp, lport, vrf_id))) {
3515 /* Sorry someone already has this one bound */
3516 if ((sctp_is_feature_on(inp, SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_PORTREUSE)) &&
3517 (sctp_is_feature_on(inp_tmp, SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_PORTREUSE))) {
3518 port_reuse_active = 1;
3519 } else {
3520 SCTP_INP_DECR_REF(inp);
3521 SCTP_INP_WUNLOCK(inp);
3522 SCTP_INP_INFO_WUNLOCK();
3523 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_PCB, EADDRINUSE);
3524 return (EADDRINUSE);
3525 }
3526 }
3527 }
3528 } else {
3529 uint16_t first, last, candidate;
3530 uint16_t count;
3531 int done;
3532
3533#if defined(_WIN32) && !defined(__Userspace__)
3534 first = 1;
3535 last = 0xffff;
3536#else
3537#if defined(__Userspace__)
3538 /* TODO ensure uid is 0, etc... */
3539#elif (defined(__FreeBSD__) || defined(__APPLE__)) && !defined(__Userspace__)
3540 if (ip_inp->inp_flags & INP_HIGHPORT) {
3541 first = MODULE_GLOBAL(ipport_hifirstauto);
3542 last = MODULE_GLOBAL(ipport_hilastauto);
3543 } else if (ip_inp->inp_flags & INP_LOWPORT) {
3544 if (p && (error =
3545#if defined(__FreeBSD__)
3546 priv_check(p, PRIV_NETINET_RESERVEDPORT)
3547#elif defined(__APPLE__)
3548 suser(p->p_ucred, &p->p_acflag)
3549#else
3550 suser(p, 0)
3551#endif
3552 )) {
3553 SCTP_INP_DECR_REF(inp);
3554 SCTP_INP_WUNLOCK(inp);
3555 SCTP_INP_INFO_WUNLOCK();
3556 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_PCB, error);
3557 return (error);
3558 }
3559 first = MODULE_GLOBAL(ipport_lowfirstauto);
3560 last = MODULE_GLOBAL(ipport_lowlastauto);
3561 } else {
3562#endif
3563 first = MODULE_GLOBAL(ipport_firstauto);
3564 last = MODULE_GLOBAL(ipport_lastauto);
3565#if (defined(__FreeBSD__) || defined(__APPLE__)) && !defined(__Userspace__)
3566 }
3567#endif
3568#endif
3569 if (first > last) {
3570 uint16_t temp;
3571
3572 temp = first;
3573 first = last;
3574 last = temp;
3575 }
3576 count = last - first + 1; /* number of candidates */
3577 candidate = first + sctp_select_initial_TSN(&inp->sctp_ep) % (count);
3578
3579 done = 0;
3580 while (!done) {
3581#ifdef SCTP_MVRF
3582 for (i = 0; i < inp->num_vrfs; i++) {
3583 if (sctp_isport_inuse(inp, htons(candidate), inp->m_vrf_ids[i]) != NULL) {
3584 break;
3585 }
3586 }
3587 if (i == inp->num_vrfs) {
3588 done = 1;
3589 }
3590#else
3591 if (sctp_isport_inuse(inp, htons(candidate), inp->def_vrf_id) == NULL) {
3592 done = 1;
3593 }
3594#endif
3595 if (!done) {
3596 if (--count == 0) {
3597 SCTP_INP_DECR_REF(inp);
3598 SCTP_INP_WUNLOCK(inp);
3599 SCTP_INP_INFO_WUNLOCK();
3600 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_PCB, EADDRINUSE);
3601 return (EADDRINUSE);
3602 }
3603 if (candidate == last)
3604 candidate = first;
3605 else
3606 candidate = candidate + 1;
3607 }
3608 }
3609 lport = htons(candidate);
3610 }
3611 SCTP_INP_DECR_REF(inp);
3612 if (inp->sctp_flags & (SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_SOCKET_GONE |
3613 SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_SOCKET_ALLGONE)) {
3614 /*
3615 * this really should not happen. The guy did a non-blocking
3616 * bind and then did a close at the same time.
3617 */
3618 SCTP_INP_WUNLOCK(inp);
3619 SCTP_INP_INFO_WUNLOCK();
3620 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_PCB, EINVAL);
3621 return (EINVAL);
3622 }
3623 /* ok we look clear to give out this port, so lets setup the binding */
3624 if (bindall) {
3625 /* binding to all addresses, so just set in the proper flags */
3626 inp->sctp_flags |= SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_BOUNDALL;
3627 /* set the automatic addr changes from kernel flag */
3628 if (SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_auto_asconf) == 0) {
3629 sctp_feature_off(inp, SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_DO_ASCONF);
3630 sctp_feature_off(inp, SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_AUTO_ASCONF);
3631 } else {
3632 sctp_feature_on(inp, SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_DO_ASCONF);
3633 sctp_feature_on(inp, SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_AUTO_ASCONF);
3634 }
3635 if (SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_multiple_asconfs) == 0) {
3636 sctp_feature_off(inp, SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_MULTIPLE_ASCONFS);
3637 } else {
3638 sctp_feature_on(inp, SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_MULTIPLE_ASCONFS);
3639 }
3640 /* set the automatic mobility_base from kernel
3641 flag (by micchie)
3642 */
3643 if (SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_mobility_base) == 0) {
3644 sctp_mobility_feature_off(inp, SCTP_MOBILITY_BASE);
3645 sctp_mobility_feature_off(inp, SCTP_MOBILITY_PRIM_DELETED);
3646 } else {
3647 sctp_mobility_feature_on(inp, SCTP_MOBILITY_BASE);
3648 sctp_mobility_feature_off(inp, SCTP_MOBILITY_PRIM_DELETED);
3649 }
3650 /* set the automatic mobility_fasthandoff from kernel
3651 flag (by micchie)
3652 */
3653 if (SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_mobility_fasthandoff) == 0) {
3654 sctp_mobility_feature_off(inp, SCTP_MOBILITY_FASTHANDOFF);
3655 sctp_mobility_feature_off(inp, SCTP_MOBILITY_PRIM_DELETED);
3656 } else {
3657 sctp_mobility_feature_on(inp, SCTP_MOBILITY_FASTHANDOFF);
3658 sctp_mobility_feature_off(inp, SCTP_MOBILITY_PRIM_DELETED);
3659 }
3660 } else {
3661 /*
3662 * bind specific, make sure flags is off and add a new
3663 * address structure to the sctp_addr_list inside the ep
3664 * structure.
3665 *
3666 * We will need to allocate one and insert it at the head. The
3667 * socketopt call can just insert new addresses in there as
3668 * well. It will also have to do the embed scope kame hack
3669 * too (before adding).
3670 */
3671 struct sctp_ifa *ifa;
3672 union sctp_sockstore store;
3673
3674 memset(&store, 0, sizeof(store));
3675 switch (addr->sa_family) {
3676#ifdef INET
3677 case AF_INET:
3678 memcpy(&store.sin, addr, sizeof(struct sockaddr_in));
3679 store.sin.sin_port = 0;
3680 break;
3681#endif
3682#ifdef INET6
3683 case AF_INET6:
3684 memcpy(&store.sin6, addr, sizeof(struct sockaddr_in6));
3685 store.sin6.sin6_port = 0;
3686 break;
3687#endif
3688#if defined(__Userspace__)
3689 case AF_CONN:
3690 memcpy(&store.sconn, addr, sizeof(struct sockaddr_conn));
3691 store.sconn.sconn_port = 0;
3692 break;
3693#endif
3694 default:
3695 break;
3696 }
3697 /*
3698 * first find the interface with the bound address need to
3699 * zero out the port to find the address! yuck! can't do
3700 * this earlier since need port for sctp_pcb_findep()
3701 */
3702 if (sctp_ifap != NULL) {
3703 ifa = sctp_ifap;
3704 } else {
3705 /* Note for BSD we hit here always other
3706 * O/S's will pass things in via the
3707 * sctp_ifap argument.
3708 */
3709 ifa = sctp_find_ifa_by_addr(&store.sa,
3710 vrf_id, SCTP_ADDR_NOT_LOCKED);
3711 }
3712 if (ifa == NULL) {
3713 /* Can't find an interface with that address */
3714 SCTP_INP_WUNLOCK(inp);
3715 SCTP_INP_INFO_WUNLOCK();
3716 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_PCB, EADDRNOTAVAIL);
3717 return (EADDRNOTAVAIL);
3718 }
3719#ifdef INET6
3720 if (addr->sa_family == AF_INET6) {
3721 /* GAK, more FIXME IFA lock? */
3722 if (ifa->localifa_flags & SCTP_ADDR_IFA_UNUSEABLE) {
3723 /* Can't bind a non-existent addr. */
3724 SCTP_INP_WUNLOCK(inp);
3725 SCTP_INP_INFO_WUNLOCK();
3726 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_PCB, EINVAL);
3727 return (EINVAL);
3728 }
3729 }
3730#endif
3731 /* we're not bound all */
3732 inp->sctp_flags &= ~SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_BOUNDALL;
3733 /* allow bindx() to send ASCONF's for binding changes */
3734 sctp_feature_on(inp, SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_DO_ASCONF);
3735 /* clear automatic addr changes from kernel flag */
3736 sctp_feature_off(inp, SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_AUTO_ASCONF);
3737
3738 /* add this address to the endpoint list */
3739 error = sctp_insert_laddr(&inp->sctp_addr_list, ifa, 0);
3740 if (error != 0) {
3741 SCTP_INP_WUNLOCK(inp);
3742 SCTP_INP_INFO_WUNLOCK();
3743 return (error);
3744 }
3745 inp->laddr_count++;
3746 }
3747 /* find the bucket */
3748 if (port_reuse_active) {
3749 /* Put it into tcp 1-2-1 hash */
3750 head = &SCTP_BASE_INFO(sctp_tcpephash)[SCTP_PCBHASH_ALLADDR(lport, SCTP_BASE_INFO(hashtcpmark))];
3751 inp->sctp_flags |= SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_IN_TCPPOOL;
3752 } else {
3753 head = &SCTP_BASE_INFO(sctp_ephash)[SCTP_PCBHASH_ALLADDR(lport, SCTP_BASE_INFO(hashmark))];
3754 }
3755 /* put it in the bucket */
3756 LIST_INSERT_HEAD(head, inp, sctp_hash);
3757 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_PCB1, "Main hash to bind at head:%p, bound port:%d - in tcp_pool=%d\n",
3758 (void *)head, ntohs(lport), port_reuse_active);
3759 /* set in the port */
3760 inp->sctp_lport = lport;
3761
3762 /* turn off just the unbound flag */
3763 inp->sctp_flags &= ~SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_UNBOUND;
3764 SCTP_INP_WUNLOCK(inp);
3765 SCTP_INP_INFO_WUNLOCK();
3766 return (0);
3767}
3768
3769static void
3770sctp_iterator_inp_being_freed(struct sctp_inpcb *inp)
3771{
3772 struct sctp_iterator *it, *nit;
3773
3774 /*
3775 * We enter with the only the ITERATOR_LOCK in place and a write
3776 * lock on the inp_info stuff.
3777 */
3778 it = sctp_it_ctl.cur_it;
3779#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
3780 if (it && (it->vn != curvnet)) {
3781 /* Its not looking at our VNET */
3782 return;
3783 }
3784#endif
3785 if (it && (it->inp == inp)) {
3786 /*
3787 * This is tricky and we hold the iterator lock,
3788 * but when it returns and gets the lock (when we
3789 * release it) the iterator will try to operate on
3790 * inp. We need to stop that from happening. But
3791 * of course the iterator has a reference on the
3792 * stcb and inp. We can mark it and it will stop.
3793 *
3794 * If its a single iterator situation, we
3795 * set the end iterator flag. Otherwise
3796 * we set the iterator to go to the next inp.
3797 *
3798 */
3799 if (it->iterator_flags & SCTP_ITERATOR_DO_SINGLE_INP) {
3800 sctp_it_ctl.iterator_flags |= SCTP_ITERATOR_STOP_CUR_IT;
3801 } else {
3802 sctp_it_ctl.iterator_flags |= SCTP_ITERATOR_STOP_CUR_INP;
3803 }
3804 }
3805 /* Now go through and remove any single reference to
3806 * our inp that may be still pending on the list
3807 */
3808 SCTP_IPI_ITERATOR_WQ_LOCK();
3809 TAILQ_FOREACH_SAFE(it, &sctp_it_ctl.iteratorhead, sctp_nxt_itr, nit) {
3810#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
3811 if (it->vn != curvnet) {
3812 continue;
3813 }
3814#endif
3815 if (it->inp == inp) {
3816 /* This one points to me is it inp specific? */
3817 if (it->iterator_flags & SCTP_ITERATOR_DO_SINGLE_INP) {
3818 /* Remove and free this one */
3819 TAILQ_REMOVE(&sctp_it_ctl.iteratorhead,
3820 it, sctp_nxt_itr);
3821 if (it->function_atend != NULL) {
3822 (*it->function_atend) (it->pointer, it->val);
3823 }
3824 SCTP_FREE(it, SCTP_M_ITER);
3825 } else {
3826 it->inp = LIST_NEXT(it->inp, sctp_list);
3827 if (it->inp) {
3828 SCTP_INP_INCR_REF(it->inp);
3829 }
3830 }
3831 /* When its put in the refcnt is incremented so decr it */
3832 SCTP_INP_DECR_REF(inp);
3833 }
3834 }
3835 SCTP_IPI_ITERATOR_WQ_UNLOCK();
3836}
3837
3838/* release sctp_inpcb unbind the port */
3839void
3840sctp_inpcb_free(struct sctp_inpcb *inp, int immediate, int from)
3841{
3842 /*
3843 * Here we free a endpoint. We must find it (if it is in the Hash
3844 * table) and remove it from there. Then we must also find it in the
3845 * overall list and remove it from there. After all removals are
3846 * complete then any timer has to be stopped. Then start the actual
3847 * freeing. a) Any local lists. b) Any associations. c) The hash of
3848 * all associations. d) finally the ep itself.
3849 */
3850 struct sctp_tcb *asoc, *nasoc;
3851 struct sctp_laddr *laddr, *nladdr;
3852 struct inpcb *ip_pcb;
3853 struct socket *so;
3854 int being_refed = 0;
3855 struct sctp_queued_to_read *sq, *nsq;
3856#if !defined(__Userspace__)
3857#if !defined(__FreeBSD__)
3858 sctp_rtentry_t *rt;
3859#endif
3860#endif
3861 int cnt;
3862 sctp_sharedkey_t *shared_key, *nshared_key;
3863
3864#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
3865 sctp_lock_assert(SCTP_INP_SO(inp));
3866#endif
3867#ifdef SCTP_LOG_CLOSING
3868 sctp_log_closing(inp, NULL, 0);
3869#endif
3870 SCTP_ITERATOR_LOCK();
3871 /* mark any iterators on the list or being processed */
3872 sctp_iterator_inp_being_freed(inp);
3873 SCTP_ITERATOR_UNLOCK();
3874 so = inp->sctp_socket;
3875 if (inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_SOCKET_ALLGONE) {
3876 /* been here before.. eeks.. get out of here */
3877 SCTP_PRINTF("This conflict in free SHOULD not be happening! from %d, imm %d\n", from, immediate);
3878#ifdef SCTP_LOG_CLOSING
3879 sctp_log_closing(inp, NULL, 1);
3880#endif
3881 return;
3882 }
3883 SCTP_ASOC_CREATE_LOCK(inp);
3884 SCTP_INP_INFO_WLOCK();
3885
3886 SCTP_INP_WLOCK(inp);
3887 if (from == SCTP_CALLED_AFTER_CMPSET_OFCLOSE) {
3888 inp->sctp_flags &= ~SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_CLOSE_IP;
3889 /* socket is gone, so no more wakeups allowed */
3890 inp->sctp_flags |= SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_DONT_WAKE;
3891 inp->sctp_flags &= ~SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_WAKEINPUT;
3892 inp->sctp_flags &= ~SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_WAKEOUTPUT;
3893 }
3894 /* First time through we have the socket lock, after that no more. */
3895 sctp_timer_stop(SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_NEWCOOKIE, inp, NULL, NULL,
3896 SCTP_FROM_SCTP_PCB + SCTP_LOC_1);
3897
3898 if (inp->control) {
3899 sctp_m_freem(inp->control);
3900 inp->control = NULL;
3901 }
3902 if (inp->pkt) {
3903 sctp_m_freem(inp->pkt);
3904 inp->pkt = NULL;
3905 }
3906 ip_pcb = &inp->ip_inp.inp; /* we could just cast the main pointer
3907 * here but I will be nice :> (i.e.
3908 * ip_pcb = ep;) */
3909 if (immediate == SCTP_FREE_SHOULD_USE_GRACEFUL_CLOSE) {
3910 int cnt_in_sd;
3911
3912 cnt_in_sd = 0;
3913 LIST_FOREACH_SAFE(asoc, &inp->sctp_asoc_list, sctp_tcblist, nasoc) {
3914 SCTP_TCB_LOCK(asoc);
3915 if (asoc->asoc.state & SCTP_STATE_ABOUT_TO_BE_FREED) {
3916 /* Skip guys being freed */
3917 cnt_in_sd++;
3918 if (asoc->asoc.state & SCTP_STATE_IN_ACCEPT_QUEUE) {
3919 /*
3920 * Special case - we did not start a kill
3921 * timer on the asoc due to it was not
3922 * closed. So go ahead and start it now.
3923 */
3924 SCTP_CLEAR_SUBSTATE(asoc, SCTP_STATE_IN_ACCEPT_QUEUE);
3925 sctp_timer_start(SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_ASOCKILL, inp, asoc, NULL);
3926 }
3927 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(asoc);
3928 continue;
3929 }
3930 if (((SCTP_GET_STATE(asoc) == SCTP_STATE_COOKIE_WAIT) ||
3931 (SCTP_GET_STATE(asoc) == SCTP_STATE_COOKIE_ECHOED)) &&
3932 (asoc->asoc.total_output_queue_size == 0)) {
3933 /* If we have data in queue, we don't want to just
3934 * free since the app may have done, send()/close
3935 * or connect/send/close. And it wants the data
3936 * to get across first.
3937 */
3938 /* Just abandon things in the front states */
3939 if (sctp_free_assoc(inp, asoc, SCTP_PCBFREE_NOFORCE,
3940 SCTP_FROM_SCTP_PCB + SCTP_LOC_2) == 0) {
3941 cnt_in_sd++;
3942 }
3943 continue;
3944 }
3945 /* Disconnect the socket please */
3946 asoc->sctp_socket = NULL;
3947 SCTP_ADD_SUBSTATE(asoc, SCTP_STATE_CLOSED_SOCKET);
3948 if ((asoc->asoc.size_on_reasm_queue > 0) ||
3949 (asoc->asoc.control_pdapi) ||
3950 (asoc->asoc.size_on_all_streams > 0) ||
3951 (so && (so->so_rcv.sb_cc > 0))) {
3952 /* Left with Data unread */
3953 struct mbuf *op_err;
3954
3955 op_err = sctp_generate_cause(SCTP_CAUSE_USER_INITIATED_ABT, "");
3956 asoc->sctp_ep->last_abort_code = SCTP_FROM_SCTP_PCB + SCTP_LOC_3;
3957 sctp_send_abort_tcb(asoc, op_err, SCTP_SO_LOCKED);
3958 SCTP_STAT_INCR_COUNTER32(sctps_aborted);
3959 if ((SCTP_GET_STATE(asoc) == SCTP_STATE_OPEN) ||
3960 (SCTP_GET_STATE(asoc) == SCTP_STATE_SHUTDOWN_RECEIVED)) {
3961 SCTP_STAT_DECR_GAUGE32(sctps_currestab);
3962 }
3963 if (sctp_free_assoc(inp, asoc,
3964 SCTP_PCBFREE_NOFORCE, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_PCB + SCTP_LOC_4) == 0) {
3965 cnt_in_sd++;
3966 }
3967 continue;
3968 } else if (TAILQ_EMPTY(&asoc->asoc.send_queue) &&
3969 TAILQ_EMPTY(&asoc->asoc.sent_queue) &&
3970 (asoc->asoc.stream_queue_cnt == 0)) {
3971 if ((*asoc->asoc.ss_functions.sctp_ss_is_user_msgs_incomplete)(asoc, &asoc->asoc)) {
3972 goto abort_anyway;
3973 }
3974 if ((SCTP_GET_STATE(asoc) != SCTP_STATE_SHUTDOWN_SENT) &&
3975 (SCTP_GET_STATE(asoc) != SCTP_STATE_SHUTDOWN_ACK_SENT)) {
3976 struct sctp_nets *netp;
3977
3978 /*
3979 * there is nothing queued to send,
3980 * so I send shutdown
3981 */
3982 if ((SCTP_GET_STATE(asoc) == SCTP_STATE_OPEN) ||
3983 (SCTP_GET_STATE(asoc) == SCTP_STATE_SHUTDOWN_RECEIVED)) {
3984 SCTP_STAT_DECR_GAUGE32(sctps_currestab);
3985 }
3986 SCTP_SET_STATE(asoc, SCTP_STATE_SHUTDOWN_SENT);
3987 sctp_stop_timers_for_shutdown(asoc);
3988 if (asoc->asoc.alternate) {
3989 netp = asoc->asoc.alternate;
3990 } else {
3991 netp = asoc->asoc.primary_destination;
3992 }
3993 sctp_send_shutdown(asoc, netp);
3994 sctp_timer_start(SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_SHUTDOWN, asoc->sctp_ep, asoc,
3995 netp);
3996 sctp_timer_start(SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_SHUTDOWNGUARD, asoc->sctp_ep, asoc, NULL);
3997 sctp_chunk_output(inp, asoc, SCTP_OUTPUT_FROM_SHUT_TMR, SCTP_SO_LOCKED);
3998 }
3999 } else {
4000 /* mark into shutdown pending */
4001 SCTP_ADD_SUBSTATE(asoc, SCTP_STATE_SHUTDOWN_PENDING);
4002 sctp_timer_start(SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_SHUTDOWNGUARD, asoc->sctp_ep, asoc, NULL);
4003 if ((*asoc->asoc.ss_functions.sctp_ss_is_user_msgs_incomplete)(asoc, &asoc->asoc)) {
4004 SCTP_ADD_SUBSTATE(asoc, SCTP_STATE_PARTIAL_MSG_LEFT);
4005 }
4006 if (TAILQ_EMPTY(&asoc->asoc.send_queue) &&
4007 TAILQ_EMPTY(&asoc->asoc.sent_queue) &&
4008 (asoc->asoc.state & SCTP_STATE_PARTIAL_MSG_LEFT)) {
4009 struct mbuf *op_err;
4010 abort_anyway:
4011 op_err = sctp_generate_cause(SCTP_CAUSE_USER_INITIATED_ABT, "");
4012 asoc->sctp_ep->last_abort_code = SCTP_FROM_SCTP_PCB + SCTP_LOC_5;
4013 sctp_send_abort_tcb(asoc, op_err, SCTP_SO_LOCKED);
4014 SCTP_STAT_INCR_COUNTER32(sctps_aborted);
4015 if ((SCTP_GET_STATE(asoc) == SCTP_STATE_OPEN) ||
4016 (SCTP_GET_STATE(asoc) == SCTP_STATE_SHUTDOWN_RECEIVED)) {
4017 SCTP_STAT_DECR_GAUGE32(sctps_currestab);
4018 }
4019 if (sctp_free_assoc(inp, asoc,
4020 SCTP_PCBFREE_NOFORCE,
4021 SCTP_FROM_SCTP_PCB + SCTP_LOC_6) == 0) {
4022 cnt_in_sd++;
4023 }
4024 continue;
4025 } else {
4026 sctp_chunk_output(inp, asoc, SCTP_OUTPUT_FROM_CLOSING, SCTP_SO_LOCKED);
4027 }
4028 }
4029 cnt_in_sd++;
4030 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(asoc);
4031 }
4032 /* now is there some left in our SHUTDOWN state? */
4033 if (cnt_in_sd) {
4034#ifdef SCTP_LOG_CLOSING
4035 sctp_log_closing(inp, NULL, 2);
4036#endif
4037 inp->sctp_socket = NULL;
4038 SCTP_INP_WUNLOCK(inp);
4039 SCTP_ASOC_CREATE_UNLOCK(inp);
4040 SCTP_INP_INFO_WUNLOCK();
4041 return;
4042 }
4043 }
4044 inp->sctp_socket = NULL;
4045 if ((inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_UNBOUND) !=
4046 SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_UNBOUND) {
4047 /*
4048 * ok, this guy has been bound. It's port is
4049 * somewhere in the SCTP_BASE_INFO(hash table). Remove
4050 * it!
4051 */
4052 LIST_REMOVE(inp, sctp_hash);
4053 inp->sctp_flags |= SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_UNBOUND;
4054 }
4055
4056 /* If there is a timer running to kill us,
4057 * forget it, since it may have a contest
4058 * on the INP lock.. which would cause us
4059 * to die ...
4060 */
4061 cnt = 0;
4062 LIST_FOREACH_SAFE(asoc, &inp->sctp_asoc_list, sctp_tcblist, nasoc) {
4063 SCTP_TCB_LOCK(asoc);
4064 if (immediate != SCTP_FREE_SHOULD_USE_GRACEFUL_CLOSE) {
4065 /* Disconnect the socket please */
4066 asoc->sctp_socket = NULL;
4067 SCTP_ADD_SUBSTATE(asoc, SCTP_STATE_CLOSED_SOCKET);
4068 }
4069 if (asoc->asoc.state & SCTP_STATE_ABOUT_TO_BE_FREED) {
4070 if (asoc->asoc.state & SCTP_STATE_IN_ACCEPT_QUEUE) {
4071 SCTP_CLEAR_SUBSTATE(asoc, SCTP_STATE_IN_ACCEPT_QUEUE);
4072 sctp_timer_start(SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_ASOCKILL, inp, asoc, NULL);
4073 }
4074 cnt++;
4075 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(asoc);
4076 continue;
4077 }
4078 /* Free associations that are NOT killing us */
4079 if ((SCTP_GET_STATE(asoc) != SCTP_STATE_COOKIE_WAIT) &&
4080 ((asoc->asoc.state & SCTP_STATE_ABOUT_TO_BE_FREED) == 0)) {
4081 struct mbuf *op_err;
4082
4083 op_err = sctp_generate_cause(SCTP_CAUSE_USER_INITIATED_ABT, "");
4084 asoc->sctp_ep->last_abort_code = SCTP_FROM_SCTP_PCB + SCTP_LOC_7;
4085 sctp_send_abort_tcb(asoc, op_err, SCTP_SO_LOCKED);
4086 SCTP_STAT_INCR_COUNTER32(sctps_aborted);
4087 } else if (asoc->asoc.state & SCTP_STATE_ABOUT_TO_BE_FREED) {
4088 cnt++;
4089 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(asoc);
4090 continue;
4091 }
4092 if ((SCTP_GET_STATE(asoc) == SCTP_STATE_OPEN) ||
4093 (SCTP_GET_STATE(asoc) == SCTP_STATE_SHUTDOWN_RECEIVED)) {
4094 SCTP_STAT_DECR_GAUGE32(sctps_currestab);
4095 }
4096 if (sctp_free_assoc(inp, asoc, SCTP_PCBFREE_FORCE,
4097 SCTP_FROM_SCTP_PCB + SCTP_LOC_8) == 0) {
4098 cnt++;
4099 }
4100 }
4101 if (cnt) {
4102 /* Ok we have someone out there that will kill us */
4103#ifdef SCTP_LOG_CLOSING
4104 sctp_log_closing(inp, NULL, 3);
4105#endif
4106 SCTP_INP_WUNLOCK(inp);
4107 SCTP_ASOC_CREATE_UNLOCK(inp);
4108 SCTP_INP_INFO_WUNLOCK();
4109 return;
4110 }
4111 if (SCTP_INP_LOCK_CONTENDED(inp))
4112 being_refed++;
4113 if (SCTP_INP_READ_CONTENDED(inp))
4114 being_refed++;
4115 if (SCTP_ASOC_CREATE_LOCK_CONTENDED(inp))
4116 being_refed++;
4117 /* NOTE: 0 refcount also means no timers are referencing us. */
4118 if ((inp->refcount) ||
4119 (being_refed) ||
4120 (inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_CLOSE_IP)) {
4121#ifdef SCTP_LOG_CLOSING
4122 sctp_log_closing(inp, NULL, 4);
4123#endif
4124 sctp_timer_start(SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_INPKILL, inp, NULL, NULL);
4125 SCTP_INP_WUNLOCK(inp);
4126 SCTP_ASOC_CREATE_UNLOCK(inp);
4127 SCTP_INP_INFO_WUNLOCK();
4128 return;
4129 }
4130 inp->sctp_ep.signature_change.type = 0;
4131 inp->sctp_flags |= SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_SOCKET_ALLGONE;
4132 /* Remove it from the list .. last thing we need a
4133 * lock for.
4134 */
4135 LIST_REMOVE(inp, sctp_list);
4136 SCTP_INP_WUNLOCK(inp);
4137 SCTP_ASOC_CREATE_UNLOCK(inp);
4138 SCTP_INP_INFO_WUNLOCK();
4139
4140#ifdef SCTP_LOG_CLOSING
4141 sctp_log_closing(inp, NULL, 5);
4142#endif
4143#if !(defined(_WIN32) || defined(__Userspace__))
4144#if !(defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__))
4145 rt = ip_pcb->inp_route.ro_rt;
4146#endif
4147#endif
4148 if ((inp->sctp_asocidhash) != NULL) {
4149 SCTP_HASH_FREE(inp->sctp_asocidhash, inp->hashasocidmark);
4150 inp->sctp_asocidhash = NULL;
4151 }
4152 /*sa_ignore FREED_MEMORY*/
4153 TAILQ_FOREACH_SAFE(sq, &inp->read_queue, next, nsq) {
4154 /* Its only abandoned if it had data left */
4155 if (sq->length)
4156 SCTP_STAT_INCR(sctps_left_abandon);
4157
4158 TAILQ_REMOVE(&inp->read_queue, sq, next);
4159 sctp_free_remote_addr(sq->whoFrom);
4160 if (so)
4161 so->so_rcv.sb_cc -= sq->length;
4162 if (sq->data) {
4163 sctp_m_freem(sq->data);
4164 sq->data = NULL;
4165 }
4166 /*
4167 * no need to free the net count, since at this point all
4168 * assoc's are gone.
4169 */
4170 sctp_free_a_readq(NULL, sq);
4171 }
4172 /* Now the sctp_pcb things */
4173 /*
4174 * free each asoc if it is not already closed/free. we can't use the
4175 * macro here since le_next will get freed as part of the
4176 * sctp_free_assoc() call.
4177 */
4178 if (ip_pcb->inp_options) {
4179 (void)sctp_m_free(ip_pcb->inp_options);
4180 ip_pcb->inp_options = 0;
4181 }
4182#if !(defined(_WIN32) || defined(__Userspace__))
4183#if !defined(__FreeBSD__)
4184 if (rt) {
4185 RTFREE(rt);
4186 ip_pcb->inp_route.ro_rt = 0;
4187 }
4188#endif
4189#endif
4190#ifdef INET6
4191#if !(defined(_WIN32) || defined(__Userspace__))
4192#if (defined(__FreeBSD__) || defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__))
4193 if (ip_pcb->inp_vflag & INP_IPV6) {
4194#else
4195 if (inp->inp_vflag & INP_IPV6) {
4196#endif
4197 ip6_freepcbopts(ip_pcb->in6p_outputopts);
4198 }
4199#endif
4200#endif /* INET6 */
4201 ip_pcb->inp_vflag = 0;
4202 /* free up authentication fields */
4203 if (inp->sctp_ep.local_auth_chunks != NULL)
4204 sctp_free_chunklist(inp->sctp_ep.local_auth_chunks);
4205 if (inp->sctp_ep.local_hmacs != NULL)
4206 sctp_free_hmaclist(inp->sctp_ep.local_hmacs);
4207
4208 LIST_FOREACH_SAFE(shared_key, &inp->sctp_ep.shared_keys, next, nshared_key) {
4209 LIST_REMOVE(shared_key, next);
4210 sctp_free_sharedkey(shared_key);
4211 /*sa_ignore FREED_MEMORY*/
4212 }
4213
4214#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
4215 inp->ip_inp.inp.inp_state = INPCB_STATE_DEAD;
4216 if (in_pcb_checkstate(&inp->ip_inp.inp, WNT_STOPUSING, 1) != WNT_STOPUSING) {
4217#ifdef INVARIANTS
4218 panic("sctp_inpcb_free inp = %p couldn't set to STOPUSING\n", (void *)inp);
4219#else
4220 SCTP_PRINTF("sctp_inpcb_free inp = %p couldn't set to STOPUSING\n", (void *)inp);
4221#endif
4222 }
4223 inp->ip_inp.inp.inp_socket->so_flags |= SOF_PCBCLEARING;
4224#endif
4225 /*
4226 * if we have an address list the following will free the list of
4227 * ifaddr's that are set into this ep. Again macro limitations here,
4228 * since the LIST_FOREACH could be a bad idea.
4229 */
4230 LIST_FOREACH_SAFE(laddr, &inp->sctp_addr_list, sctp_nxt_addr, nladdr) {
4231 sctp_remove_laddr(laddr);
4232 }
4233
4234#ifdef SCTP_TRACK_FREED_ASOCS
4235 /* TEMP CODE */
4236 LIST_FOREACH_SAFE(asoc, &inp->sctp_asoc_free_list, sctp_tcblist, nasoc) {
4237 LIST_REMOVE(asoc, sctp_tcblist);
4238 SCTP_ZONE_FREE(SCTP_BASE_INFO(ipi_zone_asoc), asoc);
4239 SCTP_DECR_ASOC_COUNT();
4240 }
4241 /* *** END TEMP CODE ****/
4242#endif
4243#ifdef SCTP_MVRF
4244 SCTP_FREE(inp->m_vrf_ids, SCTP_M_MVRF);
4245#endif
4246 /* Now lets see about freeing the EP hash table. */
4247 if (inp->sctp_tcbhash != NULL) {
4248 SCTP_HASH_FREE(inp->sctp_tcbhash, inp->sctp_hashmark);
4249 inp->sctp_tcbhash = NULL;
4250 }
4251 /* Now we must put the ep memory back into the zone pool */
4252#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
4253 crfree(inp->ip_inp.inp.inp_cred);
4254 INP_LOCK_DESTROY(&inp->ip_inp.inp);
4255#endif
4256 SCTP_INP_LOCK_DESTROY(inp);
4257 SCTP_INP_READ_DESTROY(inp);
4258 SCTP_ASOC_CREATE_LOCK_DESTROY(inp);
4259#if !(defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__))
4260 SCTP_ZONE_FREE(SCTP_BASE_INFO(ipi_zone_ep), inp);
4261 SCTP_DECR_EP_COUNT();
4262#else
4263 /* For Tiger, we will do this later... */
4264#endif
4265}
4266
4267struct sctp_nets *
4268sctp_findnet(struct sctp_tcb *stcb, struct sockaddr *addr)
4269{
4270 struct sctp_nets *net;
4271 /* locate the address */
4272 TAILQ_FOREACH(net, &stcb->asoc.nets, sctp_next) {
4273 if (sctp_cmpaddr(addr, (struct sockaddr *)&net->ro._l_addr))
4274 return (net);
4275 }
4276 return (NULL);
4277}
4278
4279int
4280sctp_is_address_on_local_host(struct sockaddr *addr, uint32_t vrf_id)
4281{
4282 struct sctp_ifa *sctp_ifa;
4283 sctp_ifa = sctp_find_ifa_by_addr(addr, vrf_id, SCTP_ADDR_NOT_LOCKED);
4284 if (sctp_ifa) {
4285 return (1);
4286 } else {
4287 return (0);
4288 }
4289}
4290
4291/*
4292 * add's a remote endpoint address, done with the INIT/INIT-ACK as well as
4293 * when a ASCONF arrives that adds it. It will also initialize all the cwnd
4294 * stats of stuff.
4295 */
4296int
4297sctp_add_remote_addr(struct sctp_tcb *stcb, struct sockaddr *newaddr,
4298 struct sctp_nets **netp, uint16_t port, int set_scope, int from)
4299{
4300 /*
4301 * The following is redundant to the same lines in the
4302 * sctp_aloc_assoc() but is needed since others call the add
4303 * address function
4304 */
4305 struct sctp_nets *net, *netfirst;
4306 int addr_inscope;
4307
4308 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_PCB1, "Adding an address (from:%d) to the peer: ",
4309 from);
4310 SCTPDBG_ADDR(SCTP_DEBUG_PCB1, newaddr);
4311
4312 netfirst = sctp_findnet(stcb, newaddr);
4313 if (netfirst) {
4314 /*
4315 * Lie and return ok, we don't want to make the association
4316 * go away for this behavior. It will happen in the TCP
4317 * model in a connected socket. It does not reach the hash
4318 * table until after the association is built so it can't be
4319 * found. Mark as reachable, since the initial creation will
4320 * have been cleared and the NOT_IN_ASSOC flag will have
4321 * been added... and we don't want to end up removing it
4322 * back out.
4323 */
4324 if (netfirst->dest_state & SCTP_ADDR_UNCONFIRMED) {
4325 netfirst->dest_state = (SCTP_ADDR_REACHABLE |
4326 SCTP_ADDR_UNCONFIRMED);
4327 } else {
4328 netfirst->dest_state = SCTP_ADDR_REACHABLE;
4329 }
4330
4331 return (0);
4332 }
4333 addr_inscope = 1;
4334 switch (newaddr->sa_family) {
4335#ifdef INET
4336 case AF_INET:
4337 {
4338 struct sockaddr_in *sin;
4339
4340 sin = (struct sockaddr_in *)newaddr;
4341 if (sin->sin_addr.s_addr == 0) {
4342 /* Invalid address */
4343 return (-1);
4344 }
4345 /* zero out the zero area */
4346 memset(&sin->sin_zero, 0, sizeof(sin->sin_zero));
4347
4348 /* assure len is set */
4349#ifdef HAVE_SIN_LEN
4350 sin->sin_len = sizeof(struct sockaddr_in);
4351#endif
4352 if (set_scope) {
4353 if (IN4_ISPRIVATE_ADDRESS(&sin->sin_addr)) {
4354 stcb->asoc.scope.ipv4_local_scope = 1;
4355 }
4356 } else {
4357 /* Validate the address is in scope */
4358 if ((IN4_ISPRIVATE_ADDRESS(&sin->sin_addr)) &&
4359 (stcb->asoc.scope.ipv4_local_scope == 0)) {
4360 addr_inscope = 0;
4361 }
4362 }
4363 break;
4364 }
4365#endif
4366#ifdef INET6
4367 case AF_INET6:
4368 {
4369 struct sockaddr_in6 *sin6;
4370
4371 sin6 = (struct sockaddr_in6 *)newaddr;
4372 if (IN6_IS_ADDR_UNSPECIFIED(&sin6->sin6_addr)) {
4373 /* Invalid address */
4374 return (-1);
4375 }
4376 /* assure len is set */
4377#ifdef HAVE_SIN6_LEN
4378 sin6->sin6_len = sizeof(struct sockaddr_in6);
4379#endif
4380 if (set_scope) {
4381 if (sctp_is_address_on_local_host(newaddr, stcb->asoc.vrf_id)) {
4382 stcb->asoc.scope.loopback_scope = 1;
4383 stcb->asoc.scope.local_scope = 0;
4384 stcb->asoc.scope.ipv4_local_scope = 1;
4385 stcb->asoc.scope.site_scope = 1;
4386 } else if (IN6_IS_ADDR_LINKLOCAL(&sin6->sin6_addr)) {
4387 /*
4388 * If the new destination is a LINK_LOCAL we
4389 * must have common site scope. Don't set
4390 * the local scope since we may not share
4391 * all links, only loopback can do this.
4392 * Links on the local network would also be
4393 * on our private network for v4 too.
4394 */
4395 stcb->asoc.scope.ipv4_local_scope = 1;
4396 stcb->asoc.scope.site_scope = 1;
4397 } else if (IN6_IS_ADDR_SITELOCAL(&sin6->sin6_addr)) {
4398 /*
4399 * If the new destination is SITE_LOCAL then
4400 * we must have site scope in common.
4401 */
4402 stcb->asoc.scope.site_scope = 1;
4403 }
4404 } else {
4405 /* Validate the address is in scope */
4406 if (IN6_IS_ADDR_LOOPBACK(&sin6->sin6_addr) &&
4407 (stcb->asoc.scope.loopback_scope == 0)) {
4408 addr_inscope = 0;
4409 } else if (IN6_IS_ADDR_LINKLOCAL(&sin6->sin6_addr) &&
4410 (stcb->asoc.scope.local_scope == 0)) {
4411 addr_inscope = 0;
4412 } else if (IN6_IS_ADDR_SITELOCAL(&sin6->sin6_addr) &&
4413 (stcb->asoc.scope.site_scope == 0)) {
4414 addr_inscope = 0;
4415 }
4416 }
4417 break;
4418 }
4419#endif
4420#if defined(__Userspace__)
4421 case AF_CONN:
4422 {
4423 struct sockaddr_conn *sconn;
4424
4425 sconn = (struct sockaddr_conn *)newaddr;
4426 if (sconn->sconn_addr == NULL) {
4427 /* Invalid address */
4428 return (-1);
4429 }
4430#ifdef HAVE_SCONN_LEN
4431 sconn->sconn_len = sizeof(struct sockaddr_conn);
4432#endif
4433 break;
4434 }
4435#endif
4436 default:
4437 /* not supported family type */
4438 return (-1);
4439 }
4440 net = SCTP_ZONE_GET(SCTP_BASE_INFO(ipi_zone_net), struct sctp_nets);
4441 if (net == NULL) {
4442 return (-1);
4443 }
4444 SCTP_INCR_RADDR_COUNT();
4445 memset(net, 0, sizeof(struct sctp_nets));
4446 (void)SCTP_GETTIME_TIMEVAL(&net->start_time);
4447#ifdef HAVE_SA_LEN
4448 memcpy(&net->ro._l_addr, newaddr, newaddr->sa_len);
4449#endif
4450 switch (newaddr->sa_family) {
4451#ifdef INET
4452 case AF_INET:
4453#ifndef HAVE_SA_LEN
4454 memcpy(&net->ro._l_addr, newaddr, sizeof(struct sockaddr_in));
4455#endif
4456 ((struct sockaddr_in *)&net->ro._l_addr)->sin_port = stcb->rport;
4457 break;
4458#endif
4459#ifdef INET6
4460 case AF_INET6:
4461#ifndef HAVE_SA_LEN
4462 memcpy(&net->ro._l_addr, newaddr, sizeof(struct sockaddr_in6));
4463#endif
4464 ((struct sockaddr_in6 *)&net->ro._l_addr)->sin6_port = stcb->rport;
4465 break;
4466#endif
4467#if defined(__Userspace__)
4468 case AF_CONN:
4469#ifndef HAVE_SA_LEN
4470 memcpy(&net->ro._l_addr, newaddr, sizeof(struct sockaddr_conn));
4471#endif
4472 ((struct sockaddr_conn *)&net->ro._l_addr)->sconn_port = stcb->rport;
4473 break;
4474#endif
4475 default:
4476 break;
4477 }
4478 net->addr_is_local = sctp_is_address_on_local_host(newaddr, stcb->asoc.vrf_id);
4479 if (net->addr_is_local && ((set_scope || (from == SCTP_ADDR_IS_CONFIRMED)))) {
4480 stcb->asoc.scope.loopback_scope = 1;
4481 stcb->asoc.scope.ipv4_local_scope = 1;
4482 stcb->asoc.scope.local_scope = 0;
4483 stcb->asoc.scope.site_scope = 1;
4484 addr_inscope = 1;
4485 }
4486 net->failure_threshold = stcb->asoc.def_net_failure;
4487 net->pf_threshold = stcb->asoc.def_net_pf_threshold;
4488 if (addr_inscope == 0) {
4489 net->dest_state = (SCTP_ADDR_REACHABLE |
4490 SCTP_ADDR_OUT_OF_SCOPE);
4491 } else {
4492 if (from == SCTP_ADDR_IS_CONFIRMED)
4493 /* SCTP_ADDR_IS_CONFIRMED is passed by connect_x */
4494 net->dest_state = SCTP_ADDR_REACHABLE;
4495 else
4496 net->dest_state = SCTP_ADDR_REACHABLE |
4497 SCTP_ADDR_UNCONFIRMED;
4498 }
4499 /* We set this to 0, the timer code knows that
4500 * this means its an initial value
4501 */
4502 net->rto_needed = 1;
4503 net->RTO = 0;
4504 net->RTO_measured = 0;
4505 stcb->asoc.numnets++;
4506 net->ref_count = 1;
4507 net->cwr_window_tsn = net->last_cwr_tsn = stcb->asoc.sending_seq - 1;
4508 net->port = port;
4509 net->dscp = stcb->asoc.default_dscp;
4510#ifdef INET6
4511 net->flowlabel = stcb->asoc.default_flowlabel;
4512#endif
4513 if (sctp_stcb_is_feature_on(stcb->sctp_ep, stcb, SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_DONOT_HEARTBEAT)) {
4514 net->dest_state |= SCTP_ADDR_NOHB;
4515 } else {
4516 net->dest_state &= ~SCTP_ADDR_NOHB;
4517 }
4518 if (sctp_stcb_is_feature_on(stcb->sctp_ep, stcb, SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_DO_NOT_PMTUD)) {
4519 net->dest_state |= SCTP_ADDR_NO_PMTUD;
4520 } else {
4521 net->dest_state &= ~SCTP_ADDR_NO_PMTUD;
4522 }
4523 net->heart_beat_delay = stcb->asoc.heart_beat_delay;
4524 /* Init the timer structure */
4525 SCTP_OS_TIMER_INIT(&net->rxt_timer.timer);
4526 SCTP_OS_TIMER_INIT(&net->pmtu_timer.timer);
4527 SCTP_OS_TIMER_INIT(&net->hb_timer.timer);
4528
4529 /* Now generate a route for this guy */
4530#ifdef INET6
4531#ifdef SCTP_EMBEDDED_V6_SCOPE
4532 /* KAME hack: embed scopeid */
4533 if (newaddr->sa_family == AF_INET6) {
4534 struct sockaddr_in6 *sin6;
4535
4536 sin6 = (struct sockaddr_in6 *)&net->ro._l_addr;
4537#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
4538#if defined(APPLE_LEOPARD) || defined(APPLE_SNOWLEOPARD)
4539 (void)in6_embedscope(&sin6->sin6_addr, sin6, &stcb->sctp_ep->ip_inp.inp, NULL);
4540#else
4541 (void)in6_embedscope(&sin6->sin6_addr, sin6, &stcb->sctp_ep->ip_inp.inp, NULL, NULL);
4542#endif
4543#elif defined(SCTP_KAME)
4544 (void)sa6_embedscope(sin6, MODULE_GLOBAL(ip6_use_defzone));
4545#else
4546 (void)in6_embedscope(&sin6->sin6_addr, sin6);
4547#endif
4548#ifndef SCOPEDROUTING
4549 sin6->sin6_scope_id = 0;
4550#endif
4551 }
4552#endif /* SCTP_EMBEDDED_V6_SCOPE */
4553#endif
4554 SCTP_RTALLOC((sctp_route_t *)&net->ro,
4555 stcb->asoc.vrf_id,
4556 stcb->sctp_ep->fibnum);
4557
4558 net->src_addr_selected = 0;
4559#if !defined(__Userspace__)
4560 if (SCTP_ROUTE_HAS_VALID_IFN(&net->ro)) {
4561 /* Get source address */
4562 net->ro._s_addr = sctp_source_address_selection(stcb->sctp_ep,
4563 stcb,
4564 (sctp_route_t *)&net->ro,
4565 net,
4566 0,
4567 stcb->asoc.vrf_id);
4568 if (stcb->asoc.default_mtu > 0) {
4569 net->mtu = stcb->asoc.default_mtu;
4570 switch (net->ro._l_addr.sa.sa_family) {
4571#ifdef INET
4572 case AF_INET:
4573 net->mtu += SCTP_MIN_V4_OVERHEAD;
4574 break;
4575#endif
4576#ifdef INET6
4577 case AF_INET6:
4578 net->mtu += SCTP_MIN_OVERHEAD;
4579 break;
4580#endif
4581#if defined(__Userspace__)
4582 case AF_CONN:
4583 net->mtu += sizeof(struct sctphdr);
4584 break;
4585#endif
4586 default:
4587 break;
4588 }
4589#if defined(INET) || defined(INET6)
4590 if (net->port) {
4591 net->mtu += (uint32_t)sizeof(struct udphdr);
4592 }
4593#endif
4594 } else if (net->ro._s_addr != NULL) {
4595 uint32_t imtu, rmtu, hcmtu;
4596
4597 net->src_addr_selected = 1;
4598 /* Now get the interface MTU */
4599 if (net->ro._s_addr->ifn_p != NULL) {
4600 imtu = SCTP_GATHER_MTU_FROM_INTFC(net->ro._s_addr->ifn_p);
4601 } else {
4602 imtu = 0;
4603 }
4604#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
4605 rmtu = SCTP_GATHER_MTU_FROM_ROUTE(net->ro._s_addr, &net->ro._l_addr.sa, net->ro.ro_nh);
4606 hcmtu = sctp_hc_get_mtu(&net->ro._l_addr, stcb->sctp_ep->fibnum);
4607#else
4608 rmtu = SCTP_GATHER_MTU_FROM_ROUTE(net->ro._s_addr, &net->ro._l_addr.sa, net->ro.ro_rt);
4609 hcmtu = 0;
4610#endif
4611 net->mtu = sctp_min_mtu(hcmtu, rmtu, imtu);
4612#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
4613#else
4614 if (rmtu == 0) {
4615 /* Start things off to match mtu of interface please. */
4616 SCTP_SET_MTU_OF_ROUTE(&net->ro._l_addr.sa,
4617 net->ro.ro_rt, net->mtu);
4618 }
4619#endif
4620 }
4621 }
4622#endif
4623 if (net->mtu == 0) {
4624 if (stcb->asoc.default_mtu > 0) {
4625 net->mtu = stcb->asoc.default_mtu;
4626 switch (net->ro._l_addr.sa.sa_family) {
4627#ifdef INET
4628 case AF_INET:
4629 net->mtu += SCTP_MIN_V4_OVERHEAD;
4630 break;
4631#endif
4632#ifdef INET6
4633 case AF_INET6:
4634 net->mtu += SCTP_MIN_OVERHEAD;
4635 break;
4636#endif
4637#if defined(__Userspace__)
4638 case AF_CONN:
4639 net->mtu += sizeof(struct sctphdr);
4640 break;
4641#endif
4642 default:
4643 break;
4644 }
4645#if defined(INET) || defined(INET6)
4646 if (net->port) {
4647 net->mtu += (uint32_t)sizeof(struct udphdr);
4648 }
4649#endif
4650 } else {
4651 switch (newaddr->sa_family) {
4652#ifdef INET
4653 case AF_INET:
4654 net->mtu = SCTP_DEFAULT_MTU;
4655 break;
4656#endif
4657#ifdef INET6
4658 case AF_INET6:
4659 net->mtu = 1280;
4660 break;
4661#endif
4662#if defined(__Userspace__)
4663 case AF_CONN:
4664 net->mtu = 1280;
4665 break;
4666#endif
4667 default:
4668 break;
4669 }
4670 }
4671 }
4672#if defined(INET) || defined(INET6)
4673 if (net->port) {
4674 net->mtu -= (uint32_t)sizeof(struct udphdr);
4675 }
4676#endif
4677 if (from == SCTP_ALLOC_ASOC) {
4678 stcb->asoc.smallest_mtu = net->mtu;
4679 }
4680 if (stcb->asoc.smallest_mtu > net->mtu) {
4681 sctp_pathmtu_adjustment(stcb, net->mtu);
4682 }
4683#ifdef INET6
4684#ifdef SCTP_EMBEDDED_V6_SCOPE
4685 if (newaddr->sa_family == AF_INET6) {
4686 struct sockaddr_in6 *sin6;
4687
4688 sin6 = (struct sockaddr_in6 *)&net->ro._l_addr;
4689#ifdef SCTP_KAME
4690 (void)sa6_recoverscope(sin6);
4691#else
4692 (void)in6_recoverscope(sin6, &sin6->sin6_addr, NULL);
4693#endif /* SCTP_KAME */
4694 }
4695#endif /* SCTP_EMBEDDED_V6_SCOPE */
4696#endif
4697
4698 /* JRS - Use the congestion control given in the CC module */
4699 if (stcb->asoc.cc_functions.sctp_set_initial_cc_param != NULL)
4700 (*stcb->asoc.cc_functions.sctp_set_initial_cc_param)(stcb, net);
4701
4702 /*
4703 * CMT: CUC algo - set find_pseudo_cumack to TRUE (1) at beginning
4704 * of assoc (2005/06/27, iyengar@cis.udel.edu)
4705 */
4706 net->find_pseudo_cumack = 1;
4707 net->find_rtx_pseudo_cumack = 1;
4708#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
4709 /* Choose an initial flowid. */
4710 net->flowid = stcb->asoc.my_vtag ^
4711 ntohs(stcb->rport) ^
4712 ntohs(stcb->sctp_ep->sctp_lport);
4713 net->flowtype = M_HASHTYPE_OPAQUE_HASH;
4714#endif
4715 if (netp) {
4716 *netp = net;
4717 }
4718 netfirst = TAILQ_FIRST(&stcb->asoc.nets);
4719#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
4720 if (net->ro.ro_nh == NULL) {
4721#else
4722 if (net->ro.ro_rt == NULL) {
4723#endif
4724 /* Since we have no route put it at the back */
4725 TAILQ_INSERT_TAIL(&stcb->asoc.nets, net, sctp_next);
4726 } else if (netfirst == NULL) {
4727 /* We are the first one in the pool. */
4728 TAILQ_INSERT_HEAD(&stcb->asoc.nets, net, sctp_next);
4729#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
4730 } else if (netfirst->ro.ro_nh == NULL) {
4731#else
4732 } else if (netfirst->ro.ro_rt == NULL) {
4733#endif
4734 /*
4735 * First one has NO route. Place this one ahead of the first
4736 * one.
4737 */
4738 TAILQ_INSERT_HEAD(&stcb->asoc.nets, net, sctp_next);
4739#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
4740 } else if (net->ro.ro_nh->nh_ifp != netfirst->ro.ro_nh->nh_ifp) {
4741#else
4742 } else if (net->ro.ro_rt->rt_ifp != netfirst->ro.ro_rt->rt_ifp) {
4743#endif
4744 /*
4745 * This one has a different interface than the one at the
4746 * top of the list. Place it ahead.
4747 */
4748 TAILQ_INSERT_HEAD(&stcb->asoc.nets, net, sctp_next);
4749 } else {
4750 /*
4751 * Ok we have the same interface as the first one. Move
4752 * forward until we find either a) one with a NULL route...
4753 * insert ahead of that b) one with a different ifp.. insert
4754 * after that. c) end of the list.. insert at the tail.
4755 */
4756 struct sctp_nets *netlook;
4757
4758 do {
4759 netlook = TAILQ_NEXT(netfirst, sctp_next);
4760 if (netlook == NULL) {
4761 /* End of the list */
4762 TAILQ_INSERT_TAIL(&stcb->asoc.nets, net, sctp_next);
4763 break;
4764#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
4765 } else if (netlook->ro.ro_nh == NULL) {
4766#else
4767 } else if (netlook->ro.ro_rt == NULL) {
4768#endif
4769 /* next one has NO route */
4770 TAILQ_INSERT_BEFORE(netfirst, net, sctp_next);
4771 break;
4772#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
4773 } else if (netlook->ro.ro_nh->nh_ifp != net->ro.ro_nh->nh_ifp) {
4774#else
4775 } else if (netlook->ro.ro_rt->rt_ifp != net->ro.ro_rt->rt_ifp) {
4776#endif
4777 TAILQ_INSERT_AFTER(&stcb->asoc.nets, netlook,
4778 net, sctp_next);
4779 break;
4780 }
4781 /* Shift forward */
4782 netfirst = netlook;
4783 } while (netlook != NULL);
4784 }
4785
4786 /* got to have a primary set */
4787 if (stcb->asoc.primary_destination == 0) {
4788 stcb->asoc.primary_destination = net;
4789#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
4790 } else if ((stcb->asoc.primary_destination->ro.ro_nh == NULL) &&
4791 (net->ro.ro_nh) &&
4792#else
4793 } else if ((stcb->asoc.primary_destination->ro.ro_rt == NULL) &&
4794 (net->ro.ro_rt) &&
4795#endif
4796 ((net->dest_state & SCTP_ADDR_UNCONFIRMED) == 0)) {
4797 /* No route to current primary adopt new primary */
4798 stcb->asoc.primary_destination = net;
4799 }
4800 /* Validate primary is first */
4801 net = TAILQ_FIRST(&stcb->asoc.nets);
4802 if ((net != stcb->asoc.primary_destination) &&
4803 (stcb->asoc.primary_destination)) {
4804 /* first one on the list is NOT the primary
4805 * sctp_cmpaddr() is much more efficient if
4806 * the primary is the first on the list, make it
4807 * so.
4808 */
4809 TAILQ_REMOVE(&stcb->asoc.nets,
4810 stcb->asoc.primary_destination, sctp_next);
4811 TAILQ_INSERT_HEAD(&stcb->asoc.nets,
4812 stcb->asoc.primary_destination, sctp_next);
4813 }
4814 return (0);
4815}
4816
4817static uint32_t
4818sctp_aloc_a_assoc_id(struct sctp_inpcb *inp, struct sctp_tcb *stcb)
4819{
4820 uint32_t id;
4821 struct sctpasochead *head;
4822 struct sctp_tcb *lstcb;
4823
4824 try_again:
4825 if (inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_SOCKET_ALLGONE) {
4826 /* TSNH */
4827 return (0);
4828 }
4829 /*
4830 * We don't allow assoc id to be one of SCTP_FUTURE_ASSOC,
4831 * SCTP_CURRENT_ASSOC and SCTP_ALL_ASSOC.
4832 */
4833 if (inp->sctp_associd_counter <= SCTP_ALL_ASSOC) {
4834 inp->sctp_associd_counter = SCTP_ALL_ASSOC + 1;
4835 }
4836 id = inp->sctp_associd_counter;
4837 inp->sctp_associd_counter++;
4838 lstcb = sctp_findasoc_ep_asocid_locked(inp, (sctp_assoc_t)id, 0);
4839 if (lstcb) {
4840 goto try_again;
4841 }
4842 head = &inp->sctp_asocidhash[SCTP_PCBHASH_ASOC(id, inp->hashasocidmark)];
4843 LIST_INSERT_HEAD(head, stcb, sctp_tcbasocidhash);
4844 stcb->asoc.in_asocid_hash = 1;
4845 return (id);
4846}
4847
4848/*
4849 * allocate an association and add it to the endpoint. The caller must be
4850 * careful to add all additional addresses once they are know right away or
4851 * else the assoc will be may experience a blackout scenario.
4852 */
4853struct sctp_tcb *
4854sctp_aloc_assoc(struct sctp_inpcb *inp, struct sockaddr *firstaddr,
4855 int *error, uint32_t override_tag, uint32_t vrf_id,
4856 uint16_t o_streams, uint16_t port,
4857#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
4858 struct thread *p,
4859#elif defined(_WIN32) && !defined(__Userspace__)
4860 PKTHREAD p,
4861#else
4862#if defined(__Userspace__)
4863 /* __Userspace__ NULL proc is going to be passed here. See sctp_lower_sosend */
4864#endif
4865 struct proc *p,
4866#endif
4867 int initialize_auth_params)
4868{
4869 /* note the p argument is only valid in unbound sockets */
4870
4871 struct sctp_tcb *stcb;
4872 struct sctp_association *asoc;
4873 struct sctpasochead *head;
4874 uint16_t rport;
4875 int err;
4876
4877 /*
4878 * Assumption made here: Caller has done a
4879 * sctp_findassociation_ep_addr(ep, addr's); to make sure the
4880 * address does not exist already.
4881 */
4882 if (SCTP_BASE_INFO(ipi_count_asoc) >= SCTP_MAX_NUM_OF_ASOC) {
4883 /* Hit max assoc, sorry no more */
4884 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_PCB, ENOBUFS);
4885 *error = ENOBUFS;
4886 return (NULL);
4887 }
4888 if (firstaddr == NULL) {
4889 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_PCB, EINVAL);
4890 *error = EINVAL;
4891 return (NULL);
4892 }
4893 SCTP_INP_RLOCK(inp);
4894 if ((inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_IN_TCPPOOL) &&
4895 ((sctp_is_feature_off(inp, SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_PORTREUSE)) ||
4896 (inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_CONNECTED))) {
4897 /*
4898 * If its in the TCP pool, its NOT allowed to create an
4899 * association. The parent listener needs to call
4900 * sctp_aloc_assoc.. or the one-2-many socket. If a peeled
4901 * off, or connected one does this.. its an error.
4902 */
4903 SCTP_INP_RUNLOCK(inp);
4904 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_PCB, EINVAL);
4905 *error = EINVAL;
4906 return (NULL);
4907 }
4908 if ((inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_IN_TCPPOOL) ||
4909 (inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_TCPTYPE)) {
4910 if ((inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_WAS_CONNECTED) ||
4911 (inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_WAS_ABORTED)) {
4912 SCTP_INP_RUNLOCK(inp);
4913 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_PCB, EINVAL);
4914 *error = EINVAL;
4915 return (NULL);
4916 }
4917 }
4918 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_PCB3, "Allocate an association for peer:");
4919#ifdef SCTP_DEBUG
4920 if (firstaddr) {
4921 SCTPDBG_ADDR(SCTP_DEBUG_PCB3, firstaddr);
4922 switch (firstaddr->sa_family) {
4923#ifdef INET
4924 case AF_INET:
4925 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_PCB3, "Port:%d\n",
4926 ntohs(((struct sockaddr_in *)firstaddr)->sin_port));
4927 break;
4928#endif
4929#ifdef INET6
4930 case AF_INET6:
4931 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_PCB3, "Port:%d\n",
4932 ntohs(((struct sockaddr_in6 *)firstaddr)->sin6_port));
4933 break;
4934#endif
4935#if defined(__Userspace__)
4936 case AF_CONN:
4937 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_PCB3, "Port:%d\n",
4938 ntohs(((struct sockaddr_conn *)firstaddr)->sconn_port));
4939 break;
4940#endif
4941 default:
4942 break;
4943 }
4944 } else {
4945 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_PCB3,"None\n");
4946 }
4947#endif /* SCTP_DEBUG */
4948 switch (firstaddr->sa_family) {
4949#ifdef INET
4950 case AF_INET:
4951 {
4952 struct sockaddr_in *sin;
4953
4954 sin = (struct sockaddr_in *)firstaddr;
4955 if ((ntohs(sin->sin_port) == 0) ||
4956 (sin->sin_addr.s_addr == INADDR_ANY) ||
4957 (sin->sin_addr.s_addr == INADDR_BROADCAST) ||
4958 IN_MULTICAST(ntohl(sin->sin_addr.s_addr)) ||
4959#if defined(__Userspace__)
4960 (((inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_BOUND_CONN) != 0) ||
4961 (((inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_BOUND_V6) != 0) &&
4962 (SCTP_IPV6_V6ONLY(inp) != 0)))) {
4963#else
4964 (((inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_BOUND_V6) != 0) &&
4965 (SCTP_IPV6_V6ONLY(inp) != 0))) {
4966#endif
4967 /* Invalid address */
4968 SCTP_INP_RUNLOCK(inp);
4969 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_PCB, EINVAL);
4970 *error = EINVAL;
4971 return (NULL);
4972 }
4973 rport = sin->sin_port;
4974 break;
4975 }
4976#endif
4977#ifdef INET6
4978 case AF_INET6:
4979 {
4980 struct sockaddr_in6 *sin6;
4981
4982 sin6 = (struct sockaddr_in6 *)firstaddr;
4983 if ((ntohs(sin6->sin6_port) == 0) ||
4984 IN6_IS_ADDR_UNSPECIFIED(&sin6->sin6_addr) ||
4985 IN6_IS_ADDR_MULTICAST(&sin6->sin6_addr) ||
4986 ((inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_BOUND_V6) == 0)) {
4987 /* Invalid address */
4988 SCTP_INP_RUNLOCK(inp);
4989 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_PCB, EINVAL);
4990 *error = EINVAL;
4991 return (NULL);
4992 }
4993 rport = sin6->sin6_port;
4994 break;
4995 }
4996#endif
4997#if defined(__Userspace__)
4998 case AF_CONN:
4999 {
5000 struct sockaddr_conn *sconn;
5001
5002 sconn = (struct sockaddr_conn *)firstaddr;
5003 if ((ntohs(sconn->sconn_port) == 0) ||
5004 (sconn->sconn_addr == NULL) ||
5005 ((inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_BOUND_CONN) == 0)) {
5006 /* Invalid address */
5007 SCTP_INP_RUNLOCK(inp);
5008 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_PCB, EINVAL);
5009 *error = EINVAL;
5010 return (NULL);
5011 }
5012 rport = sconn->sconn_port;
5013 break;
5014 }
5015#endif
5016 default:
5017 /* not supported family type */
5018 SCTP_INP_RUNLOCK(inp);
5019 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_PCB, EINVAL);
5020 *error = EINVAL;
5021 return (NULL);
5022 }
5023 SCTP_INP_RUNLOCK(inp);
5024 if (inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_UNBOUND) {
5025 /*
5026 * If you have not performed a bind, then we need to do the
5027 * ephemeral bind for you.
5028 */
5029 if ((err = sctp_inpcb_bind(inp->sctp_socket, NULL, NULL, p))) {
5030 /* bind error, probably perm */
5031 *error = err;
5032 return (NULL);
5033 }
5034 }
5035 stcb = SCTP_ZONE_GET(SCTP_BASE_INFO(ipi_zone_asoc), struct sctp_tcb);
5036 if (stcb == NULL) {
5037 /* out of memory? */
5038 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_PCB, ENOMEM);
5039 *error = ENOMEM;
5040 return (NULL);
5041 }
5042 SCTP_INCR_ASOC_COUNT();
5043
5044 memset(stcb, 0, sizeof(*stcb));
5045 asoc = &stcb->asoc;
5046
5047 SCTP_TCB_LOCK_INIT(stcb);
5048 SCTP_TCB_SEND_LOCK_INIT(stcb);
5049 stcb->rport = rport;
5050 /* setup back pointer's */
5051 stcb->sctp_ep = inp;
5052 stcb->sctp_socket = inp->sctp_socket;
5053 if ((err = sctp_init_asoc(inp, stcb, override_tag, vrf_id, o_streams))) {
5054 /* failed */
5055 SCTP_TCB_LOCK_DESTROY(stcb);
5056 SCTP_TCB_SEND_LOCK_DESTROY(stcb);
5057 SCTP_ZONE_FREE(SCTP_BASE_INFO(ipi_zone_asoc), stcb);
5058 SCTP_DECR_ASOC_COUNT();
5059 *error = err;
5060 return (NULL);
5061 }
5062 /* and the port */
5063 SCTP_INP_INFO_WLOCK();
5064 SCTP_INP_WLOCK(inp);
5065 if (inp->sctp_flags & (SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_SOCKET_GONE | SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_SOCKET_ALLGONE)) {
5066 /* inpcb freed while alloc going on */
5067 SCTP_TCB_LOCK_DESTROY(stcb);
5068 SCTP_TCB_SEND_LOCK_DESTROY(stcb);
5069 SCTP_ZONE_FREE(SCTP_BASE_INFO(ipi_zone_asoc), stcb);
5070 SCTP_INP_WUNLOCK(inp);
5071 SCTP_INP_INFO_WUNLOCK();
5072 SCTP_DECR_ASOC_COUNT();
5073 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_PCB, EINVAL);
5074 *error = EINVAL;
5075 return (NULL);
5076 }
5077 SCTP_TCB_LOCK(stcb);
5078
5079 asoc->assoc_id = sctp_aloc_a_assoc_id(inp, stcb);
5080 /* now that my_vtag is set, add it to the hash */
5081 head = &SCTP_BASE_INFO(sctp_asochash)[SCTP_PCBHASH_ASOC(stcb->asoc.my_vtag, SCTP_BASE_INFO(hashasocmark))];
5082 /* put it in the bucket in the vtag hash of assoc's for the system */
5083 LIST_INSERT_HEAD(head, stcb, sctp_asocs);
5084 SCTP_INP_INFO_WUNLOCK();
5085
5086 if (sctp_add_remote_addr(stcb, firstaddr, NULL, port, SCTP_DO_SETSCOPE, SCTP_ALLOC_ASOC)) {
5087 /* failure.. memory error? */
5088 if (asoc->strmout) {
5089 SCTP_FREE(asoc->strmout, SCTP_M_STRMO);
5090 asoc->strmout = NULL;
5091 }
5092 if (asoc->mapping_array) {
5093 SCTP_FREE(asoc->mapping_array, SCTP_M_MAP);
5094 asoc->mapping_array = NULL;
5095 }
5096 if (asoc->nr_mapping_array) {
5097 SCTP_FREE(asoc->nr_mapping_array, SCTP_M_MAP);
5098 asoc->nr_mapping_array = NULL;
5099 }
5100 SCTP_DECR_ASOC_COUNT();
5101 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
5102 SCTP_TCB_LOCK_DESTROY(stcb);
5103 SCTP_TCB_SEND_LOCK_DESTROY(stcb);
5104 LIST_REMOVE(stcb, sctp_tcbasocidhash);
5105 SCTP_ZONE_FREE(SCTP_BASE_INFO(ipi_zone_asoc), stcb);
5106 SCTP_INP_WUNLOCK(inp);
5107 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_PCB, ENOBUFS);
5108 *error = ENOBUFS;
5109 return (NULL);
5110 }
5111 /* Init all the timers */
5112 SCTP_OS_TIMER_INIT(&asoc->dack_timer.timer);
5113 SCTP_OS_TIMER_INIT(&asoc->strreset_timer.timer);
5114 SCTP_OS_TIMER_INIT(&asoc->asconf_timer.timer);
5115 SCTP_OS_TIMER_INIT(&asoc->shut_guard_timer.timer);
5116 SCTP_OS_TIMER_INIT(&asoc->autoclose_timer.timer);
5117 SCTP_OS_TIMER_INIT(&asoc->delete_prim_timer.timer);
5118
5119 LIST_INSERT_HEAD(&inp->sctp_asoc_list, stcb, sctp_tcblist);
5120 /* now file the port under the hash as well */
5121 if (inp->sctp_tcbhash != NULL) {
5122 head = &inp->sctp_tcbhash[SCTP_PCBHASH_ALLADDR(stcb->rport,
5123 inp->sctp_hashmark)];
5124 LIST_INSERT_HEAD(head, stcb, sctp_tcbhash);
5125 }
5126 if (initialize_auth_params == SCTP_INITIALIZE_AUTH_PARAMS) {
5127 sctp_initialize_auth_params(inp, stcb);
5128 }
5129 SCTP_INP_WUNLOCK(inp);
5130 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_PCB1, "Association %p now allocated\n", (void *)stcb);
5131 return (stcb);
5132}
5133
5134void
5135sctp_remove_net(struct sctp_tcb *stcb, struct sctp_nets *net)
5136{
5137 struct sctp_inpcb *inp;
5138 struct sctp_association *asoc;
5139
5140 inp = stcb->sctp_ep;
5141 asoc = &stcb->asoc;
5142 asoc->numnets--;
5143 TAILQ_REMOVE(&asoc->nets, net, sctp_next);
5144 if (net == asoc->primary_destination) {
5145 /* Reset primary */
5146 struct sctp_nets *lnet;
5147
5148 lnet = TAILQ_FIRST(&asoc->nets);
5149 /* Mobility adaptation
5150 Ideally, if deleted destination is the primary, it becomes
5151 a fast retransmission trigger by the subsequent SET PRIMARY.
5152 (by micchie)
5153 */
5154 if (sctp_is_mobility_feature_on(stcb->sctp_ep,
5155 SCTP_MOBILITY_BASE) ||
5156 sctp_is_mobility_feature_on(stcb->sctp_ep,
5157 SCTP_MOBILITY_FASTHANDOFF)) {
5158 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_ASCONF1, "remove_net: primary dst is deleting\n");
5159 if (asoc->deleted_primary != NULL) {
5160 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_ASCONF1, "remove_net: deleted primary may be already stored\n");
5161 goto out;
5162 }
5163 asoc->deleted_primary = net;
5164 atomic_add_int(&net->ref_count, 1);
5165 memset(&net->lastsa, 0, sizeof(net->lastsa));
5166 memset(&net->lastsv, 0, sizeof(net->lastsv));
5167 sctp_mobility_feature_on(stcb->sctp_ep,
5168 SCTP_MOBILITY_PRIM_DELETED);
5169 sctp_timer_start(SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_PRIM_DELETED,
5170 stcb->sctp_ep, stcb, NULL);
5171 }
5172out:
5173 /* Try to find a confirmed primary */
5174 asoc->primary_destination = sctp_find_alternate_net(stcb, lnet, 0);
5175 }
5176 if (net == asoc->last_data_chunk_from) {
5177 /* Reset primary */
5178 asoc->last_data_chunk_from = TAILQ_FIRST(&asoc->nets);
5179 }
5180 if (net == asoc->last_control_chunk_from) {
5181 /* Clear net */
5182 asoc->last_control_chunk_from = NULL;
5183 }
5184 if (net == asoc->last_net_cmt_send_started) {
5185 /* Clear net */
5186 asoc->last_net_cmt_send_started = NULL;
5187 }
5188 if (net == stcb->asoc.alternate) {
5189 sctp_free_remote_addr(stcb->asoc.alternate);
5190 stcb->asoc.alternate = NULL;
5191 }
5192 sctp_timer_stop(SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_PATHMTURAISE, inp, stcb, net,
5193 SCTP_FROM_SCTP_PCB + SCTP_LOC_9);
5194 sctp_timer_stop(SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_HEARTBEAT, inp, stcb, net,
5195 SCTP_FROM_SCTP_PCB + SCTP_LOC_10);
5196 net->dest_state |= SCTP_ADDR_BEING_DELETED;
5197 sctp_free_remote_addr(net);
5198}
5199
5200/*
5201 * remove a remote endpoint address from an association, it will fail if the
5202 * address does not exist.
5203 */
5204int
5205sctp_del_remote_addr(struct sctp_tcb *stcb, struct sockaddr *remaddr)
5206{
5207 /*
5208 * Here we need to remove a remote address. This is quite simple, we
5209 * first find it in the list of address for the association
5210 * (tasoc->asoc.nets) and then if it is there, we do a LIST_REMOVE
5211 * on that item. Note we do not allow it to be removed if there are
5212 * no other addresses.
5213 */
5214 struct sctp_association *asoc;
5215 struct sctp_nets *net, *nnet;
5216
5217 asoc = &stcb->asoc;
5218
5219 /* locate the address */
5220 TAILQ_FOREACH_SAFE(net, &asoc->nets, sctp_next, nnet) {
5221 if (net->ro._l_addr.sa.sa_family != remaddr->sa_family) {
5222 continue;
5223 }
5224 if (sctp_cmpaddr((struct sockaddr *)&net->ro._l_addr,
5225 remaddr)) {
5226 /* we found the guy */
5227 if (asoc->numnets < 2) {
5228 /* Must have at LEAST two remote addresses */
5229 return (-1);
5230 } else {
5231 sctp_remove_net(stcb, net);
5232 return (0);
5233 }
5234 }
5235 }
5236 /* not found. */
5237 return (-2);
5238}
5239
5240void
5241sctp_delete_from_timewait(uint32_t tag, uint16_t lport, uint16_t rport)
5242{
5243 struct sctpvtaghead *chain;
5244 struct sctp_tagblock *twait_block;
5245 int found = 0;
5246 int i;
5247
5248 chain = &SCTP_BASE_INFO(vtag_timewait)[(tag % SCTP_STACK_VTAG_HASH_SIZE)];
5249 LIST_FOREACH(twait_block, chain, sctp_nxt_tagblock) {
5250 for (i = 0; i < SCTP_NUMBER_IN_VTAG_BLOCK; i++) {
5251 if ((twait_block->vtag_block[i].v_tag == tag) &&
5252 (twait_block->vtag_block[i].lport == lport) &&
5253 (twait_block->vtag_block[i].rport == rport)) {
5254 twait_block->vtag_block[i].tv_sec_at_expire = 0;
5255 twait_block->vtag_block[i].v_tag = 0;
5256 twait_block->vtag_block[i].lport = 0;
5257 twait_block->vtag_block[i].rport = 0;
5258 found = 1;
5259 break;
5260 }
5261 }
5262 if (found)
5263 break;
5264 }
5265}
5266
5267int
5268sctp_is_in_timewait(uint32_t tag, uint16_t lport, uint16_t rport)
5269{
5270 struct sctpvtaghead *chain;
5271 struct sctp_tagblock *twait_block;
5272 int found = 0;
5273 int i;
5274
5275 SCTP_INP_INFO_WLOCK();
5276 chain = &SCTP_BASE_INFO(vtag_timewait)[(tag % SCTP_STACK_VTAG_HASH_SIZE)];
5277 LIST_FOREACH(twait_block, chain, sctp_nxt_tagblock) {
5278 for (i = 0; i < SCTP_NUMBER_IN_VTAG_BLOCK; i++) {
5279 if ((twait_block->vtag_block[i].v_tag == tag) &&
5280 (twait_block->vtag_block[i].lport == lport) &&
5281 (twait_block->vtag_block[i].rport == rport)) {
5282 found = 1;
5283 break;
5284 }
5285 }
5286 if (found)
5287 break;
5288 }
5289 SCTP_INP_INFO_WUNLOCK();
5290 return (found);
5291}
5292
5293void
5294sctp_add_vtag_to_timewait(uint32_t tag, uint32_t time, uint16_t lport, uint16_t rport)
5295{
5296 struct sctpvtaghead *chain;
5297 struct sctp_tagblock *twait_block;
5298 struct timeval now;
5299 int set, i;
5300
5301 if (time == 0) {
5302 /* Its disabled */
5303 return;
5304 }
5305 (void)SCTP_GETTIME_TIMEVAL(&now);
5306 chain = &SCTP_BASE_INFO(vtag_timewait)[(tag % SCTP_STACK_VTAG_HASH_SIZE)];
5307 set = 0;
5308 LIST_FOREACH(twait_block, chain, sctp_nxt_tagblock) {
5309 /* Block(s) present, lets find space, and expire on the fly */
5310 for (i = 0; i < SCTP_NUMBER_IN_VTAG_BLOCK; i++) {
5311 if ((twait_block->vtag_block[i].v_tag == 0) &&
5312 !set) {
5313 twait_block->vtag_block[i].tv_sec_at_expire =
5314 now.tv_sec + time;
5315 twait_block->vtag_block[i].v_tag = tag;
5316 twait_block->vtag_block[i].lport = lport;
5317 twait_block->vtag_block[i].rport = rport;
5318 set = 1;
5319 } else if ((twait_block->vtag_block[i].v_tag) &&
5320 ((long)twait_block->vtag_block[i].tv_sec_at_expire < now.tv_sec)) {
5321 /* Audit expires this guy */
5322 twait_block->vtag_block[i].tv_sec_at_expire = 0;
5323 twait_block->vtag_block[i].v_tag = 0;
5324 twait_block->vtag_block[i].lport = 0;
5325 twait_block->vtag_block[i].rport = 0;
5326 if (set == 0) {
5327 /* Reuse it for my new tag */
5328 twait_block->vtag_block[i].tv_sec_at_expire = now.tv_sec + time;
5329 twait_block->vtag_block[i].v_tag = tag;
5330 twait_block->vtag_block[i].lport = lport;
5331 twait_block->vtag_block[i].rport = rport;
5332 set = 1;
5333 }
5334 }
5335 }
5336 if (set) {
5337 /*
5338 * We only do up to the block where we can
5339 * place our tag for audits
5340 */
5341 break;
5342 }
5343 }
5344 /* Need to add a new block to chain */
5345 if (!set) {
5346 SCTP_MALLOC(twait_block, struct sctp_tagblock *,
