5347 sizeof(struct sctp_tagblock), SCTP_M_TIMW);
5348 if (twait_block == NULL) {
5349 return;
5350 }
5351 memset(twait_block, 0, sizeof(struct sctp_tagblock));
5352 LIST_INSERT_HEAD(chain, twait_block, sctp_nxt_tagblock);
5353 twait_block->vtag_block[0].tv_sec_at_expire = now.tv_sec + time;
5354 twait_block->vtag_block[0].v_tag = tag;
5355 twait_block->vtag_block[0].lport = lport;
5356 twait_block->vtag_block[0].rport = rport;
5357 }
5358}
5359
5360void
5361sctp_clean_up_stream(struct sctp_tcb *stcb, struct sctp_readhead *rh)
5362{
5363 struct sctp_tmit_chunk *chk, *nchk;
5364 struct sctp_queued_to_read *control, *ncontrol;
5365
5366 TAILQ_FOREACH_SAFE(control, rh, next_instrm, ncontrol) {
5367 TAILQ_REMOVE(rh, control, next_instrm);
5368 control->on_strm_q = 0;
5369 if (control->on_read_q == 0) {
5370 sctp_free_remote_addr(control->whoFrom);
5371 if (control->data) {
5372 sctp_m_freem(control->data);
5373 control->data = NULL;
5374 }
5375 }
5376 /* Reassembly free? */
5377 TAILQ_FOREACH_SAFE(chk, &control->reasm, sctp_next, nchk) {
5378 TAILQ_REMOVE(&control->reasm, chk, sctp_next);
5379 if (chk->data) {
5380 sctp_m_freem(chk->data);
5381 chk->data = NULL;
5382 }
5383 if (chk->holds_key_ref)
5384 sctp_auth_key_release(stcb, chk->auth_keyid, SCTP_SO_LOCKED);
5385 sctp_free_remote_addr(chk->whoTo);
5386 SCTP_ZONE_FREE(SCTP_BASE_INFO(ipi_zone_chunk), chk);
5387 SCTP_DECR_CHK_COUNT();
5388 /*sa_ignore FREED_MEMORY*/
5389 }
5390 /*
5391 * We don't free the address here
5392 * since all the net's were freed
5393 * above.
5394 */
5395 if (control->on_read_q == 0) {
5396 sctp_free_a_readq(stcb, control);
5397 }
5398 }
5399}
5400
5401/*-
5402 * Free the association after un-hashing the remote port. This
5403 * function ALWAYS returns holding NO LOCK on the stcb. It DOES
5404 * expect that the input to this function IS a locked TCB.
5405 * It will return 0, if it did NOT destroy the association (instead
5406 * it unlocks it. It will return NON-zero if it either destroyed the
5407 * association OR the association is already destroyed.
5408 */
5409int
5410sctp_free_assoc(struct sctp_inpcb *inp, struct sctp_tcb *stcb, int from_inpcbfree, int from_location)
5411{
5412 int i;
5413 struct sctp_association *asoc;
5414 struct sctp_nets *net, *nnet;
5415 struct sctp_laddr *laddr, *naddr;
5416 struct sctp_tmit_chunk *chk, *nchk;
5417 struct sctp_asconf_addr *aparam, *naparam;
5418 struct sctp_asconf_ack *aack, *naack;
5419 struct sctp_stream_reset_list *strrst, *nstrrst;
5420 struct sctp_queued_to_read *sq, *nsq;
5421 struct sctp_stream_queue_pending *sp, *nsp;
5422 sctp_sharedkey_t *shared_key, *nshared_key;
5423 struct socket *so;
5424
5425 /* first, lets purge the entry from the hash table. */
5426#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
5427 sctp_lock_assert(SCTP_INP_SO(inp));
5428#endif
5429
5430#ifdef SCTP_LOG_CLOSING
5431 sctp_log_closing(inp, stcb, 6);
5432#endif
5433 if (stcb->asoc.state == 0) {
5434#ifdef SCTP_LOG_CLOSING
5435 sctp_log_closing(inp, NULL, 7);
5436#endif
5437 /* there is no asoc, really TSNH :-0 */
5438 return (1);
5439 }
5440 SCTP_TCB_SEND_LOCK(stcb);
5441 if (stcb->asoc.alternate) {
5442 sctp_free_remote_addr(stcb->asoc.alternate);
5443 stcb->asoc.alternate = NULL;
5444 }
5445#if !(defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__))
5446 /* TEMP CODE */
5447 if (stcb->freed_from_where == 0) {
5448 /* Only record the first place free happened from */
5449 stcb->freed_from_where = from_location;
5450 }
5451 /* TEMP CODE */
5452#endif
5453
5454 asoc = &stcb->asoc;
5455 if ((inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_SOCKET_ALLGONE) ||
5456 (inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_SOCKET_GONE))
5457 /* nothing around */
5458 so = NULL;
5459 else
5460 so = inp->sctp_socket;
5461
5462 /*
5463 * We used timer based freeing if a reader or writer is in the way.
5464 * So we first check if we are actually being called from a timer,
5465 * if so we abort early if a reader or writer is still in the way.
5466 */
5467 if ((stcb->asoc.state & SCTP_STATE_ABOUT_TO_BE_FREED) &&
5468 (from_inpcbfree == SCTP_NORMAL_PROC)) {
5469 /*
5470 * is it the timer driving us? if so are the reader/writers
5471 * gone?
5472 */
5473 if (stcb->asoc.refcnt) {
5474 /* nope, reader or writer in the way */
5475 sctp_timer_start(SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_ASOCKILL, inp, stcb, NULL);
5476 /* no asoc destroyed */
5477 SCTP_TCB_SEND_UNLOCK(stcb);
5478 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
5479#ifdef SCTP_LOG_CLOSING
5480 sctp_log_closing(inp, stcb, 8);
5481#endif
5482 return (0);
5483 }
5484 }
5485 /* Now clean up any other timers */
5486 sctp_stop_association_timers(stcb, false);
5487 /* Now the read queue needs to be cleaned up (only once) */
5488 if ((stcb->asoc.state & SCTP_STATE_ABOUT_TO_BE_FREED) == 0) {
5489 SCTP_ADD_SUBSTATE(stcb, SCTP_STATE_ABOUT_TO_BE_FREED);
5490 SCTP_INP_READ_LOCK(inp);
5491 TAILQ_FOREACH(sq, &inp->read_queue, next) {
5492 if (sq->stcb == stcb) {
5493 sq->do_not_ref_stcb = 1;
5494 sq->sinfo_cumtsn = stcb->asoc.cumulative_tsn;
5495 /* If there is no end, there never
5496 * will be now.
5497 */
5498 if (sq->end_added == 0) {
5499 /* Held for PD-API clear that. */
5500 sq->pdapi_aborted = 1;
5501 sq->held_length = 0;
5502 if (sctp_stcb_is_feature_on(inp, stcb, SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_PDAPIEVNT) && (so != NULL)) {
5503 /*
5504 * Need to add a PD-API aborted indication.
5505 * Setting the control_pdapi assures that it will
5506 * be added right after this msg.
5507 */
5508 uint32_t strseq;
5509 stcb->asoc.control_pdapi = sq;
5510 strseq = (sq->sinfo_stream << 16) | (sq->mid & 0x0000ffff);
5511 sctp_ulp_notify(SCTP_NOTIFY_PARTIAL_DELVIERY_INDICATION,
5512 stcb,
5513 SCTP_PARTIAL_DELIVERY_ABORTED,
5514 (void *)&strseq,
5515 SCTP_SO_LOCKED);
5516 stcb->asoc.control_pdapi = NULL;
5517 }
5518 }
5519 /* Add an end to wake them */
5520 sq->end_added = 1;
5521 }
5522 }
5523 SCTP_INP_READ_UNLOCK(inp);
5524 if (stcb->block_entry) {
5525 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, stcb, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_PCB, ECONNRESET);
5526 stcb->block_entry->error = ECONNRESET;
5527 stcb->block_entry = NULL;
5528 }
5529 }
5530 if ((stcb->asoc.refcnt) || (stcb->asoc.state & SCTP_STATE_IN_ACCEPT_QUEUE)) {
5531 /* Someone holds a reference OR the socket is unaccepted yet.
5532 */
5533 if ((stcb->asoc.refcnt) ||
5534 (inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_SOCKET_ALLGONE) ||
5535 (inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_SOCKET_GONE)) {
5536 SCTP_CLEAR_SUBSTATE(stcb, SCTP_STATE_IN_ACCEPT_QUEUE);
5537 sctp_timer_start(SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_ASOCKILL, inp, stcb, NULL);
5538 }
5539 SCTP_TCB_SEND_UNLOCK(stcb);
5540 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
5541 if ((inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_SOCKET_ALLGONE) ||
5542 (inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_SOCKET_GONE))
5543 /* nothing around */
5544 so = NULL;
5545 if (so) {
5546 /* Wake any reader/writers */
5547 sctp_sorwakeup(inp, so);
5548 sctp_sowwakeup(inp, so);
5549 }
5550
5551#ifdef SCTP_LOG_CLOSING
5552 sctp_log_closing(inp, stcb, 9);
5553#endif
5554 /* no asoc destroyed */
5555 return (0);
5556 }
5557#ifdef SCTP_LOG_CLOSING
5558 sctp_log_closing(inp, stcb, 10);
5559#endif
5560 /* When I reach here, no others want
5561 * to kill the assoc yet.. and I own
5562 * the lock. Now its possible an abort
5563 * comes in when I do the lock exchange
5564 * below to grab all the locks to do
5565 * the final take out. to prevent this
5566 * we increment the count, which will
5567 * start a timer and blow out above thus
5568 * assuring us that we hold exclusive
5569 * killing of the asoc. Note that
5570 * after getting back the TCB lock
5571 * we will go ahead and increment the
5572 * counter back up and stop any timer
5573 * a passing stranger may have started :-S
5574 */
5575 if (from_inpcbfree == SCTP_NORMAL_PROC) {
5576 atomic_add_int(&stcb->asoc.refcnt, 1);
5577
5578 SCTP_TCB_SEND_UNLOCK(stcb);
5579 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
5580 SCTP_INP_INFO_WLOCK();
5581 SCTP_INP_WLOCK(inp);
5582 SCTP_TCB_LOCK(stcb);
5583 SCTP_TCB_SEND_LOCK(stcb);
5584 }
5585 /* Double check the GONE flag */
5586 if ((inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_SOCKET_ALLGONE) ||
5587 (inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_SOCKET_GONE))
5588 /* nothing around */
5589 so = NULL;
5590
5591 if ((inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_TCPTYPE) ||
5592 (inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_IN_TCPPOOL)) {
5593 /*
5594 * For TCP type we need special handling when we are
5595 * connected. We also include the peel'ed off ones to.
5596 */
5597 if (inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_CONNECTED) {
5598 inp->sctp_flags &= ~SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_CONNECTED;
5599 inp->sctp_flags |= SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_WAS_CONNECTED;
5600 if (so) {
5601 SOCKBUF_LOCK(&so->so_rcv);
5602 so->so_state &= ~(SS_ISCONNECTING |
5603 SS_ISDISCONNECTING |
5604 SS_ISCONFIRMING |
5605 SS_ISCONNECTED);
5606 so->so_state |= SS_ISDISCONNECTED;
5607#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
5608 socantrcvmore(so);
5609#else
5610 socantrcvmore_locked(so);
5611#endif
5612 socantsendmore(so);
5613 sctp_sowwakeup(inp, so);
5614 sctp_sorwakeup(inp, so);
5615 SCTP_SOWAKEUP(so);
5616 }
5617 }
5618 }
5619
5620 /* Make it invalid too, that way if its
5621 * about to run it will abort and return.
5622 */
5623 /* re-increment the lock */
5624 if (from_inpcbfree == SCTP_NORMAL_PROC) {
5625 atomic_add_int(&stcb->asoc.refcnt, -1);
5626 }
5627 if (stcb->asoc.refcnt) {
5628 SCTP_CLEAR_SUBSTATE(stcb, SCTP_STATE_IN_ACCEPT_QUEUE);
5629 sctp_timer_start(SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_ASOCKILL, inp, stcb, NULL);
5630 if (from_inpcbfree == SCTP_NORMAL_PROC) {
5631 SCTP_INP_INFO_WUNLOCK();
5632 SCTP_INP_WUNLOCK(inp);
5633 }
5634 SCTP_TCB_SEND_UNLOCK(stcb);
5635 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
5636 return (0);
5637 }
5638 asoc->state = 0;
5639 if (inp->sctp_tcbhash) {
5640 LIST_REMOVE(stcb, sctp_tcbhash);
5641 }
5642 if (stcb->asoc.in_asocid_hash) {
5643 LIST_REMOVE(stcb, sctp_tcbasocidhash);
5644 }
5645 /* Now lets remove it from the list of ALL associations in the EP */
5646 LIST_REMOVE(stcb, sctp_tcblist);
5647 if (from_inpcbfree == SCTP_NORMAL_PROC) {
5648 SCTP_INP_INCR_REF(inp);
5649 SCTP_INP_WUNLOCK(inp);
5650 }
5651 /* pull from vtag hash */
5652 LIST_REMOVE(stcb, sctp_asocs);
5653 sctp_add_vtag_to_timewait(asoc->my_vtag, SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_vtag_time_wait),
5654 inp->sctp_lport, stcb->rport);
5655
5656 /* Now restop the timers to be sure
5657 * this is paranoia at is finest!
5658 */
5659 sctp_stop_association_timers(stcb, true);
5660
5661 /*
5662 * The chunk lists and such SHOULD be empty but we check them just
5663 * in case.
5664 */
5665 /* anything on the wheel needs to be removed */
5666 for (i = 0; i < asoc->streamoutcnt; i++) {
5667 struct sctp_stream_out *outs;
5668
5669 outs = &asoc->strmout[i];
5670 /* now clean up any chunks here */
5671 TAILQ_FOREACH_SAFE(sp, &outs->outqueue, next, nsp) {
5672 atomic_subtract_int(&asoc->stream_queue_cnt, 1);
5673 TAILQ_REMOVE(&outs->outqueue, sp, next);
5674 stcb->asoc.ss_functions.sctp_ss_remove_from_stream(stcb, asoc, outs, sp, 1);
5675 sctp_free_spbufspace(stcb, asoc, sp);
5676 if (sp->data) {
5677 if (so) {
5678 /* Still an open socket - report */
5679 sctp_ulp_notify(SCTP_NOTIFY_SPECIAL_SP_FAIL, stcb,
5680 0, (void *)sp, SCTP_SO_LOCKED);
5681 }
5682 if (sp->data) {
5683 sctp_m_freem(sp->data);
5684 sp->data = NULL;
5685 sp->tail_mbuf = NULL;
5686 sp->length = 0;
5687 }
5688 }
5689 if (sp->net) {
5690 sctp_free_remote_addr(sp->net);
5691 sp->net = NULL;
5692 }
5693 sctp_free_a_strmoq(stcb, sp, SCTP_SO_LOCKED);
5694 }
5695 }
5696 /*sa_ignore FREED_MEMORY*/
5697 TAILQ_FOREACH_SAFE(strrst, &asoc->resetHead, next_resp, nstrrst) {
5698 TAILQ_REMOVE(&asoc->resetHead, strrst, next_resp);
5699 SCTP_FREE(strrst, SCTP_M_STRESET);
5700 }
5701 TAILQ_FOREACH_SAFE(sq, &asoc->pending_reply_queue, next, nsq) {
5702 TAILQ_REMOVE(&asoc->pending_reply_queue, sq, next);
5703 if (sq->data) {
5704 sctp_m_freem(sq->data);
5705 sq->data = NULL;
5706 }
5707 sctp_free_remote_addr(sq->whoFrom);
5708 sq->whoFrom = NULL;
5709 sq->stcb = NULL;
5710 /* Free the ctl entry */
5711 sctp_free_a_readq(stcb, sq);
5712 /*sa_ignore FREED_MEMORY*/
5713 }
5714 TAILQ_FOREACH_SAFE(chk, &asoc->free_chunks, sctp_next, nchk) {
5715 TAILQ_REMOVE(&asoc->free_chunks, chk, sctp_next);
5716 if (chk->data) {
5717 sctp_m_freem(chk->data);
5718 chk->data = NULL;
5719 }
5720 if (chk->holds_key_ref)
5721 sctp_auth_key_release(stcb, chk->auth_keyid, SCTP_SO_LOCKED);
5722 SCTP_ZONE_FREE(SCTP_BASE_INFO(ipi_zone_chunk), chk);
5723 SCTP_DECR_CHK_COUNT();
5724 atomic_subtract_int(&SCTP_BASE_INFO(ipi_free_chunks), 1);
5725 asoc->free_chunk_cnt--;
5726 /*sa_ignore FREED_MEMORY*/
5727 }
5728 /* pending send queue SHOULD be empty */
5729 TAILQ_FOREACH_SAFE(chk, &asoc->send_queue, sctp_next, nchk) {
5730 if (asoc->strmout[chk->rec.data.sid].chunks_on_queues > 0) {
5731 asoc->strmout[chk->rec.data.sid].chunks_on_queues--;
5732#ifdef INVARIANTS
5733 } else {
5734 panic("No chunks on the queues for sid %u.", chk->rec.data.sid);
5735#endif
5736 }
5737 TAILQ_REMOVE(&asoc->send_queue, chk, sctp_next);
5738 if (chk->data) {
5739 if (so) {
5740 /* Still a socket? */
5741 sctp_ulp_notify(SCTP_NOTIFY_UNSENT_DG_FAIL, stcb,
5742 0, chk, SCTP_SO_LOCKED);
5743 }
5744 if (chk->data) {
5745 sctp_m_freem(chk->data);
5746 chk->data = NULL;
5747 }
5748 }
5749 if (chk->holds_key_ref)
5750 sctp_auth_key_release(stcb, chk->auth_keyid, SCTP_SO_LOCKED);
5751 if (chk->whoTo) {
5752 sctp_free_remote_addr(chk->whoTo);
5753 chk->whoTo = NULL;
5754 }
5755 SCTP_ZONE_FREE(SCTP_BASE_INFO(ipi_zone_chunk), chk);
5756 SCTP_DECR_CHK_COUNT();
5757 /*sa_ignore FREED_MEMORY*/
5758 }
5759 /* sent queue SHOULD be empty */
5760 TAILQ_FOREACH_SAFE(chk, &asoc->sent_queue, sctp_next, nchk) {
5761 if (chk->sent != SCTP_DATAGRAM_NR_ACKED) {
5762 if (asoc->strmout[chk->rec.data.sid].chunks_on_queues > 0) {
5763 asoc->strmout[chk->rec.data.sid].chunks_on_queues--;
5764#ifdef INVARIANTS
5765 } else {
5766 panic("No chunks on the queues for sid %u.", chk->rec.data.sid);
5767#endif
5768 }
5769 }
5770 TAILQ_REMOVE(&asoc->sent_queue, chk, sctp_next);
5771 if (chk->data) {
5772 if (so) {
5773 /* Still a socket? */
5774 sctp_ulp_notify(SCTP_NOTIFY_SENT_DG_FAIL, stcb,
5775 0, chk, SCTP_SO_LOCKED);
5776 }
5777 if (chk->data) {
5778 sctp_m_freem(chk->data);
5779 chk->data = NULL;
5780 }
5781 }
5782 if (chk->holds_key_ref)
5783 sctp_auth_key_release(stcb, chk->auth_keyid, SCTP_SO_LOCKED);
5784 sctp_free_remote_addr(chk->whoTo);
5785 SCTP_ZONE_FREE(SCTP_BASE_INFO(ipi_zone_chunk), chk);
5786 SCTP_DECR_CHK_COUNT();
5787 /*sa_ignore FREED_MEMORY*/
5788 }
5789#ifdef INVARIANTS
5790 for (i = 0; i < stcb->asoc.streamoutcnt; i++) {
5791 if (stcb->asoc.strmout[i].chunks_on_queues > 0) {
5792 panic("%u chunks left for stream %u.", stcb->asoc.strmout[i].chunks_on_queues, i);
5793 }
5794 }
5795#endif
5796 /* control queue MAY not be empty */
5797 TAILQ_FOREACH_SAFE(chk, &asoc->control_send_queue, sctp_next, nchk) {
5798 TAILQ_REMOVE(&asoc->control_send_queue, chk, sctp_next);
5799 if (chk->data) {
5800 sctp_m_freem(chk->data);
5801 chk->data = NULL;
5802 }
5803 if (chk->holds_key_ref)
5804 sctp_auth_key_release(stcb, chk->auth_keyid, SCTP_SO_LOCKED);
5805 sctp_free_remote_addr(chk->whoTo);
5806 SCTP_ZONE_FREE(SCTP_BASE_INFO(ipi_zone_chunk), chk);
5807 SCTP_DECR_CHK_COUNT();
5808 /*sa_ignore FREED_MEMORY*/
5809 }
5810 /* ASCONF queue MAY not be empty */
5811 TAILQ_FOREACH_SAFE(chk, &asoc->asconf_send_queue, sctp_next, nchk) {
5812 TAILQ_REMOVE(&asoc->asconf_send_queue, chk, sctp_next);
5813 if (chk->data) {
5814 sctp_m_freem(chk->data);
5815 chk->data = NULL;
5816 }
5817 if (chk->holds_key_ref)
5818 sctp_auth_key_release(stcb, chk->auth_keyid, SCTP_SO_LOCKED);
5819 sctp_free_remote_addr(chk->whoTo);
5820 SCTP_ZONE_FREE(SCTP_BASE_INFO(ipi_zone_chunk), chk);
5821 SCTP_DECR_CHK_COUNT();
5822 /*sa_ignore FREED_MEMORY*/
5823 }
5824 if (asoc->mapping_array) {
5825 SCTP_FREE(asoc->mapping_array, SCTP_M_MAP);
5826 asoc->mapping_array = NULL;
5827 }
5828 if (asoc->nr_mapping_array) {
5829 SCTP_FREE(asoc->nr_mapping_array, SCTP_M_MAP);
5830 asoc->nr_mapping_array = NULL;
5831 }
5832 /* the stream outs */
5833 if (asoc->strmout) {
5834 SCTP_FREE(asoc->strmout, SCTP_M_STRMO);
5835 asoc->strmout = NULL;
5836 }
5837 asoc->strm_realoutsize = asoc->streamoutcnt = 0;
5838 if (asoc->strmin) {
5839 for (i = 0; i < asoc->streamincnt; i++) {
5840 sctp_clean_up_stream(stcb, &asoc->strmin[i].inqueue);
5841 sctp_clean_up_stream(stcb, &asoc->strmin[i].uno_inqueue);
5842 }
5843 SCTP_FREE(asoc->strmin, SCTP_M_STRMI);
5844 asoc->strmin = NULL;
5845 }
5846 asoc->streamincnt = 0;
5847 TAILQ_FOREACH_SAFE(net, &asoc->nets, sctp_next, nnet) {
5848#ifdef INVARIANTS
5849 if (SCTP_BASE_INFO(ipi_count_raddr) == 0) {
5850 panic("no net's left alloc'ed, or list points to itself");
5851 }
5852#endif
5853 TAILQ_REMOVE(&asoc->nets, net, sctp_next);
5854 sctp_free_remote_addr(net);
5855 }
5856 LIST_FOREACH_SAFE(laddr, &asoc->sctp_restricted_addrs, sctp_nxt_addr, naddr) {
5857 /*sa_ignore FREED_MEMORY*/
5858 sctp_remove_laddr(laddr);
5859 }
5860
5861 /* pending asconf (address) parameters */
5862 TAILQ_FOREACH_SAFE(aparam, &asoc->asconf_queue, next, naparam) {
5863 /*sa_ignore FREED_MEMORY*/
5864 TAILQ_REMOVE(&asoc->asconf_queue, aparam, next);
5865 SCTP_FREE(aparam,SCTP_M_ASC_ADDR);
5866 }
5867 TAILQ_FOREACH_SAFE(aack, &asoc->asconf_ack_sent, next, naack) {
5868 /*sa_ignore FREED_MEMORY*/
5869 TAILQ_REMOVE(&asoc->asconf_ack_sent, aack, next);
5870 if (aack->data != NULL) {
5871 sctp_m_freem(aack->data);
5872 }
5873 SCTP_ZONE_FREE(SCTP_BASE_INFO(ipi_zone_asconf_ack), aack);
5874 }
5875 /* clean up auth stuff */
5876 if (asoc->local_hmacs)
5877 sctp_free_hmaclist(asoc->local_hmacs);
5878 if (asoc->peer_hmacs)
5879 sctp_free_hmaclist(asoc->peer_hmacs);
5880
5881 if (asoc->local_auth_chunks)
5882 sctp_free_chunklist(asoc->local_auth_chunks);
5883 if (asoc->peer_auth_chunks)
5884 sctp_free_chunklist(asoc->peer_auth_chunks);
5885
5886 sctp_free_authinfo(&asoc->authinfo);
5887
5888 LIST_FOREACH_SAFE(shared_key, &asoc->shared_keys, next, nshared_key) {
5889 LIST_REMOVE(shared_key, next);
5890 sctp_free_sharedkey(shared_key);
5891 /*sa_ignore FREED_MEMORY*/
5892 }
5893
5894 /* Insert new items here :> */
5895
5896 /* Get rid of LOCK */
5897 SCTP_TCB_SEND_UNLOCK(stcb);
5898 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
5899 SCTP_TCB_LOCK_DESTROY(stcb);
5900 SCTP_TCB_SEND_LOCK_DESTROY(stcb);
5901 if (from_inpcbfree == SCTP_NORMAL_PROC) {
5902 SCTP_INP_INFO_WUNLOCK();
5903 SCTP_INP_RLOCK(inp);
5904 }
5905#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
5906 /* TEMP CODE */
5907 stcb->freed_from_where = from_location;
5908#endif
5909#ifdef SCTP_TRACK_FREED_ASOCS
5910 if (inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_SOCKET_GONE) {
5911 /* now clean up the tasoc itself */
5912 SCTP_ZONE_FREE(SCTP_BASE_INFO(ipi_zone_asoc), stcb);
5913 SCTP_DECR_ASOC_COUNT();
5914 } else {
5915 LIST_INSERT_HEAD(&inp->sctp_asoc_free_list, stcb, sctp_tcblist);
5916 }
5917#else
5918 SCTP_ZONE_FREE(SCTP_BASE_INFO(ipi_zone_asoc), stcb);
5919 SCTP_DECR_ASOC_COUNT();
5920#endif
5921 if (from_inpcbfree == SCTP_NORMAL_PROC) {
5922 if (inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_SOCKET_GONE) {
5923 /* If its NOT the inp_free calling us AND
5924 * sctp_close as been called, we
5925 * call back...
5926 */
5927 SCTP_INP_RUNLOCK(inp);
5928 /* This will start the kill timer (if we are
5929 * the last one) since we hold an increment yet. But
5930 * this is the only safe way to do this
5931 * since otherwise if the socket closes
5932 * at the same time we are here we might
5933 * collide in the cleanup.
5934 */
5935 sctp_inpcb_free(inp,
5936 SCTP_FREE_SHOULD_USE_GRACEFUL_CLOSE,
5937 SCTP_CALLED_DIRECTLY_NOCMPSET);
5938 SCTP_INP_DECR_REF(inp);
5939 } else {
5940 /* The socket is still open. */
5941 SCTP_INP_DECR_REF(inp);
5942 SCTP_INP_RUNLOCK(inp);
5943 }
5944 }
5945 /* destroyed the asoc */
5946#ifdef SCTP_LOG_CLOSING
5947 sctp_log_closing(inp, NULL, 11);
5948#endif
5949 return (1);
5950}
5951
5952/*
5953 * determine if a destination is "reachable" based upon the addresses bound
5954 * to the current endpoint (e.g. only v4 or v6 currently bound)
5955 */
5956/*
5957 * FIX: if we allow assoc-level bindx(), then this needs to be fixed to use
5958 * assoc level v4/v6 flags, as the assoc *may* not have the same address
5959 * types bound as its endpoint
5960 */
5961int
5962sctp_destination_is_reachable(struct sctp_tcb *stcb, struct sockaddr *destaddr)
5963{
5964 struct sctp_inpcb *inp;
5965 int answer;
5966
5967 /*
5968 * No locks here, the TCB, in all cases is already locked and an
5969 * assoc is up. There is either a INP lock by the caller applied (in
5970 * asconf case when deleting an address) or NOT in the HB case,
5971 * however if HB then the INP increment is up and the INP will not
5972 * be removed (on top of the fact that we have a TCB lock). So we
5973 * only want to read the sctp_flags, which is either bound-all or
5974 * not.. no protection needed since once an assoc is up you can't be
5975 * changing your binding.
5976 */
5977 inp = stcb->sctp_ep;
5978 if (inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_BOUNDALL) {
5979 /* if bound all, destination is not restricted */
5980 /*
5981 * RRS: Question during lock work: Is this correct? If you
5982 * are bound-all you still might need to obey the V4--V6
5983 * flags??? IMO this bound-all stuff needs to be removed!
5984 */
5985 return (1);
5986 }
5987 /* NOTE: all "scope" checks are done when local addresses are added */
5988 switch (destaddr->sa_family) {
5989#ifdef INET6
5990 case AF_INET6:
5991 answer = inp->ip_inp.inp.inp_vflag & INP_IPV6;
5992 break;
5993#endif
5994#ifdef INET
5995 case AF_INET:
5996 answer = inp->ip_inp.inp.inp_vflag & INP_IPV4;
5997 break;
5998#endif
5999#if defined(__Userspace__)
6000 case AF_CONN:
6001 answer = inp->ip_inp.inp.inp_vflag & INP_CONN;
6002 break;
6003#endif
6004 default:
6005 /* invalid family, so it's unreachable */
6006 answer = 0;
6007 break;
6008 }
6009 return (answer);
6010}
6011
6012/*
6013 * update the inp_vflags on an endpoint
6014 */
6015static void
6016sctp_update_ep_vflag(struct sctp_inpcb *inp)
6017{
6018 struct sctp_laddr *laddr;
6019
6020 /* first clear the flag */
6021 inp->ip_inp.inp.inp_vflag = 0;
6022 /* set the flag based on addresses on the ep list */
6023 LIST_FOREACH(laddr, &inp->sctp_addr_list, sctp_nxt_addr) {
6024 if (laddr->ifa == NULL) {
6025 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_PCB1, "%s: NULL ifa\n",
6026 __func__);
6027 continue;
6028 }
6029
6030 if (laddr->ifa->localifa_flags & SCTP_BEING_DELETED) {
6031 continue;
6032 }
6033 switch (laddr->ifa->address.sa.sa_family) {
6034#ifdef INET6
6035 case AF_INET6:
6036 inp->ip_inp.inp.inp_vflag |= INP_IPV6;
6037 break;
6038#endif
6039#ifdef INET
6040 case AF_INET:
6041 inp->ip_inp.inp.inp_vflag |= INP_IPV4;
6042 break;
6043#endif
6044#if defined(__Userspace__)
6045 case AF_CONN:
6046 inp->ip_inp.inp.inp_vflag |= INP_CONN;
6047 break;
6048#endif
6049 default:
6050 break;
6051 }
6052 }
6053}
6054
6055/*
6056 * Add the address to the endpoint local address list There is nothing to be
6057 * done if we are bound to all addresses
6058 */
6059void
6060sctp_add_local_addr_ep(struct sctp_inpcb *inp, struct sctp_ifa *ifa, uint32_t action)
6061{
6062 struct sctp_laddr *laddr;
6063 struct sctp_tcb *stcb;
6064 int fnd, error = 0;
6065
6066 fnd = 0;
6067
6068 if (inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_BOUNDALL) {
6069 /* You are already bound to all. You have it already */
6070 return;
6071 }
6072#ifdef INET6
6073 if (ifa->address.sa.sa_family == AF_INET6) {
6074 if (ifa->localifa_flags & SCTP_ADDR_IFA_UNUSEABLE) {
6075 /* Can't bind a non-useable addr. */
6076 return;
6077 }
6078 }
6079#endif
6080 /* first, is it already present? */
6081 LIST_FOREACH(laddr, &inp->sctp_addr_list, sctp_nxt_addr) {
6082 if (laddr->ifa == ifa) {
6083 fnd = 1;
6084 break;
6085 }
6086 }
6087
6088 if (fnd == 0) {
6089 /* Not in the ep list */
6090 error = sctp_insert_laddr(&inp->sctp_addr_list, ifa, action);
6091 if (error != 0)
6092 return;
6093 inp->laddr_count++;
6094 /* update inp_vflag flags */
6095 switch (ifa->address.sa.sa_family) {
6096#ifdef INET6
6097 case AF_INET6:
6098 inp->ip_inp.inp.inp_vflag |= INP_IPV6;
6099 break;
6100#endif
6101#ifdef INET
6102 case AF_INET:
6103 inp->ip_inp.inp.inp_vflag |= INP_IPV4;
6104 break;
6105#endif
6106#if defined(__Userspace__)
6107 case AF_CONN:
6108 inp->ip_inp.inp.inp_vflag |= INP_CONN;
6109 break;
6110#endif
6111 default:
6112 break;
6113 }
6114 LIST_FOREACH(stcb, &inp->sctp_asoc_list, sctp_tcblist) {
6115 sctp_add_local_addr_restricted(stcb, ifa);
6116 }
6117 }
6118 return;
6119}
6120
6121/*
6122 * select a new (hopefully reachable) destination net (should only be used
6123 * when we deleted an ep addr that is the only usable source address to reach
6124 * the destination net)
6125 */
6126static void
6127sctp_select_primary_destination(struct sctp_tcb *stcb)
6128{
6129 struct sctp_nets *net;
6130
6131 TAILQ_FOREACH(net, &stcb->asoc.nets, sctp_next) {
6132 /* for now, we'll just pick the first reachable one we find */
6133 if (net->dest_state & SCTP_ADDR_UNCONFIRMED)
6134 continue;
6135 if (sctp_destination_is_reachable(stcb,
6136 (struct sockaddr *)&net->ro._l_addr)) {
6137 /* found a reachable destination */
6138 stcb->asoc.primary_destination = net;
6139 }
6140 }
6141 /* I can't there from here! ...we're gonna die shortly... */
6142}
6143
6144/*
6145 * Delete the address from the endpoint local address list. There is nothing
6146 * to be done if we are bound to all addresses
6147 */
6148void
6149sctp_del_local_addr_ep(struct sctp_inpcb *inp, struct sctp_ifa *ifa)
6150{
6151 struct sctp_laddr *laddr;
6152 int fnd;
6153
6154 fnd = 0;
6155 if (inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_BOUNDALL) {
6156 /* You are already bound to all. You have it already */
6157 return;
6158 }
6159 LIST_FOREACH(laddr, &inp->sctp_addr_list, sctp_nxt_addr) {
6160 if (laddr->ifa == ifa) {
6161 fnd = 1;
6162 break;
6163 }
6164 }
6165 if (fnd && (inp->laddr_count < 2)) {
6166 /* can't delete unless there are at LEAST 2 addresses */
6167 return;
6168 }
6169 if (fnd) {
6170 /*
6171 * clean up any use of this address go through our
6172 * associations and clear any last_used_address that match
6173 * this one for each assoc, see if a new primary_destination
6174 * is needed
6175 */
6176 struct sctp_tcb *stcb;
6177
6178 /* clean up "next_addr_touse" */
6179 if (inp->next_addr_touse == laddr)
6180 /* delete this address */
6181 inp->next_addr_touse = NULL;
6182
6183 /* clean up "last_used_address" */
6184 LIST_FOREACH(stcb, &inp->sctp_asoc_list, sctp_tcblist) {
6185 struct sctp_nets *net;
6186
6187 SCTP_TCB_LOCK(stcb);
6188 if (stcb->asoc.last_used_address == laddr)
6189 /* delete this address */
6190 stcb->asoc.last_used_address = NULL;
6191 /* Now spin through all the nets and purge any ref to laddr */
6192 TAILQ_FOREACH(net, &stcb->asoc.nets, sctp_next) {
6193 if (net->ro._s_addr == laddr->ifa) {
6194 /* Yep, purge src address selected */
6195#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
6196 RO_NHFREE(&net->ro);
6197#else
6198 sctp_rtentry_t *rt;
6199
6200 /* delete this address if cached */
6201 rt = net->ro.ro_rt;
6202 if (rt != NULL) {
6203 RTFREE(rt);
6204 net->ro.ro_rt = NULL;
6205 }
6206#endif
6207 sctp_free_ifa(net->ro._s_addr);
6208 net->ro._s_addr = NULL;
6209 net->src_addr_selected = 0;
6210 }
6211 }
6212 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
6213 } /* for each tcb */
6214 /* remove it from the ep list */
6215 sctp_remove_laddr(laddr);
6216 inp->laddr_count--;
6217 /* update inp_vflag flags */
6218 sctp_update_ep_vflag(inp);
6219 }
6220 return;
6221}
6222
6223/*
6224 * Add the address to the TCB local address restricted list.
6225 * This is a "pending" address list (eg. addresses waiting for an
6226 * ASCONF-ACK response) and cannot be used as a valid source address.
6227 */
6228void
6229sctp_add_local_addr_restricted(struct sctp_tcb *stcb, struct sctp_ifa *ifa)
6230{
6231 struct sctp_laddr *laddr;
6232 struct sctpladdr *list;
6233
6234 /*
6235 * Assumes TCB is locked.. and possibly the INP. May need to
6236 * confirm/fix that if we need it and is not the case.
6237 */
6238 list = &stcb->asoc.sctp_restricted_addrs;
6239
6240#ifdef INET6
6241 if (ifa->address.sa.sa_family == AF_INET6) {
6242 if (ifa->localifa_flags & SCTP_ADDR_IFA_UNUSEABLE) {
6243 /* Can't bind a non-existent addr. */
6244 return;
6245 }
6246 }
6247#endif
6248 /* does the address already exist? */
6249 LIST_FOREACH(laddr, list, sctp_nxt_addr) {
6250 if (laddr->ifa == ifa) {
6251 return;
6252 }
6253 }
6254
6255 /* add to the list */
6256 (void)sctp_insert_laddr(list, ifa, 0);
6257 return;
6258}
6259
6260/*
6261 * Remove a local address from the TCB local address restricted list
6262 */
6263void
6264sctp_del_local_addr_restricted(struct sctp_tcb *stcb, struct sctp_ifa *ifa)
6265{
6266 struct sctp_inpcb *inp;
6267 struct sctp_laddr *laddr;
6268
6269 /*
6270 * This is called by asconf work. It is assumed that a) The TCB is
6271 * locked and b) The INP is locked. This is true in as much as I can
6272 * trace through the entry asconf code where I did these locks.
6273 * Again, the ASCONF code is a bit different in that it does lock
6274 * the INP during its work often times. This must be since we don't
6275 * want other proc's looking up things while what they are looking
6276 * up is changing :-D
6277 */
6278
6279 inp = stcb->sctp_ep;
6280 /* if subset bound and don't allow ASCONF's, can't delete last */
6281 if (((inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_BOUNDALL) == 0) &&
6282 sctp_is_feature_off(inp, SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_DO_ASCONF)) {
6283 if (stcb->sctp_ep->laddr_count < 2) {
6284 /* can't delete last address */
6285 return;
6286 }
6287 }
6288 LIST_FOREACH(laddr, &stcb->asoc.sctp_restricted_addrs, sctp_nxt_addr) {
6289 /* remove the address if it exists */
6290 if (laddr->ifa == NULL)
6291 continue;
6292 if (laddr->ifa == ifa) {
6293 sctp_remove_laddr(laddr);
6294 return;
6295 }
6296 }
6297
6298 /* address not found! */
6299 return;
6300}

6302#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
6303/* sysctl */
6304static int sctp_max_number_of_assoc = SCTP_MAX_NUM_OF_ASOC;
6305static int sctp_scale_up_for_address = SCTP_SCALE_FOR_ADDR;
6306#endif

6308#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
6309#if defined(SCTP_MCORE_INPUT) && defined(SMP)
6310struct sctp_mcore_ctrl *sctp_mcore_workers = NULL;
6311int *sctp_cpuarry = NULL;
6312
6313void
6314sctp_queue_to_mcore(struct mbuf *m, int off, int cpu_to_use)
6315{
6316 /* Queue a packet to a processor for the specified core */
6317 struct sctp_mcore_queue *qent;
6318 struct sctp_mcore_ctrl *wkq;
6319 int need_wake = 0;
6320
6321 if (sctp_mcore_workers == NULL) {
6322 /* Something went way bad during setup */
6323 sctp_input_with_port(m, off, 0);
6324 return;
6325 }
6326 SCTP_MALLOC(qent, struct sctp_mcore_queue *,
6327 (sizeof(struct sctp_mcore_queue)),
6328 SCTP_M_MCORE);
6329 if (qent == NULL) {
6330 /* This is trouble */
6331 sctp_input_with_port(m, off, 0);
6332 return;
6333 }
6334 qent->vn = curvnet;
6335 qent->m = m;
6336 qent->off = off;
6337 qent->v6 = 0;
6338 wkq = &sctp_mcore_workers[cpu_to_use];
6339 SCTP_MCORE_QLOCK(wkq);
6340
6341 TAILQ_INSERT_TAIL(&wkq->que, qent, next);
6342 if (wkq->running == 0) {
6343 need_wake = 1;
6344 }
6345 SCTP_MCORE_QUNLOCK(wkq);
6346 if (need_wake) {
6347 wakeup(&wkq->running);
6348 }
6349}
6350
6351static void
6352sctp_mcore_thread(void *arg)
6353{
6354
6355 struct sctp_mcore_ctrl *wkq;
6356 struct sctp_mcore_queue *qent;
6357
6358 wkq = (struct sctp_mcore_ctrl *)arg;
6359 struct mbuf *m;
6360 int off, v6;
6361
6362 /* Wait for first tickle */
6363 SCTP_MCORE_LOCK(wkq);
6364 wkq->running = 0;
6365 msleep(&wkq->running,
6366 &wkq->core_mtx,
6367 0, "wait for pkt", 0);
6368 SCTP_MCORE_UNLOCK(wkq);
6369
6370 /* Bind to our cpu */
6371 thread_lock(curthread);
6372 sched_bind(curthread, wkq->cpuid);
6373 thread_unlock(curthread);
6374
6375 /* Now lets start working */
6376 SCTP_MCORE_LOCK(wkq);
6377 /* Now grab lock and go */
6378 for (;;) {
6379 SCTP_MCORE_QLOCK(wkq);
6380 skip_sleep:
6381 wkq->running = 1;
6382 qent = TAILQ_FIRST(&wkq->que);
6383 if (qent) {
6384 TAILQ_REMOVE(&wkq->que, qent, next);
6385 SCTP_MCORE_QUNLOCK(wkq);
6386 CURVNET_SET(qent->vn);
6387 m = qent->m;
6388 off = qent->off;
6389 v6 = qent->v6;
6390 SCTP_FREE(qent, SCTP_M_MCORE);
6391 if (v6 == 0) {
6392 sctp_input_with_port(m, off, 0);
6393 } else {
6394 SCTP_PRINTF("V6 not yet supported\n");
6395 sctp_m_freem(m);
6396 }
6397 CURVNET_RESTORE();
6398 SCTP_MCORE_QLOCK(wkq);
6399 }
6400 wkq->running = 0;
6401 if (!TAILQ_EMPTY(&wkq->que)) {
6402 goto skip_sleep;
6403 }
6404 SCTP_MCORE_QUNLOCK(wkq);
6405 msleep(&wkq->running,
6406 &wkq->core_mtx,
6407 0, "wait for pkt", 0);
6408 }
6409}
6410
6411static void
6412sctp_startup_mcore_threads(void)
6413{
6414 int i, cpu;
6415
6416 if (mp_ncpus == 1)
6417 return;
6418
6419 if (sctp_mcore_workers != NULL) {
6420 /* Already been here in some previous
6421 * vnet?
6422 */
6423 return;
6424 }
6425 SCTP_MALLOC(sctp_mcore_workers, struct sctp_mcore_ctrl *,
6426 ((mp_maxid+1) * sizeof(struct sctp_mcore_ctrl)),
6427 SCTP_M_MCORE);
6428 if (sctp_mcore_workers == NULL) {
6429 /* TSNH I hope */
6430 return;
6431 }
6432 memset(sctp_mcore_workers, 0 , ((mp_maxid+1) *
6433 sizeof(struct sctp_mcore_ctrl)));
6434 /* Init the structures */
6435 for (i = 0; i<=mp_maxid; i++) {
6436 TAILQ_INIT(&sctp_mcore_workers[i].que);
6437 SCTP_MCORE_LOCK_INIT(&sctp_mcore_workers[i]);
6438 SCTP_MCORE_QLOCK_INIT(&sctp_mcore_workers[i]);
6439 sctp_mcore_workers[i].cpuid = i;
6440 }
6441 if (sctp_cpuarry == NULL) {
6442 SCTP_MALLOC(sctp_cpuarry, int *,
6443 (mp_ncpus * sizeof(int)),
6444 SCTP_M_MCORE);
6445 i = 0;
6446 CPU_FOREACH(cpu) {
6447 sctp_cpuarry[i] = cpu;
6448 i++;
6449 }
6450 }
6451 /* Now start them all */
6452 CPU_FOREACH(cpu) {
6453 (void)kproc_create(sctp_mcore_thread,
6454 (void *)&sctp_mcore_workers[cpu],
6455 &sctp_mcore_workers[cpu].thread_proc,
6456 0,
6457 SCTP_KTHREAD_PAGES,
6458 SCTP_MCORE_NAME);
6459 }
6460}
6461#endif
6462#endif
6463
6464#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
6465#if defined(SCTP_NOT_YET)
6466static struct mbuf *
6467sctp_netisr_hdlr(struct mbuf *m, uintptr_t source)
6468{
6469 struct ip *ip;
6470 struct sctphdr *sh;
6471 int offset;
6472 uint32_t flowid, tag;
6473
6474 /*
6475 * No flow id built by lower layers fix it so we
6476 * create one.
6477 */
6478 ip = mtod(m, struct ip *);
6479 offset = (ip->ip_hl << 2) + sizeof(struct sctphdr);
6480 if (SCTP_BUF_LEN(m) < offset) {
6481 if ((m = m_pullup(m, offset)) == NULL) {
6482 SCTP_STAT_INCR(sctps_hdrops);
6483 return (NULL);
6484 }
6485 ip = mtod(m, struct ip *);
6486 }
6487 sh = (struct sctphdr *)((caddr_t)ip + (ip->ip_hl << 2));
6488 tag = htonl(sh->v_tag);
6489 flowid = tag ^ ntohs(sh->dest_port) ^ ntohs(sh->src_port);
6490 m->m_pkthdr.flowid = flowid;
6491 /* FIX ME */
6492 m->m_flags |= M_FLOWID;
6493 return (m);
6494}

6719
6720/*
6721 * Assumes that the SCTP_BASE_INFO() lock is NOT held.
6722 */
6723void
6724sctp_pcb_finish(void)
6725{
6726 struct sctp_vrflist *vrf_bucket;
6727 struct sctp_vrf *vrf, *nvrf;
6728 struct sctp_ifn *ifn, *nifn;
6729 struct sctp_ifa *ifa, *nifa;
6730 struct sctpvtaghead *chain;
6731 struct sctp_tagblock *twait_block, *prev_twait_block;
6732 struct sctp_laddr *wi, *nwi;
6733 int i;
6734 struct sctp_iterator *it, *nit;
6735
6736 if (SCTP_BASE_VAR(sctp_pcb_initialized) == 0) {
6737 SCTP_PRINTF("%s: race condition on teardown.\n", __func__);
6738 return;
6739 }
6740 SCTP_BASE_VAR(sctp_pcb_initialized) = 0;
6741#if !(defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__))
6742 /* Notify the iterator to exit. */
6743 SCTP_IPI_ITERATOR_WQ_LOCK();
6744 sctp_it_ctl.iterator_flags |= SCTP_ITERATOR_MUST_EXIT;
6745 sctp_wakeup_iterator();
6746 SCTP_IPI_ITERATOR_WQ_UNLOCK();
6747#endif
6748#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
6749#if !defined(APPLE_LEOPARD) && !defined(APPLE_SNOWLEOPARD) && !defined(APPLE_LION) && !defined(APPLE_MOUNTAINLION)
6750 in_pcbinfo_detach(&SCTP_BASE_INFO(sctbinfo));
6751#endif
6752 SCTP_IPI_ITERATOR_WQ_LOCK();
6753 do {
6754 msleep(&sctp_it_ctl.iterator_flags,
6755 sctp_it_ctl.ipi_iterator_wq_mtx,
6756 0, "waiting_for_work", 0);
6757 } while ((sctp_it_ctl.iterator_flags & SCTP_ITERATOR_EXITED) == 0);
6758 thread_deallocate(sctp_it_ctl.thread_proc);
6759 SCTP_IPI_ITERATOR_WQ_UNLOCK();
6760#endif
6761#if defined(_WIN32) && !defined(__Userspace__)
6762 if (sctp_it_ctl.iterator_thread_obj != NULL) {
6763 NTSTATUS status = STATUS_SUCCESS;
6764
6765 KeSetEvent(&sctp_it_ctl.iterator_wakeup[1], IO_NO_INCREMENT, FALSE);
6766 status = KeWaitForSingleObject(sctp_it_ctl.iterator_thread_obj,
6767 Executive,
6768 KernelMode,
6769 FALSE,
6770 NULL);
6771 ObDereferenceObject(sctp_it_ctl.iterator_thread_obj);
6772 }
6773#endif
6774#if defined(__Userspace__)
6775 if (SCTP_BASE_VAR(iterator_thread_started)) {
6776#if defined(_WIN32)
6777 WaitForSingleObject(sctp_it_ctl.thread_proc, INFINITE);
6778 CloseHandle(sctp_it_ctl.thread_proc);
6779 sctp_it_ctl.thread_proc = NULL;
6780#else
6781 pthread_join(sctp_it_ctl.thread_proc, NULL);
6782 sctp_it_ctl.thread_proc = 0;
6783#endif
6784 }
6785#endif
6786#if defined(SCTP_PROCESS_LEVEL_LOCKS)
6787#if defined(_WIN32)
6788 DeleteConditionVariable(&sctp_it_ctl.iterator_wakeup);
6789#else
6790 pthread_cond_destroy(&sctp_it_ctl.iterator_wakeup);
6791 pthread_mutexattr_destroy(&SCTP_BASE_VAR(mtx_attr));
6792#endif
6793#endif
6794 /* In FreeBSD the iterator thread never exits
6795 * but we do clean up.
6796 * The only way FreeBSD reaches here is if we have VRF's
6797 * but we still add the ifdef to make it compile on old versions.
6798 */
6799#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
6800retry:
6801#endif
6802 SCTP_IPI_ITERATOR_WQ_LOCK();
6803#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
6804 /*
6805 * sctp_iterator_worker() might be working on an it entry without
6806 * holding the lock. We won't find it on the list either and
6807 * continue and free/destroy it. While holding the lock, spin, to
6808 * avoid the race condition as sctp_iterator_worker() will have to
6809 * wait to re-acquire the lock.
6810 */
6811 if (sctp_it_ctl.iterator_running != 0 || sctp_it_ctl.cur_it != NULL) {
6812 SCTP_IPI_ITERATOR_WQ_UNLOCK();
6813 SCTP_PRINTF("%s: Iterator running while we held the lock. Retry. "
6814 "cur_it=%p\n", __func__, sctp_it_ctl.cur_it);
6815 DELAY(10);
6816 goto retry;
6817 }
6818#endif
6819 TAILQ_FOREACH_SAFE(it, &sctp_it_ctl.iteratorhead, sctp_nxt_itr, nit) {
6820#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
6821 if (it->vn != curvnet) {
6822 continue;
6823 }
6824#endif
6825 TAILQ_REMOVE(&sctp_it_ctl.iteratorhead, it, sctp_nxt_itr);
6826 if (it->function_atend != NULL) {
6827 (*it->function_atend) (it->pointer, it->val);
6828 }
6829 SCTP_FREE(it,SCTP_M_ITER);
6830 }
6831 SCTP_IPI_ITERATOR_WQ_UNLOCK();
6832#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
6833 SCTP_ITERATOR_LOCK();
6834 if ((sctp_it_ctl.cur_it) &&
6835 (sctp_it_ctl.cur_it->vn == curvnet)) {
6836 sctp_it_ctl.iterator_flags |= SCTP_ITERATOR_STOP_CUR_IT;
6837 }
6838 SCTP_ITERATOR_UNLOCK();
6839#endif
6840#if !(defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__))
6841 SCTP_IPI_ITERATOR_WQ_DESTROY();
6842 SCTP_ITERATOR_LOCK_DESTROY();
6843#endif
6844 SCTP_OS_TIMER_STOP_DRAIN(&SCTP_BASE_INFO(addr_wq_timer.timer));
6845 SCTP_WQ_ADDR_LOCK();
6846 LIST_FOREACH_SAFE(wi, &SCTP_BASE_INFO(addr_wq), sctp_nxt_addr, nwi) {
6847 LIST_REMOVE(wi, sctp_nxt_addr);
6848 SCTP_DECR_LADDR_COUNT();
6849 if (wi->action == SCTP_DEL_IP_ADDRESS) {
6850 SCTP_FREE(wi->ifa, SCTP_M_IFA);
6851 }
6852 SCTP_ZONE_FREE(SCTP_BASE_INFO(ipi_zone_laddr), wi);
6853 }
6854 SCTP_WQ_ADDR_UNLOCK();
6855
6856 /*
6857 * free the vrf/ifn/ifa lists and hashes (be sure address monitor
6858 * is destroyed first).
6859 */
6860 SCTP_IPI_ADDR_WLOCK();
6861 vrf_bucket = &SCTP_BASE_INFO(sctp_vrfhash)[(SCTP_DEFAULT_VRFID & SCTP_BASE_INFO(hashvrfmark))];
6862 LIST_FOREACH_SAFE(vrf, vrf_bucket, next_vrf, nvrf) {
6863 LIST_FOREACH_SAFE(ifn, &vrf->ifnlist, next_ifn, nifn) {
6864 LIST_FOREACH_SAFE(ifa, &ifn->ifalist, next_ifa, nifa) {
6865 /* free the ifa */
6866 LIST_REMOVE(ifa, next_bucket);
6867 LIST_REMOVE(ifa, next_ifa);
6868 SCTP_FREE(ifa, SCTP_M_IFA);
6869 }
6870 /* free the ifn */
6871 LIST_REMOVE(ifn, next_bucket);
6872 LIST_REMOVE(ifn, next_ifn);
6873 SCTP_FREE(ifn, SCTP_M_IFN);
6874 }
6875 SCTP_HASH_FREE(vrf->vrf_addr_hash, vrf->vrf_addr_hashmark);
6876 /* free the vrf */
6877 LIST_REMOVE(vrf, next_vrf);
6878 SCTP_FREE(vrf, SCTP_M_VRF);
6879 }
6880 SCTP_IPI_ADDR_WUNLOCK();
6881 /* free the vrf hashes */
6882 SCTP_HASH_FREE(SCTP_BASE_INFO(sctp_vrfhash), SCTP_BASE_INFO(hashvrfmark));
6883 SCTP_HASH_FREE(SCTP_BASE_INFO(vrf_ifn_hash), SCTP_BASE_INFO(vrf_ifn_hashmark));
6884
6885 /* free the TIMEWAIT list elements malloc'd in the function
6886 * sctp_add_vtag_to_timewait()...
6887 */
6888 for (i = 0; i < SCTP_STACK_VTAG_HASH_SIZE; i++) {
6889 chain = &SCTP_BASE_INFO(vtag_timewait)[i];
6890 if (!LIST_EMPTY(chain)) {
6891 prev_twait_block = NULL;
6892 LIST_FOREACH(twait_block, chain, sctp_nxt_tagblock) {
6893 if (prev_twait_block) {
6894 SCTP_FREE(prev_twait_block, SCTP_M_TIMW);
6895 }
6896 prev_twait_block = twait_block;
6897 }
6898 SCTP_FREE(prev_twait_block, SCTP_M_TIMW);
6899 }
6900 }
6901
6902 /* free the locks and mutexes */
6903#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
6904 SCTP_TIMERQ_LOCK_DESTROY();
6905#endif
6906#ifdef SCTP_PACKET_LOGGING
6907 SCTP_IP_PKTLOG_DESTROY();
6908#endif
6909 SCTP_IPI_ADDR_DESTROY();
6910#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
6911 SCTP_IPI_COUNT_DESTROY();
6912#endif
6913 SCTP_STATLOG_DESTROY();
6914 SCTP_INP_INFO_LOCK_DESTROY();
6915
6916 SCTP_WQ_ADDR_DESTROY();
6917
6918#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
6919#if defined(APPLE_LEOPARD) || defined(APPLE_SNOWLEOPARD) || defined(APPLE_LION) || defined(APPLE_MOUNTAINLION)
6920 lck_grp_attr_free(SCTP_BASE_INFO(sctbinfo).mtx_grp_attr);
6921 lck_grp_free(SCTP_BASE_INFO(sctbinfo).mtx_grp);
6922 lck_attr_free(SCTP_BASE_INFO(sctbinfo).mtx_attr);
6923#else
6924 lck_grp_attr_free(SCTP_BASE_INFO(sctbinfo).ipi_lock_grp_attr);
6925 lck_grp_free(SCTP_BASE_INFO(sctbinfo).ipi_lock_grp);
6926 lck_attr_free(SCTP_BASE_INFO(sctbinfo).ipi_lock_attr);
6927#endif
6928#endif
6929#if defined(__Userspace__)
6930 SCTP_TIMERQ_LOCK_DESTROY();
6931 SCTP_ZONE_DESTROY(zone_mbuf);
6932 SCTP_ZONE_DESTROY(zone_clust);
6933 SCTP_ZONE_DESTROY(zone_ext_refcnt);
6934#endif
6935 /* Get rid of other stuff too. */
6936 if (SCTP_BASE_INFO(sctp_asochash) != NULL)
6937 SCTP_HASH_FREE(SCTP_BASE_INFO(sctp_asochash), SCTP_BASE_INFO(hashasocmark));
6938 if (SCTP_BASE_INFO(sctp_ephash) != NULL)
6939 SCTP_HASH_FREE(SCTP_BASE_INFO(sctp_ephash), SCTP_BASE_INFO(hashmark));
6940 if (SCTP_BASE_INFO(sctp_tcpephash) != NULL)
6941 SCTP_HASH_FREE(SCTP_BASE_INFO(sctp_tcpephash), SCTP_BASE_INFO(hashtcpmark));
6942
6943#if defined(_WIN32) || defined(__FreeBSD__) || defined(__Userspace__)
6944 SCTP_ZONE_DESTROY(SCTP_BASE_INFO(ipi_zone_ep));
6945 SCTP_ZONE_DESTROY(SCTP_BASE_INFO(ipi_zone_asoc));
6946 SCTP_ZONE_DESTROY(SCTP_BASE_INFO(ipi_zone_laddr));
6947 SCTP_ZONE_DESTROY(SCTP_BASE_INFO(ipi_zone_net));
6948 SCTP_ZONE_DESTROY(SCTP_BASE_INFO(ipi_zone_chunk));
6949 SCTP_ZONE_DESTROY(SCTP_BASE_INFO(ipi_zone_readq));
6950 SCTP_ZONE_DESTROY(SCTP_BASE_INFO(ipi_zone_strmoq));
6951 SCTP_ZONE_DESTROY(SCTP_BASE_INFO(ipi_zone_asconf));
6952 SCTP_ZONE_DESTROY(SCTP_BASE_INFO(ipi_zone_asconf_ack));
6953#endif
6954#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
6955#if defined(SMP) && defined(SCTP_USE_PERCPU_STAT)
6956 SCTP_FREE(SCTP_BASE_STATS, SCTP_M_MCORE);
6957#endif
6958#endif
6959}
6960
6961int
6962sctp_load_addresses_from_init(struct sctp_tcb *stcb, struct mbuf *m,
6963 int offset, int limit,
6964 struct sockaddr *src, struct sockaddr *dst,
6965 struct sockaddr *altsa, uint16_t port)
6966{
6967 /*
6968 * grub through the INIT pulling addresses and loading them to the
6969 * nets structure in the asoc. The from address in the mbuf should
6970 * also be loaded (if it is not already). This routine can be called
6971 * with either INIT or INIT-ACK's as long as the m points to the IP
6972 * packet and the offset points to the beginning of the parameters.
6973 */
6974 struct sctp_inpcb *inp;
6975 struct sctp_nets *net, *nnet, *net_tmp;
6976 struct sctp_paramhdr *phdr, param_buf;
6977 struct sctp_tcb *stcb_tmp;
6978 uint16_t ptype, plen;
6979 struct sockaddr *sa;
6980 uint8_t random_store[SCTP_PARAM_BUFFER_SIZE];
6981 struct sctp_auth_random *p_random = NULL;
6982 uint16_t random_len = 0;
6983 uint8_t hmacs_store[SCTP_PARAM_BUFFER_SIZE];
6984 struct sctp_auth_hmac_algo *hmacs = NULL;
6985 uint16_t hmacs_len = 0;
6986 uint8_t saw_asconf = 0;
6987 uint8_t saw_asconf_ack = 0;
6988 uint8_t chunks_store[SCTP_PARAM_BUFFER_SIZE];
6989 struct sctp_auth_chunk_list *chunks = NULL;
6990 uint16_t num_chunks = 0;
6991 sctp_key_t *new_key;
6992 uint32_t keylen;
6993 int got_random = 0, got_hmacs = 0, got_chklist = 0;
6994 uint8_t peer_supports_ecn;
6995 uint8_t peer_supports_prsctp;
6996 uint8_t peer_supports_auth;
6997 uint8_t peer_supports_asconf;
6998 uint8_t peer_supports_asconf_ack;
6999 uint8_t peer_supports_reconfig;
7000 uint8_t peer_supports_nrsack;
7001 uint8_t peer_supports_pktdrop;
7002 uint8_t peer_supports_idata;
7003#ifdef INET
7004 struct sockaddr_in sin;
7005#endif
7006#ifdef INET6
7007 struct sockaddr_in6 sin6;
7008#endif
7009
7010 /* First get the destination address setup too. */
7011#ifdef INET
7012 memset(&sin, 0, sizeof(sin));
7013 sin.sin_family = AF_INET;
7014#ifdef HAVE_SIN_LEN
7015 sin.sin_len = sizeof(sin);
7016#endif
7017 sin.sin_port = stcb->rport;
7018#endif
7019#ifdef INET6
7020 memset(&sin6, 0, sizeof(sin6));
7021 sin6.sin6_family = AF_INET6;
7022#ifdef HAVE_SIN6_LEN
7023 sin6.sin6_len = sizeof(struct sockaddr_in6);
7024#endif
7025 sin6.sin6_port = stcb->rport;
7026#endif
7027 if (altsa) {
7028 sa = altsa;
7029 } else {
7030 sa = src;
7031 }
7032 peer_supports_idata = 0;
7033 peer_supports_ecn = 0;
7034 peer_supports_prsctp = 0;
7035 peer_supports_auth = 0;
7036 peer_supports_asconf = 0;
7037 peer_supports_asconf_ack = 0;
7038 peer_supports_reconfig = 0;
7039 peer_supports_nrsack = 0;
7040 peer_supports_pktdrop = 0;
7041 TAILQ_FOREACH(net, &stcb->asoc.nets, sctp_next) {
7042 /* mark all addresses that we have currently on the list */
7043 net->dest_state |= SCTP_ADDR_NOT_IN_ASSOC;
7044 }
7045 /* does the source address already exist? if so skip it */
7046 inp = stcb->sctp_ep;
7047 atomic_add_int(&stcb->asoc.refcnt, 1);
7048 stcb_tmp = sctp_findassociation_ep_addr(&inp, sa, &net_tmp, dst, stcb);
7049 atomic_add_int(&stcb->asoc.refcnt, -1);
7050
7051 if ((stcb_tmp == NULL && inp == stcb->sctp_ep) || inp == NULL) {
7052 /* we must add the source address */
7053 /* no scope set here since we have a tcb already. */
7054 switch (sa->sa_family) {
7055#ifdef INET
7056 case AF_INET:
7057 if (stcb->asoc.scope.ipv4_addr_legal) {
7058 if (sctp_add_remote_addr(stcb, sa, NULL, port, SCTP_DONOT_SETSCOPE, SCTP_LOAD_ADDR_2)) {
7059 return (-1);
7060 }
7061 }
7062 break;
7063#endif
7064#ifdef INET6
7065 case AF_INET6:
7066 if (stcb->asoc.scope.ipv6_addr_legal) {
7067 if (sctp_add_remote_addr(stcb, sa, NULL, port, SCTP_DONOT_SETSCOPE, SCTP_LOAD_ADDR_3)) {
7068 return (-2);
7069 }
7070 }
7071 break;
7072#endif
7073#if defined(__Userspace__)
7074 case AF_CONN:
7075 if (stcb->asoc.scope.conn_addr_legal) {
7076 if (sctp_add_remote_addr(stcb, sa, NULL, port, SCTP_DONOT_SETSCOPE, SCTP_LOAD_ADDR_3)) {
7077 return (-2);
7078 }
7079 }
7080 break;
7081#endif
7082 default:
7083 break;
7084 }
7085 } else {
7086 if (net_tmp != NULL && stcb_tmp == stcb) {
7087 net_tmp->dest_state &= ~SCTP_ADDR_NOT_IN_ASSOC;
7088 } else if (stcb_tmp != stcb) {
7089 /* It belongs to another association? */
7090 if (stcb_tmp)
7091 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb_tmp);
7092 return (-3);
7093 }
7094 }
7095 if (stcb->asoc.state == 0) {
7096 /* the assoc was freed? */
7097 return (-4);
7098 }
7099 /* now we must go through each of the params. */
7100 phdr = sctp_get_next_param(m, offset, &param_buf, sizeof(param_buf));
7101 while (phdr) {
7102 ptype = ntohs(phdr->param_type);
7103 plen = ntohs(phdr->param_length);
7104 /*
7105 * SCTP_PRINTF("ptype => %0x, plen => %d\n", (uint32_t)ptype,
7106 * (int)plen);
7107 */
7108 if (offset + plen > limit) {
7109 break;
7110 }
7111 if (plen < sizeof(struct sctp_paramhdr)) {
7112 break;
7113 }
7114#ifdef INET
7115 if (ptype == SCTP_IPV4_ADDRESS) {
7116 if (stcb->asoc.scope.ipv4_addr_legal) {
7117 struct sctp_ipv4addr_param *p4, p4_buf;
7118
7119 /* ok get the v4 address and check/add */
7120 phdr = sctp_get_next_param(m, offset,
7121 (struct sctp_paramhdr *)&p4_buf,
7122 sizeof(p4_buf));
7123 if (plen != sizeof(struct sctp_ipv4addr_param) ||
7124 phdr == NULL) {
7125 return (-5);
7126 }
7127 p4 = (struct sctp_ipv4addr_param *)phdr;
7128 sin.sin_addr.s_addr = p4->addr;
7129 if (IN_MULTICAST(ntohl(sin.sin_addr.s_addr))) {
7130 /* Skip multi-cast addresses */
7131 goto next_param;
7132 }
7133 if ((sin.sin_addr.s_addr == INADDR_BROADCAST) ||
7134 (sin.sin_addr.s_addr == INADDR_ANY)) {
7135 goto next_param;
7136 }
7137 sa = (struct sockaddr *)&sin;
7138 inp = stcb->sctp_ep;
7139 atomic_add_int(&stcb->asoc.refcnt, 1);
7140 stcb_tmp = sctp_findassociation_ep_addr(&inp, sa, &net,
7141 dst, stcb);
7142 atomic_add_int(&stcb->asoc.refcnt, -1);
7143
7144 if ((stcb_tmp == NULL && inp == stcb->sctp_ep) ||
7145 inp == NULL) {
7146 /* we must add the source address */
7147 /*
7148 * no scope set since we have a tcb
7149 * already
7150 */
7151
7152 /*
7153 * we must validate the state again
7154 * here
7155 */
7156 add_it_now:
7157 if (stcb->asoc.state == 0) {
7158 /* the assoc was freed? */
7159 return (-7);
7160 }
7161 if (sctp_add_remote_addr(stcb, sa, NULL, port, SCTP_DONOT_SETSCOPE, SCTP_LOAD_ADDR_4)) {
7162 return (-8);
7163 }
7164 } else if (stcb_tmp == stcb) {
7165 if (stcb->asoc.state == 0) {
7166 /* the assoc was freed? */
7167 return (-10);
7168 }
7169 if (net != NULL) {
7170 /* clear flag */
7171 net->dest_state &=
7172 ~SCTP_ADDR_NOT_IN_ASSOC;
7173 }
7174 } else {
7175 /*
7176 * strange, address is in another
7177 * assoc? straighten out locks.
7178 */
7179 if (stcb_tmp) {
7180 if (SCTP_GET_STATE(stcb_tmp) == SCTP_STATE_COOKIE_WAIT) {
7181 struct mbuf *op_err;
7182 char msg[SCTP_DIAG_INFO_LEN];
7183
7184 /* in setup state we abort this guy */
7185 SCTP_SNPRINTF(msg, sizeof(msg),
7186 "%s:%d at %s", __FILE__, __LINE__, __func__);
7187 op_err = sctp_generate_cause(SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_diag_info_code),
7188 msg);
7189 sctp_abort_an_association(stcb_tmp->sctp_ep,
7190 stcb_tmp, op_err,
7191 SCTP_SO_NOT_LOCKED);
7192 goto add_it_now;
7193 }
7194 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb_tmp);
7195 }
7196
7197 if (stcb->asoc.state == 0) {
7198 /* the assoc was freed? */
7199 return (-12);
7200 }
7201 return (-13);
7202 }
7203 }
7204 } else
7205#endif
7206#ifdef INET6
7207 if (ptype == SCTP_IPV6_ADDRESS) {
7208 if (stcb->asoc.scope.ipv6_addr_legal) {
7209 /* ok get the v6 address and check/add */
7210 struct sctp_ipv6addr_param *p6, p6_buf;
7211
7212 phdr = sctp_get_next_param(m, offset,
7213 (struct sctp_paramhdr *)&p6_buf,
7214 sizeof(p6_buf));
7215 if (plen != sizeof(struct sctp_ipv6addr_param) ||
7216 phdr == NULL) {
7217 return (-14);
7218 }
7219 p6 = (struct sctp_ipv6addr_param *)phdr;
7220 memcpy((caddr_t)&sin6.sin6_addr, p6->addr,
7221 sizeof(p6->addr));
7222 if (IN6_IS_ADDR_MULTICAST(&sin6.sin6_addr)) {
7223 /* Skip multi-cast addresses */
7224 goto next_param;
7225 }
7226 if (IN6_IS_ADDR_LINKLOCAL(&sin6.sin6_addr)) {
7227 /* Link local make no sense without scope */
7228 goto next_param;
7229 }
7230 sa = (struct sockaddr *)&sin6;
7231 inp = stcb->sctp_ep;
7232 atomic_add_int(&stcb->asoc.refcnt, 1);
7233 stcb_tmp = sctp_findassociation_ep_addr(&inp, sa, &net,
7234 dst, stcb);
7235 atomic_add_int(&stcb->asoc.refcnt, -1);
7236 if (stcb_tmp == NULL &&
7237 (inp == stcb->sctp_ep || inp == NULL)) {
7238 /*
7239 * we must validate the state again
7240 * here
7241 */
7242 add_it_now6:
7243 if (stcb->asoc.state == 0) {
7244 /* the assoc was freed? */
7245 return (-16);
7246 }
7247 /*
7248 * we must add the address, no scope
7249 * set
7250 */
7251 if (sctp_add_remote_addr(stcb, sa, NULL, port, SCTP_DONOT_SETSCOPE, SCTP_LOAD_ADDR_5)) {
7252 return (-17);
7253 }
7254 } else if (stcb_tmp == stcb) {
7255 /*
7256 * we must validate the state again
7257 * here
7258 */
7259 if (stcb->asoc.state == 0) {
7260 /* the assoc was freed? */
7261 return (-19);
7262 }
7263 if (net != NULL) {
7264 /* clear flag */
7265 net->dest_state &=
7266 ~SCTP_ADDR_NOT_IN_ASSOC;
7267 }
7268 } else {
7269 /*
7270 * strange, address is in another
7271 * assoc? straighten out locks.
7272 */
7273 if (stcb_tmp) {
7274 if (SCTP_GET_STATE(stcb_tmp) == SCTP_STATE_COOKIE_WAIT) {
7275 struct mbuf *op_err;
7276 char msg[SCTP_DIAG_INFO_LEN];
7277
7278 /* in setup state we abort this guy */
7279 SCTP_SNPRINTF(msg, sizeof(msg),
7280 "%s:%d at %s", __FILE__, __LINE__, __func__);
7281 op_err = sctp_generate_cause(SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_diag_info_code),
7282 msg);
7283 sctp_abort_an_association(stcb_tmp->sctp_ep,
7284 stcb_tmp, op_err,
7285 SCTP_SO_NOT_LOCKED);
7286 goto add_it_now6;
7287 }
7288 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb_tmp);
7289 }
7290 if (stcb->asoc.state == 0) {
7291 /* the assoc was freed? */
7292 return (-21);
7293 }
7294 return (-22);
7295 }
7296 }
7297 } else
7298#endif
7299 if (ptype == SCTP_ECN_CAPABLE) {
7300 peer_supports_ecn = 1;
7301 } else if (ptype == SCTP_ULP_ADAPTATION) {
7302 if (stcb->asoc.state != SCTP_STATE_OPEN) {
7303 struct sctp_adaptation_layer_indication ai, *aip;
7304
7305 phdr = sctp_get_next_param(m, offset,
7306 (struct sctp_paramhdr *)&ai, sizeof(ai));
7307 aip = (struct sctp_adaptation_layer_indication *)phdr;
7308 if (aip) {
7309 stcb->asoc.peers_adaptation = ntohl(aip->indication);
7310 stcb->asoc.adaptation_needed = 1;
7311 }
7312 }
7313 } else if (ptype == SCTP_SET_PRIM_ADDR) {
7314 struct sctp_asconf_addr_param lstore, *fee;
7315 int lptype;
7316 struct sockaddr *lsa = NULL;
7317#ifdef INET
7318 struct sctp_asconf_addrv4_param *fii;
7319#endif
7320
7321 if (stcb->asoc.asconf_supported == 0) {
7322 return (-100);
7323 }
7324 if (plen > sizeof(lstore)) {
7325 return (-23);
7326 }
7327 if (plen < sizeof(struct sctp_asconf_addrv4_param)) {
7328 return (-101);
7329 }
7330 phdr = sctp_get_next_param(m, offset,
7331 (struct sctp_paramhdr *)&lstore,
7332 plen);
7333 if (phdr == NULL) {
7334 return (-24);
7335 }
7336 fee = (struct sctp_asconf_addr_param *)phdr;
7337 lptype = ntohs(fee->addrp.ph.param_type);
7338 switch (lptype) {
7339#ifdef INET
7340 case SCTP_IPV4_ADDRESS:
7341 if (plen !=
7342 sizeof(struct sctp_asconf_addrv4_param)) {
7343 SCTP_PRINTF("Sizeof setprim in init/init ack not %d but %d - ignored\n",
7344 (int)sizeof(struct sctp_asconf_addrv4_param),
7345 plen);
7346 } else {
7347 fii = (struct sctp_asconf_addrv4_param *)fee;
7348 sin.sin_addr.s_addr = fii->addrp.addr;
7349 lsa = (struct sockaddr *)&sin;
7350 }
7351 break;
7352#endif
7353#ifdef INET6
7354 case SCTP_IPV6_ADDRESS:
7355 if (plen !=
7356 sizeof(struct sctp_asconf_addr_param)) {
7357 SCTP_PRINTF("Sizeof setprim (v6) in init/init ack not %d but %d - ignored\n",
7358 (int)sizeof(struct sctp_asconf_addr_param),
7359 plen);
7360 } else {
7361 memcpy(sin6.sin6_addr.s6_addr,
7362 fee->addrp.addr,
7363 sizeof(fee->addrp.addr));
7364 lsa = (struct sockaddr *)&sin6;
7365 }
7366 break;
7367#endif
7368 default:
7369 break;
7370 }
7371 if (lsa) {
7372 (void)sctp_set_primary_addr(stcb, sa, NULL);
7373 }
7374 } else if (ptype == SCTP_HAS_NAT_SUPPORT) {
7375 stcb->asoc.peer_supports_nat = 1;
7376 } else if (ptype == SCTP_PRSCTP_SUPPORTED) {
7377 /* Peer supports pr-sctp */
7378 peer_supports_prsctp = 1;
7379 } else if (ptype == SCTP_SUPPORTED_CHUNK_EXT) {
7380 /* A supported extension chunk */
7381 struct sctp_supported_chunk_types_param *pr_supported;
7382 uint8_t local_store[SCTP_PARAM_BUFFER_SIZE];
7383 int num_ent, i;
7384
7385 if (plen > sizeof(local_store)) {
7386 return (-35);
7387 }
7388 phdr = sctp_get_next_param(m, offset,
7389 (struct sctp_paramhdr *)&local_store, plen);
7390 if (phdr == NULL) {
7391 return (-25);
7392 }
7393 pr_supported = (struct sctp_supported_chunk_types_param *)phdr;
7394 num_ent = plen - sizeof(struct sctp_paramhdr);
7395 for (i = 0; i < num_ent; i++) {
7396 switch (pr_supported->chunk_types[i]) {
7397 case SCTP_ASCONF:
7398 peer_supports_asconf = 1;
7399 break;
7400 case SCTP_ASCONF_ACK:
7401 peer_supports_asconf_ack = 1;
7402 break;
7403 case SCTP_FORWARD_CUM_TSN:
7404 peer_supports_prsctp = 1;
7405 break;
7406 case SCTP_PACKET_DROPPED:
7407 peer_supports_pktdrop = 1;
7408 break;
7409 case SCTP_NR_SELECTIVE_ACK:
7410 peer_supports_nrsack = 1;
7411 break;
7412 case SCTP_STREAM_RESET:
7413 peer_supports_reconfig = 1;
7414 break;
7415 case SCTP_AUTHENTICATION:
7416 peer_supports_auth = 1;
7417 break;
7418 case SCTP_IDATA:
7419 peer_supports_idata = 1;
7420 break;
7421 default:
7422 /* one I have not learned yet */
7423 break;
7424 }
7425 }
7426 } else if (ptype == SCTP_RANDOM) {
7427 if (plen > sizeof(random_store))
7428 break;
7429 if (got_random) {
7430 /* already processed a RANDOM */
7431 goto next_param;
7432 }
7433 phdr = sctp_get_next_param(m, offset,
7434 (struct sctp_paramhdr *)random_store,
7435 plen);
7436 if (phdr == NULL)
7437 return (-26);
7438 p_random = (struct sctp_auth_random *)phdr;
7439 random_len = plen - sizeof(*p_random);
7440 /* enforce the random length */
7441 if (random_len != SCTP_AUTH_RANDOM_SIZE_REQUIRED) {
7442 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_AUTH1, "SCTP: invalid RANDOM len\n");
7443 return (-27);
7444 }
7445 got_random = 1;
7446 } else if (ptype == SCTP_HMAC_LIST) {
7447 uint16_t num_hmacs;
7448 uint16_t i;
7449
7450 if (plen > sizeof(hmacs_store))
7451 break;
7452 if (got_hmacs) {
7453 /* already processed a HMAC list */
7454 goto next_param;
7455 }
7456 phdr = sctp_get_next_param(m, offset,
7457 (struct sctp_paramhdr *)hmacs_store,
7458 plen);
7459 if (phdr == NULL)
7460 return (-28);
7461 hmacs = (struct sctp_auth_hmac_algo *)phdr;
7462 hmacs_len = plen - sizeof(*hmacs);
7463 num_hmacs = hmacs_len / sizeof(hmacs->hmac_ids[0]);
7464 /* validate the hmac list */
7465 if (sctp_verify_hmac_param(hmacs, num_hmacs)) {
7466 return (-29);
7467 }
7468 if (stcb->asoc.peer_hmacs != NULL)
7469 sctp_free_hmaclist(stcb->asoc.peer_hmacs);
7470 stcb->asoc.peer_hmacs = sctp_alloc_hmaclist(num_hmacs);
7471 if (stcb->asoc.peer_hmacs != NULL) {
7472 for (i = 0; i < num_hmacs; i++) {
7473 (void)sctp_auth_add_hmacid(stcb->asoc.peer_hmacs,
7474 ntohs(hmacs->hmac_ids[i]));
7475 }
7476 }
7477 got_hmacs = 1;
7478 } else if (ptype == SCTP_CHUNK_LIST) {
7479 int i;
7480
7481 if (plen > sizeof(chunks_store))
7482 break;
7483 if (got_chklist) {
7484 /* already processed a Chunks list */
7485 goto next_param;
7486 }
7487 phdr = sctp_get_next_param(m, offset,
7488 (struct sctp_paramhdr *)chunks_store,
7489 plen);
7490 if (phdr == NULL)
7491 return (-30);
7492 chunks = (struct sctp_auth_chunk_list *)phdr;
7493 num_chunks = plen - sizeof(*chunks);
7494 if (stcb->asoc.peer_auth_chunks != NULL)
7495 sctp_clear_chunklist(stcb->asoc.peer_auth_chunks);
7496 else
7497 stcb->asoc.peer_auth_chunks = sctp_alloc_chunklist();
7498 for (i = 0; i < num_chunks; i++) {
7499 (void)sctp_auth_add_chunk(chunks->chunk_types[i],
7500 stcb->asoc.peer_auth_chunks);
7501 /* record asconf/asconf-ack if listed */
7502 if (chunks->chunk_types[i] == SCTP_ASCONF)
7503 saw_asconf = 1;
7504 if (chunks->chunk_types[i] == SCTP_ASCONF_ACK)
7505 saw_asconf_ack = 1;
7506 }
7507 got_chklist = 1;
7508 } else if ((ptype == SCTP_HEARTBEAT_INFO) ||
7509 (ptype == SCTP_STATE_COOKIE) ||
7510 (ptype == SCTP_UNRECOG_PARAM) ||
7511 (ptype == SCTP_COOKIE_PRESERVE) ||
7512 (ptype == SCTP_SUPPORTED_ADDRTYPE) ||
7513 (ptype == SCTP_ADD_IP_ADDRESS) ||
7514 (ptype == SCTP_DEL_IP_ADDRESS) ||
7515 (ptype == SCTP_ERROR_CAUSE_IND) ||
7516 (ptype == SCTP_SUCCESS_REPORT)) {
7517 /* don't care */
7518 } else {
7519 if ((ptype & 0x8000) == 0x0000) {
7520 /*
7521 * must stop processing the rest of the
7522 * param's. Any report bits were handled
7523 * with the call to
7524 * sctp_arethere_unrecognized_parameters()
7525 * when the INIT or INIT-ACK was first seen.
7526 */
7527 break;
7528 }
7529 }
7530
7531 next_param:
7532 offset += SCTP_SIZE32(plen);
7533 if (offset >= limit) {
7534 break;
7535 }
7536 phdr = sctp_get_next_param(m, offset, &param_buf,
7537 sizeof(param_buf));
7538 }
7539 /* Now check to see if we need to purge any addresses */
7540 TAILQ_FOREACH_SAFE(net, &stcb->asoc.nets, sctp_next, nnet) {
7541 if ((net->dest_state & SCTP_ADDR_NOT_IN_ASSOC) ==
7542 SCTP_ADDR_NOT_IN_ASSOC) {
7543 /* This address has been removed from the asoc */
7544 /* remove and free it */
7545 stcb->asoc.numnets--;
7546 TAILQ_REMOVE(&stcb->asoc.nets, net, sctp_next);
7547 if (net == stcb->asoc.alternate) {
7548 sctp_free_remote_addr(stcb->asoc.alternate);
7549 stcb->asoc.alternate = NULL;
7550 }
7551 if (net == stcb->asoc.primary_destination) {
7552 stcb->asoc.primary_destination = NULL;
7553 sctp_select_primary_destination(stcb);
7554 }
7555 sctp_free_remote_addr(net);
7556 }
7557 }
7558 if ((stcb->asoc.ecn_supported == 1) &&
7559 (peer_supports_ecn == 0)) {
7560 stcb->asoc.ecn_supported = 0;
7561 }
7562 if ((stcb->asoc.prsctp_supported == 1) &&
7563 (peer_supports_prsctp == 0)) {
7564 stcb->asoc.prsctp_supported = 0;
7565 }
7566 if ((stcb->asoc.auth_supported == 1) &&
7567 ((peer_supports_auth == 0) ||
7568 (got_random == 0) || (got_hmacs == 0))) {
7569 stcb->asoc.auth_supported = 0;
7570 }
7571 if ((stcb->asoc.asconf_supported == 1) &&
7572 ((peer_supports_asconf == 0) || (peer_supports_asconf_ack == 0) ||
7573 (stcb->asoc.auth_supported == 0) ||
7574 (saw_asconf == 0) || (saw_asconf_ack == 0))) {
7575 stcb->asoc.asconf_supported = 0;
7576 }
7577 if ((stcb->asoc.reconfig_supported == 1) &&
7578 (peer_supports_reconfig == 0)) {
7579 stcb->asoc.reconfig_supported = 0;
7580 }
7581 if ((stcb->asoc.idata_supported == 1) &&
7582 (peer_supports_idata == 0)) {
7583 stcb->asoc.idata_supported = 0;
7584 }
7585 if ((stcb->asoc.nrsack_supported == 1) &&
7586 (peer_supports_nrsack == 0)) {
7587 stcb->asoc.nrsack_supported = 0;
7588 }
7589 if ((stcb->asoc.pktdrop_supported == 1) &&
7590 (peer_supports_pktdrop == 0)){
7591 stcb->asoc.pktdrop_supported = 0;
7592 }
7593 /* validate authentication required parameters */
7594 if ((peer_supports_auth == 0) && (got_chklist == 1)) {
7595 /* peer does not support auth but sent a chunks list? */
7596 return (-31);
7597 }
7598 if ((peer_supports_asconf == 1) && (peer_supports_auth == 0)) {
7599 /* peer supports asconf but not auth? */
7600 return (-32);
7601 } else if ((peer_supports_asconf == 1) &&
7602 (peer_supports_auth == 1) &&
7603 ((saw_asconf == 0) || (saw_asconf_ack == 0))) {
7604 return (-33);
7605 }
7606 /* concatenate the full random key */
7607 keylen = sizeof(*p_random) + random_len + sizeof(*hmacs) + hmacs_len;
7608 if (chunks != NULL) {
7609 keylen += sizeof(*chunks) + num_chunks;
7610 }
7611 new_key = sctp_alloc_key(keylen);
7612 if (new_key != NULL) {
7613 /* copy in the RANDOM */
7614 if (p_random != NULL) {
7615 keylen = sizeof(*p_random) + random_len;
7616 memcpy(new_key->key, p_random, keylen);
7617 } else {
7618 keylen = 0;
7619 }
7620 /* append in the AUTH chunks */
7621 if (chunks != NULL) {
7622 memcpy(new_key->key + keylen, chunks,
7623 sizeof(*chunks) + num_chunks);
7624 keylen += sizeof(*chunks) + num_chunks;
7625 }
7626 /* append in the HMACs */
7627 if (hmacs != NULL) {
7628 memcpy(new_key->key + keylen, hmacs,
7629 sizeof(*hmacs) + hmacs_len);
7630 }
7631 } else {
7632 /* failed to get memory for the key */
7633 return (-34);
7634 }
7635 if (stcb->asoc.authinfo.peer_random != NULL)
7636 sctp_free_key(stcb->asoc.authinfo.peer_random);
7637 stcb->asoc.authinfo.peer_random = new_key;
7638 sctp_clear_cachedkeys(stcb, stcb->asoc.authinfo.assoc_keyid);
7639 sctp_clear_cachedkeys(stcb, stcb->asoc.authinfo.recv_keyid);
7640
7641 return (0);
7642}
7643
7644int
7645sctp_set_primary_addr(struct sctp_tcb *stcb, struct sockaddr *sa,
7646 struct sctp_nets *net)
7647{
7648 /* make sure the requested primary address exists in the assoc */
7649 if (net == NULL && sa)
7650 net = sctp_findnet(stcb, sa);
7651
7652 if (net == NULL) {
7653 /* didn't find the requested primary address! */
7654 return (-1);
7655 } else {
7656 /* set the primary address */
7657 if (net->dest_state & SCTP_ADDR_UNCONFIRMED) {
7658 /* Must be confirmed, so queue to set */
7659 net->dest_state |= SCTP_ADDR_REQ_PRIMARY;
7660 return (0);
7661 }
7662 stcb->asoc.primary_destination = net;
7663 if (!(net->dest_state & SCTP_ADDR_PF) && (stcb->asoc.alternate)) {
7664 sctp_free_remote_addr(stcb->asoc.alternate);
7665 stcb->asoc.alternate = NULL;
7666 }
7667 net = TAILQ_FIRST(&stcb->asoc.nets);
7668 if (net != stcb->asoc.primary_destination) {
7669 /* first one on the list is NOT the primary
7670 * sctp_cmpaddr() is much more efficient if
7671 * the primary is the first on the list, make it
7672 * so.
7673 */
7674 TAILQ_REMOVE(&stcb->asoc.nets, stcb->asoc.primary_destination, sctp_next);
7675 TAILQ_INSERT_HEAD(&stcb->asoc.nets, stcb->asoc.primary_destination, sctp_next);
7676 }
7677 return (0);
7678 }
7679}
7680
7681int
7682sctp_is_vtag_good(uint32_t tag, uint16_t lport, uint16_t rport, struct timeval *now)
7683{
7684 /*
7685 * This function serves two purposes. It will see if a TAG can be
7686 * re-used and return 1 for yes it is ok and 0 for don't use that
7687 * tag. A secondary function it will do is purge out old tags that
7688 * can be removed.
7689 */
7690 struct sctpvtaghead *chain;
7691 struct sctp_tagblock *twait_block;
7692 struct sctpasochead *head;
7693 struct sctp_tcb *stcb;
7694 int i;
7695
7696 SCTP_INP_INFO_RLOCK();
7697 head = &SCTP_BASE_INFO(sctp_asochash)[SCTP_PCBHASH_ASOC(tag,
7698 SCTP_BASE_INFO(hashasocmark))];
7699 LIST_FOREACH(stcb, head, sctp_asocs) {
7700 /* We choose not to lock anything here. TCB's can't be
7701 * removed since we have the read lock, so they can't
7702 * be freed on us, same thing for the INP. I may
7703 * be wrong with this assumption, but we will go
7704 * with it for now :-)
7705 */
7706 if (stcb->sctp_ep->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_SOCKET_ALLGONE) {
7707 continue;
7708 }
7709 if (stcb->asoc.my_vtag == tag) {
7710 /* candidate */
7711 if (stcb->rport != rport) {
7712 continue;
7713 }
7714 if (stcb->sctp_ep->sctp_lport != lport) {
7715 continue;
7716 }
7717 /* Its a used tag set */
7718 SCTP_INP_INFO_RUNLOCK();
7719 return (0);
7720 }
7721 }
7722 chain = &SCTP_BASE_INFO(vtag_timewait)[(tag % SCTP_STACK_VTAG_HASH_SIZE)];
7723 /* Now what about timed wait ? */
7724 LIST_FOREACH(twait_block, chain, sctp_nxt_tagblock) {
7725 /*
7726 * Block(s) are present, lets see if we have this tag in the
7727 * list
7728 */
7729 for (i = 0; i < SCTP_NUMBER_IN_VTAG_BLOCK; i++) {
7730 if (twait_block->vtag_block[i].v_tag == 0) {
7731 /* not used */
7732 continue;
7733 } else if ((long)twait_block->vtag_block[i].tv_sec_at_expire <
7734 now->tv_sec) {
7735 /* Audit expires this guy */
7736 twait_block->vtag_block[i].tv_sec_at_expire = 0;
7737 twait_block->vtag_block[i].v_tag = 0;
7738 twait_block->vtag_block[i].lport = 0;
7739 twait_block->vtag_block[i].rport = 0;
7740 } else if ((twait_block->vtag_block[i].v_tag == tag) &&
7741 (twait_block->vtag_block[i].lport == lport) &&
7742 (twait_block->vtag_block[i].rport == rport)) {
7743 /* Bad tag, sorry :< */
7744 SCTP_INP_INFO_RUNLOCK();
7745 return (0);
7746 }
7747 }
7748 }
7749 SCTP_INP_INFO_RUNLOCK();
7750 return (1);
7751}
7752
7753static void
7754sctp_drain_mbufs(struct sctp_tcb *stcb)
7755{
7756 /*
7757 * We must hunt this association for MBUF's past the cumack (i.e.
7758 * out of order data that we can renege on).
7759 */
7760 struct sctp_association *asoc;
7761 struct sctp_tmit_chunk *chk, *nchk;
7762 uint32_t cumulative_tsn_p1;
7763 struct sctp_queued_to_read *control, *ncontrol;
7764 int cnt, strmat;
7765 uint32_t gap, i;
7766 int fnd = 0;
7767
7768 /* We look for anything larger than the cum-ack + 1 */
7769
7770 asoc = &stcb->asoc;
7771 if (asoc->cumulative_tsn == asoc->highest_tsn_inside_map) {
7772 /* none we can reneg on. */
7773 return;
7774 }
7775 SCTP_STAT_INCR(sctps_protocol_drains_done);
7776 cumulative_tsn_p1 = asoc->cumulative_tsn + 1;
7777 cnt = 0;
7778 /* Ok that was fun, now we will drain all the inbound streams? */
7779 for (strmat = 0; strmat < asoc->streamincnt; strmat++) {
7780 TAILQ_FOREACH_SAFE(control, &asoc->strmin[strmat].inqueue, next_instrm, ncontrol) {
7781#ifdef INVARIANTS
7782 if (control->on_strm_q != SCTP_ON_ORDERED) {
7783 panic("Huh control: %p on_q: %d -- not ordered?",
7784 control, control->on_strm_q);
7785 }
7786#endif
7787 if (SCTP_TSN_GT(control->sinfo_tsn, cumulative_tsn_p1)) {
7788 /* Yep it is above cum-ack */
7789 cnt++;
7790 SCTP_CALC_TSN_TO_GAP(gap, control->sinfo_tsn, asoc->mapping_array_base_tsn);
7791 KASSERT(control->length > 0, ("control has zero length"));
7792 if (asoc->size_on_all_streams >= control->length) {
7793 asoc->size_on_all_streams -= control->length;
7794 } else {
7795#ifdef INVARIANTS
7796 panic("size_on_all_streams = %u smaller than control length %u", asoc->size_on_all_streams, control->length);
7797#else
7798 asoc->size_on_all_streams = 0;
7799#endif
7800 }
7801 sctp_ucount_decr(asoc->cnt_on_all_streams);
7802 SCTP_UNSET_TSN_PRESENT(asoc->mapping_array, gap);
7803 if (control->on_read_q) {
7804 TAILQ_REMOVE(&stcb->sctp_ep->read_queue, control, next);
7805 control->on_read_q = 0;
7806 }
7807 TAILQ_REMOVE(&asoc->strmin[strmat].inqueue, control, next_instrm);
7808 control->on_strm_q = 0;
7809 if (control->data) {
7810 sctp_m_freem(control->data);
7811 control->data = NULL;
7812 }
7813 sctp_free_remote_addr(control->whoFrom);
7814 /* Now its reasm? */
7815 TAILQ_FOREACH_SAFE(chk, &control->reasm, sctp_next, nchk) {
7816 cnt++;
7817 SCTP_CALC_TSN_TO_GAP(gap, chk->rec.data.tsn, asoc->mapping_array_base_tsn);
7818 KASSERT(chk->send_size > 0, ("chunk has zero length"));
7819 if (asoc->size_on_reasm_queue >= chk->send_size) {
7820 asoc->size_on_reasm_queue -= chk->send_size;
7821 } else {
7822#ifdef INVARIANTS
7823 panic("size_on_reasm_queue = %u smaller than chunk length %u", asoc->size_on_reasm_queue, chk->send_size);
7824#else
7825 asoc->size_on_reasm_queue = 0;
7826#endif
7827 }
7828 sctp_ucount_decr(asoc->cnt_on_reasm_queue);
7829 SCTP_UNSET_TSN_PRESENT(asoc->mapping_array, gap);
7830 TAILQ_REMOVE(&control->reasm, chk, sctp_next);
7831 if (chk->data) {
7832 sctp_m_freem(chk->data);
7833 chk->data = NULL;
7834 }
7835 sctp_free_a_chunk(stcb, chk, SCTP_SO_NOT_LOCKED);
7836 }
7837 sctp_free_a_readq(stcb, control);
7838 }
7839 }
7840 TAILQ_FOREACH_SAFE(control, &asoc->strmin[strmat].uno_inqueue, next_instrm, ncontrol) {
7841#ifdef INVARIANTS
7842 if (control->on_strm_q != SCTP_ON_UNORDERED) {
7843 panic("Huh control: %p on_q: %d -- not unordered?",
7844 control, control->on_strm_q);
7845 }
7846#endif
7847 if (SCTP_TSN_GT(control->sinfo_tsn, cumulative_tsn_p1)) {
7848 /* Yep it is above cum-ack */
7849 cnt++;
7850 SCTP_CALC_TSN_TO_GAP(gap, control->sinfo_tsn, asoc->mapping_array_base_tsn);
7851 KASSERT(control->length > 0, ("control has zero length"));
7852 if (asoc->size_on_all_streams >= control->length) {
7853 asoc->size_on_all_streams -= control->length;
7854 } else {
7855#ifdef INVARIANTS
7856 panic("size_on_all_streams = %u smaller than control length %u", asoc->size_on_all_streams, control->length);
7857#else
7858 asoc->size_on_all_streams = 0;
7859#endif
7860 }
7861 sctp_ucount_decr(asoc->cnt_on_all_streams);
7862 SCTP_UNSET_TSN_PRESENT(asoc->mapping_array, gap);
7863 if (control->on_read_q) {
7864 TAILQ_REMOVE(&stcb->sctp_ep->read_queue, control, next);
7865 control->on_read_q = 0;
7866 }
7867 TAILQ_REMOVE(&asoc->strmin[strmat].uno_inqueue, control, next_instrm);
7868 control->on_strm_q = 0;
7869 if (control->data) {
7870 sctp_m_freem(control->data);
7871 control->data = NULL;
7872 }
7873 sctp_free_remote_addr(control->whoFrom);
7874 /* Now its reasm? */
7875 TAILQ_FOREACH_SAFE(chk, &control->reasm, sctp_next, nchk) {
7876 cnt++;
7877 SCTP_CALC_TSN_TO_GAP(gap, chk->rec.data.tsn, asoc->mapping_array_base_tsn);
7878 KASSERT(chk->send_size > 0, ("chunk has zero length"));
7879 if (asoc->size_on_reasm_queue >= chk->send_size) {
7880 asoc->size_on_reasm_queue -= chk->send_size;
7881 } else {
7882#ifdef INVARIANTS
7883 panic("size_on_reasm_queue = %u smaller than chunk length %u", asoc->size_on_reasm_queue, chk->send_size);
7884#else
7885 asoc->size_on_reasm_queue = 0;
7886#endif
7887 }
7888 sctp_ucount_decr(asoc->cnt_on_reasm_queue);
7889 SCTP_UNSET_TSN_PRESENT(asoc->mapping_array, gap);
7890 TAILQ_REMOVE(&control->reasm, chk, sctp_next);
7891 if (chk->data) {
7892 sctp_m_freem(chk->data);
7893 chk->data = NULL;
7894 }
7895 sctp_free_a_chunk(stcb, chk, SCTP_SO_NOT_LOCKED);
7896 }
7897 sctp_free_a_readq(stcb, control);
7898 }
7899 }
7900 }
7901 if (cnt) {
7902 /* We must back down to see what the new highest is */
7903 for (i = asoc->highest_tsn_inside_map; SCTP_TSN_GE(i, asoc->mapping_array_base_tsn); i--) {
7904 SCTP_CALC_TSN_TO_GAP(gap, i, asoc->mapping_array_base_tsn);
7905 if (SCTP_IS_TSN_PRESENT(asoc->mapping_array, gap)) {
7906 asoc->highest_tsn_inside_map = i;
7907 fnd = 1;
7908 break;
7909 }
7910 }
7911 if (!fnd) {
7912 asoc->highest_tsn_inside_map = asoc->mapping_array_base_tsn - 1;
7913 }
7914
7915 /*
7916 * Question, should we go through the delivery queue? The only
7917 * reason things are on here is the app not reading OR a p-d-api up.
7918 * An attacker COULD send enough in to initiate the PD-API and then
7919 * send a bunch of stuff to other streams... these would wind up on
7920 * the delivery queue.. and then we would not get to them. But in
7921 * order to do this I then have to back-track and un-deliver
7922 * sequence numbers in streams.. el-yucko. I think for now we will
7923 * NOT look at the delivery queue and leave it to be something to
7924 * consider later. An alternative would be to abort the P-D-API with
7925 * a notification and then deliver the data.... Or another method
7926 * might be to keep track of how many times the situation occurs and
7927 * if we see a possible attack underway just abort the association.
7928 */
7929#ifdef SCTP_DEBUG
7930 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_PCB1, "Freed %d chunks from reneg harvest\n", cnt);
7931#endif
7932 /*
7933 * Now do we need to find a new
7934 * asoc->highest_tsn_inside_map?
7935 */
7936 asoc->last_revoke_count = cnt;
7937 sctp_timer_stop(SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_RECV, stcb->sctp_ep, stcb, NULL,
7938 SCTP_FROM_SCTP_PCB + SCTP_LOC_11);
7939 /*sa_ignore NO_NULL_CHK*/
7940 sctp_send_sack(stcb, SCTP_SO_NOT_LOCKED);
7941 sctp_chunk_output(stcb->sctp_ep, stcb, SCTP_OUTPUT_FROM_DRAIN, SCTP_SO_NOT_LOCKED);
7942 }
7943 /*
7944 * Another issue, in un-setting the TSN's in the mapping array we
7945 * DID NOT adjust the highest_tsn marker. This will cause one of two
7946 * things to occur. It may cause us to do extra work in checking for
7947 * our mapping array movement. More importantly it may cause us to
7948 * SACK every datagram. This may not be a bad thing though since we
7949 * will recover once we get our cum-ack above and all this stuff we
7950 * dumped recovered.
7951 */
7952}
7953
7954void
7955sctp_drain()
7956{
7957 /*
7958 * We must walk the PCB lists for ALL associations here. The system
7959 * is LOW on MBUF's and needs help. This is where reneging will
7960 * occur. We really hope this does NOT happen!
7961 */
7962#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
7963 VNET_ITERATOR_DECL(vnet_iter);
7964#else
7965 struct sctp_inpcb *inp;
7966 struct sctp_tcb *stcb;
7967
7968 SCTP_STAT_INCR(sctps_protocol_drain_calls);
7969 if (SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_do_drain) == 0) {
7970 return;
7971 }
7972#endif
7973#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
7974 VNET_LIST_RLOCK_NOSLEEP();
7975 VNET_FOREACH(vnet_iter) {
7976 CURVNET_SET(vnet_iter);
7977 struct sctp_inpcb *inp;
7978 struct sctp_tcb *stcb;
7979#endif
7980
7981#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
7982 SCTP_STAT_INCR(sctps_protocol_drain_calls);
7983 if (SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_do_drain) == 0) {
7984#ifdef VIMAGE
7985 continue;
7986#else
7987 return;
7988#endif
7989 }
7990#endif
7991 SCTP_INP_INFO_RLOCK();
7992 LIST_FOREACH(inp, &SCTP_BASE_INFO(listhead), sctp_list) {
7993 /* For each endpoint */
7994 SCTP_INP_RLOCK(inp);
7995 LIST_FOREACH(stcb, &inp->sctp_asoc_list, sctp_tcblist) {
7996 /* For each association */
7997 SCTP_TCB_LOCK(stcb);
7998 sctp_drain_mbufs(stcb);
7999 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
8000 }
8001 SCTP_INP_RUNLOCK(inp);
8002 }
8003 SCTP_INP_INFO_RUNLOCK();
8004#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
8005 CURVNET_RESTORE();
8006 }
8007 VNET_LIST_RUNLOCK_NOSLEEP();
8008#endif
8009}
8010
8011/*
8012 * start a new iterator
8013 * iterates through all endpoints and associations based on the pcb_state
8014 * flags and asoc_state. "af" (mandatory) is executed for all matching
8015 * assocs and "ef" (optional) is executed when the iterator completes.
8016 * "inpf" (optional) is executed for each new endpoint as it is being
8017 * iterated through. inpe (optional) is called when the inp completes
8018 * its way through all the stcbs.
8019 */
8020int
8021sctp_initiate_iterator(inp_func inpf,
8022 asoc_func af,
8023 inp_func inpe,
8024 uint32_t pcb_state,
8025 uint32_t pcb_features,
8026 uint32_t asoc_state,
8027 void *argp,
8028 uint32_t argi,
8029 end_func ef,
8030 struct sctp_inpcb *s_inp,
8031 uint8_t chunk_output_off)
8032{
8033 struct sctp_iterator *it = NULL;
8034
8035 if (af == NULL) {
8036 return (-1);
8037 }
8038 if (SCTP_BASE_VAR(sctp_pcb_initialized) == 0) {
8039 SCTP_PRINTF("%s: abort on initialize being %d\n", __func__,
8040 SCTP_BASE_VAR(sctp_pcb_initialized));
8041 return (-1);
8042 }
8043 SCTP_MALLOC(it, struct sctp_iterator *, sizeof(struct sctp_iterator),
8044 SCTP_M_ITER);
8045 if (it == NULL) {
8046 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(NULL, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_PCB, ENOMEM);
8047 return (-1);
8048 }
8049 memset(it, 0, sizeof(*it));
8050 it->function_assoc = af;
8051 it->function_inp = inpf;
8052 if (inpf)
8053 it->done_current_ep = 0;
8054 else
8055 it->done_current_ep = 1;
8056 it->function_atend = ef;
8057 it->pointer = argp;
8058 it->val = argi;
8059 it->pcb_flags = pcb_state;
8060 it->pcb_features = pcb_features;
8061 it->asoc_state = asoc_state;
8062 it->function_inp_end = inpe;
8063 it->no_chunk_output = chunk_output_off;
8064#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
8065 it->vn = curvnet;
8066#endif
8067 if (s_inp) {
8068 /* Assume lock is held here */
8069 it->inp = s_inp;
8070 SCTP_INP_INCR_REF(it->inp);
8071 it->iterator_flags = SCTP_ITERATOR_DO_SINGLE_INP;
8072 } else {
8073 SCTP_INP_INFO_RLOCK();
8074 it->inp = LIST_FIRST(&SCTP_BASE_INFO(listhead));
8075 if (it->inp) {
8076 SCTP_INP_INCR_REF(it->inp);
8077 }
8078 SCTP_INP_INFO_RUNLOCK();
8079 it->iterator_flags = SCTP_ITERATOR_DO_ALL_INP;
8080 }
8081 SCTP_IPI_ITERATOR_WQ_LOCK();
8082 if (SCTP_BASE_VAR(sctp_pcb_initialized) == 0) {
8083 SCTP_IPI_ITERATOR_WQ_UNLOCK();
8084 SCTP_PRINTF("%s: rollback on initialize being %d it=%p\n", __func__,
8085 SCTP_BASE_VAR(sctp_pcb_initialized), it);
8086 SCTP_FREE(it, SCTP_M_ITER);
8087 return (-1);
8088 }
8089 TAILQ_INSERT_TAIL(&sctp_it_ctl.iteratorhead, it, sctp_nxt_itr);
8090 if (sctp_it_ctl.iterator_running == 0) {
8091 sctp_wakeup_iterator();
8092 }
8093 SCTP_IPI_ITERATOR_WQ_UNLOCK();
8094 /* sa_ignore MEMLEAK {memory is put on the tailq for the iterator} */
8095 return (0);
8096}
